column6: Hada Labo UV Moist Emulsion SPF50+ PA+++ 38mL Sunscreen
column13: Good for winter, but not too greasy.
column14:
I have very dry, very sensitive and acne prone skin. On top of that, I am about an NC~5 and burn simply from sitting in my room near a sunny window. In short, I need a very dependable sunscreen with great protection that works with my skin.

In the summer I love to use the Hada Labo UV Creamy Gel. It offers fantastic UVA and UVB protection and has a nice finish. However, in the winter, that sunscreen is just too drying for me and I get flaky skin. So I needed something that still had good protection and was more moisturizing.

In terms of feel, this is a slightly greasier sunscreen than all the ones with alcohol in them. I think it is simply impossible to not use alcohol in sunscreen and get a super dry matte finish. But I don't mind the formula. It goes on very moist at the beginning, but doesn't look greasy or anything. You can definitely wear makeup over it. Great for the winter time.

However, this sunscreen is only a PA +++ instead of a PA ++++ like the UV Creamy Gel, which is why I had to take off a star. For someone who is very serious about sun protection, the UVA blocking abilities are very important, and I prefer to have the max.

The bottle is also rather small and be sure to give it a good shake before using!

column6: Emjoi AP-18R Emagine Dual Opposed 72 Tweezer Head Epilator, Violet
column13: A Bargain without sacrifice of quality!
column14: I purchased this in April 2014, so I've been using it for over a year. I bought it to replace my Braun SE 7181 WD Silk Epil 7 Epilator Xpressive Pro, Orange/Copper which cost only $79 and change at the time. It is now $115. I loved the Braun epilator, but it was no longer holding much of a charge. Unlike this unit the Braun cannot be used with the charger plugged in. I paid $95 for the Emjoi. It is only $59 now! Though I still like the Braun a little bit more than the Emjoi because it required less time to use as it is a more efficient epilator I recommend this one. It is worth a little extra time to spend slightly more than half the cost of the Braun. Also the fact that it can be used with the charger plugged in is a great advantage. I suspect that the Braun did not allow use while plugged in because it was a wet/dry product. In other words you could use it while bathing. I never found this to be advantageous. Quite the opposite. I find it is much more efficient to use while your skin is dry. Since it takes time to wait for a recharge if it dies half way through I prefer the Emjoi's ability to be used while plugged in. I do no find it painful to epilate with either product, but some people do. When I purchased the Braun I had read a number of reviews that had said it would be very painful. That's true of all the epilators I researched. Perhaps I just have a higher than normal threshold for pain. I've been told that by doctors after all, but I do not find epilating painful. Keep your skin taut while using any epilator, especially when doing your underarms, to avoid catching skin. Catching skin IS painful, for anyone. However, if you are careful this will not be a problem. At the current price this product is a fantastic bargain! I hate shaving. I've been waxed and tried waxing myself. Waxing is just too messy. Even having it done professionally leaves some wax on the skin where they miss during clean up. I've used the epilator everywhere. It is much more efficient.If you pay to be waxed, this will pay for itself in a use or two. You can still get your upper lip waxed as that is not very expensive and this epilator is not meant for facial use. I still use it for my upper lip, but I do not recommend it. It is quite easy to get your actual lip caught. I don't have much hair there. In fact I didn't have any visible hair on my upper lip until I was approaching 40. Now I have a little bit and have become adept enough with the Emjoi to catch it all without injuring myself, but it's not easy so consider yourself warned! For all places below the neck I highly recommend the Emjoi. It is more than worth the price and considerably cheaper than equivalent products. Buy one before the price goes back up, and still consider it even if it the price does increase. It is a worthy product after all.

column13: AWESOME for any rough skin and calluses!
column14: I LOVE this. I'm a barefoot baby. If I could go barefoot all the time I would. However, as a result, I have icky calluses on my big toe and heels. column14:
ok so i have dry frizzy hair. the kind that i can't even wash it two days in a row without it becoming a tangly coarse mess. the kind that i have had every hair dresser i go to say "your hair is so dry you need moisturizing hair shampoo to fix this" even though i had been using every single hair product i could and has just settled into thinking this was just my hair type.

this hair product literally changed my life. i could tell from day one i used it that it was different. it made my hair really soft and smooth! and actually calmed the frizz and made it seem hydrated right out of the shower.
the only downside is that the conditioner kinda has a smokey nut smell, and if you don't use a brush in the shower it makes it tangled? i would suggest using this shampoo and then the keratin conditioner or the vitamin E conditioner with it.
ogx is my favorite brand because many of the shampoos are sulfate free which is nice for dyed hair. and good for your hair in general because it doesn't have that greasy fake "hydrated" feeling afterwards.

if you have coarse dry hair i would really recommend giving this shampoo a try!

column14:
TOCCA Florence is a gorgeous floral scent that I can't get enough of.

I don't get much scent from the top notes of Italian bergamot, grapefruit leaves, green pear or apple. I find the middle floral notes of ivory gardenia, crushed violet petals, jasmine, tuberose and blue iris much more prominent. Okay, I can't really pick out the individual floral scents, but I do get a floral sense. If you a floral fan, like me, give TOCCA Florence a spritz!

column6: ULTIMATE Vitamin C Serum 22% Advanced Proprietary Blend Vitamin C E Ferulic + 11% Hyaluronic + 1% E + 1% Ferulic Acid
column14:
Vitamin C is critical for your body and plays an important role in maintaining healthy, resilient skin. While young skin is full of vitamin C, aging skin naturally loses this nutrient over time. Other factors like exposure to UV light, pollutants and cigarette smoke compound the decline of vitamin C, contributing to signs of aging. The good news is that you can fight back by replenishing your skin‚Äôs vitamin C levels to help to combat and even reverse time‚Äôs effect on your face.
I chose this serum, mostly , to help fade my melasma and sun spots.... Surprisingly it has started to help them...When it comes to treating age spots, you don‚Äôt need chemical peels and lasers ‚Äì it turns out that vitamin C can have almost the same results! Age spots are essentially sun damage, and vitamin C is a powerful antioxidant, shown to reduce the number of sunburned cells as well as reverse age-related damage to skin. While it‚Äôs not a replacement for sunscreen, vitamin C protects against and may repair UV damage like discoloration and fine lines.
I liked the smell, texture and the rapid results from this serum... I did receive this product, free, for unbiased testing purposes...the opinions are my own...

column6: [MIZON] Bee Venom Calming Fresh Cream 50ml (1.69 fl.oz.)
column13: Nice, simple, might be actually effective somehow?
column14:
This is a nice, thick cream in a thick frosted, heavy jar. It doesn't have a discernible scent to me and has a white/barely pinkish cast. Thicker than the Mizon snail creams without the gooey consistency.

The jar is so cute I can't even. It's so heavy for its size though.

I don't use this on my whole face, just on areas that are red and angry from acne. It doesn't burn or sting. The most I get from it feeling wise is a barely noticeable ...tingle? almost like my skin is chilled in that spot for a second or two after it sinks in. I'm not sure yet how calming it will be in the long run but it hasn't broken me out and I almost feel like it made some of my worse spots come to a 'head' overnight as if they were healing faster. Hm. I feel like I'm going to use the jar up and go from there because I like it a lot right now and it hasn't had a negative effect on me yet. The price was good for the amount, too! Don't be scared about the bee venom title--unless, of course, you're severely allergic to bees and in which case I would probably not buy anything with 'bee' in the title ever.

column6: SweatBlock Antiperspirant - Clinical Strength - Reduce Sweat up to 7-days per Use
column14: This works as intended.  I have been trying multiple products and this was the first of what I have tried in order to help me reduce or eliminate excessive sweating at my armpits when I get out of the house.  While it didnt appear that this lasted a week before having to reapply, it did work for several days.  I was very impressed coming from someone who experiences a lot of problems with sweat being exposed on my clothes every time I went out on the night life.  I put this on as directed.  Apply at night.  You will notice the strong cloves odor, but will be unnoticeable by the morning.  No stinging or irritation occured for me versus another product I tried.  My only issue with this is that it is not your ordinary application process.  These come in packets very similar to a wet nap.  You use it once and throw it away.  I did try to save it for another application use which was still a little damp after a few days of storing it back in the package.  This might prolong the need to purchase more frequently.  While this does indeed work, I would have liked a product that you could apply more naturally instead of a wet nap, wipe and throw away process.  Otherwise, this will work for you.  I do not anticipate however, that will last 8 weeks for me.  After 3 days I felt I needed another application.  I would have to buy a good stock of these in order to feel secure and sweat free.  I have to say though, it does work and you will be pleased at how well it works.

column14: I bought this sunscreen because it was recommended by a blogger who was writing about a cure for Melasma (dark spots on the face) which I also have. She specifically recommended this as her favorite brand of sunscreen to wear daily on the face, because it contains SAFE ingredients and is without carcinogens.  If you've read the recent research about sunscreen, popular brands can actually cause cancer once the chemicals interact with sunlight and seep into your skin. Very concerning! I've used this on my face daily for about two months now. A small amount goes a long way. I put my makeup (either liquid or pressed powder foundation) right over the sunscreen and it does not feel oily or anything. It feels great and I think it has done a great job of preventing my melasma from darkening over the summer months.

column6: BENTON Snail Bee High Content Essence
column13: A nice, light product to wear under your moisturizer
column14:
Like many fans of Asian beauty, I enjoy this product. The packaging says it's an "essence," but I consider it more of a very light gel. While the product is moisturizing on its own, I think it works best in tandem with a lotion, especially if you plan to use it at night. The gel is translucent and scentless, and it absorbs quickly into the skin. I've noticed that if I use more than one pump, not all of the product absorbs into my skin, leaving a tacky film on top.

The main ingredient, snail mucin, has quite the reputation abroad. Cosmetics companies laud its many supposed benefits, such as improving skin elasticity, boosting collagen production, evening skin tone, etc. Now, I don't know about all that, but I do love this product. After using it for the better part of a year, I think that I've incurred enough benefit to repurchase. My skin seems healthier than it did before, and it is certainly more moisturized. I don't really believe the manufacturer's claims that this can firm up or even out your skin. However, I think that this is a worthy product given how inexpensive it is.

column6: Hamilton Beach UV Bulb 04810
column13: Fits right, lights up, and may even work!
column14:
We bought this bulb for an older model HB air purifier that was discontinued ages ago but still runs. Decided to stretch its use a little longer so we got new filters and prefilters and this new bulb. It has been a month running nonstop, and no problems with the UV bulb as far as we can tell.

Ours came from Allergy Be Gone, and as I write this review a different vendor name appears atop my screen. Shoppers should note -- with marketplace products you should read the product reviews AND the seller feedback both, as they are two separate topics. Here I am only reviewing the product itself, which is how it is supposed to work.

Years ago, I heard people dismiss the Hamilton Beach system, saying that UV light will only kill germs that are "bathed" in it (meaning they sit in the UV light for a while, rather than flying past quickly, the way they do in a fan-driven air cleaner). I do not know if they are right. The point does make sense but I figure, put the bulb in there and hope for the best. Maybe it will keep us healthier, maybe not, but it seemed worth a try.

We've had this machine for a long time, and our experience with the bulbs was always that they lasted quite a while. The owners manual and the bulb package suggest that you should replace them once a year regardless. Is it necessary? I have no idea! At this point, if the machine itself lasts a year I will feel grateful. :-)

I am giving it 5 stars based on past experience with them lasting a while, and with the new one lighting up readily and still working a month later. That's about all I can go on, and so far I have no complaints.

Occasionally, I might get a tiny pimple, but if spend extra time cleansing that area with this product, the pimple is usually gone in a day or two with no acne scars left behind. However, I have dry skin and a good moisturizer will counteract the effects of the dryness. Overall this product has been a lifesaver.

column6: Cool Mist Humidifier,Oak Leaf 1.3L Multi-Color Room Humidifiers Ultrasonic Essential Oil Diffuser,Large Capacity,7 Color LED Lights,Waterless Auto Shut-Off
column13: Makes my home smell heavenly for hours
column14:
I'm an aromatherapy convert now and I have a diffuser going almost all the time. In my crazy, busy household, I find more and more that the fragrance coming from my diffuser really does have a calming influence on me.

I was particularly excited to get this diffuser from Oak Leaf because of its 250ml capacity. That's more than twice as much as any of my other diffusers!

It arrives beautifully boxed - would make for a lovely presentation if gifting it. The diffuser is a gentle, oval shape and is made of slightly textured, frosted, white plastic. It has a band around the edge that lights a pretty, blue color that you can turn on or off.

To use, lift the top straight off, fill to the marked line with water (measuring cup included), add a 2-5 drops of your favorite essential oil, attach the power cord and plug it in. Push the button on front to select low or high mode and that's it. It immediately begins producing a dry mist that fills the are with fragrance. On the low setting, it lasts all night!

I clean mine by wiping it out completely with a paper towel every few days after the water has diffused down to a low level. I know from experience that wiping it out regularly prolongs the life of the diffuser and prevents bacteria from multiplying.

As others have mentioned, the included manual isn't especially good but it's a simple, beautiful, well-made device that is easy to use.

There may be some confusion about this diffuser because of the product page pictures, but it has only a blue LED light. No other colors. The light is either on or off and there is no color change or blinking or anything else. Just blue light or not. Personally, I like this. The blue is pretty and serves as a night light when I want it. Otherwise, I don't want sounds or changing lights or anything but glorious, long lasting scent to fill my home and this diffuser gives me exactly that.

NOTE: I was provided a free or discounted sample for review but a positive review was not asked for, promised or implied. However, because my daughter liked this one so much, I purchased a second one for her - hence the Amazon Verified Purchase badge that is now appearing.nted sample for review but a positive review was not asked for, promised or implied. column6: Dramatically Different Moisturizing Gel By Clinique, 4.2 Ounce
column13: A great go-to moisturizer for acne prone skin!
column14:
I have always had acne prone skin. When I was a teenager I tried many products from drugstores and found that the moisturizers were usually too heavy for my skin and had a tendency to make me break out. I have tried some moisturizers which are not supposed to clog pores (even those in one of my favorite skincare lines, Mario Badescu) and found that even these products cause breakouts or make my skin feel "coated".

I usually use the moisturizer in the morning and at night and also use all about eyes rich for the delicate skin under my eyes (since I use acne products with salicylic acid to keep my skin clear I know it is important to keep the skin under my eyes from getting dry!).

Clinique dramatically different moisturizing gel is the moisturizer I have come back to time and time again--I am always looking for new products to try to see if another moisturizer will be even better for my skin, but so far I have not found a moisturizer that comes close to supplementing or replacing my Clinique. I have tried Estee Lauder moisturizers also and found them too heavy and rich for my acne prone skin. I will keep experimenting and looking for new moisturizers to try but until I find one that blows dramatically different gel out of the water, it will be my go to moisturizer.

column6: Ivation Mini Nano Ionic Nanocare Facial Steamer
column14:
This is as simple of a device as you will ever own. You pour water in up to the fill line, put the cap back on followed by the large plastic piece that funnels the steam to your face and then press the power button.

In about 3 minutes you'll hear the water bubbling inside and then steam will start coming out at a moderate pace. It is more than enough to help with the sinuses or give your face a good steam cleaning. The steam lasts for about 20 minutes and all you have to do is turn the power back off when you are finished.

The steam is hot, obviously, but not scalding hot which is a good thing for a device that you use at such close quarters.

The base is sturdy but it does get warm when the device is being used. It was not too hot for me to handle it while it was on. The unit is fairly small, the base is about the height of an energy drink can with the base being wider at the bottom than at the top.

Overall this is a nice facial steamer that just does the job simply and effectively with the right amount of steam that won't burn you while you use it. Recommended.

Sample provided for review.

column6: Estee Lauder Double Wear Light Stay-in-Place Makeup 1oz/30ml
column13: Caution--this light makeup may cause breakouts and irritate existing breakouts in acne prone skin!
column14:
Estee Lauder is a great brand and I have bought eyeshadow and blush from their lines with no problems. I have tried both the Double Wear and Double Wear Light foundations and though I love the amount of coverage they provided when I had extremely acne prone skin, I found that the heaviness of the makeup itself only added to the cycle of breakouts that I was having. Unfortunately I had to stop using this foundation completely and give what remained of the bottles to my mom (who has a similar skin tone but drier skin--and she has never had breakouts so the heaviness of makeup is not a concern for her).

Though this makeup says that it is "light" it is only light compared to the original Double Wear it is still far heavier than the majority of the foundations that I have tried over the years. column6: Baby Foot Exfoliant Foot Peel, Lavender Scented, 2.4 Fl. Oz.
column13: Effective. Bizarre. You'll molt like a snake, and then your feet will be crazy smooth.
column14:
These are amazing. They're effective. They are the weirdest, longest pedicure process I've ever undergone. It took several days for the peeling to begin. After I applied the booties, the skin on my feet felt "tight", as if my skin was no longer big enough for my feet, until it started peeling. And then once it starts peeling...ooh, boy. You do not want to go anywhere where your bare feet will be visible. The peeling process is a slow process, taking up to a full week. If you get a good strip to start loosening up, go ahead and peel it. It's oddly gratifying to remove sheets of dead skin. Just be cautious to not be overly aggressive with peeling. Don't peel where it's not clearly loose and easy to lift. The layer of skin under the dead skin needs to toughen up just a bit before it's exposed. If you peel too aggressively, you will make yourself a tender foot and be limping around a day or so! (Ask my husband about his experience with this!) The soles of my feet came off in almost one big piece. It was half gross/half fascinating. They WORK. My feet weren't excessively gross or scaly, but it took 2 treatments, 2 weeks apart to get them really soft. My husband's feet were stereotypical gross man-feet with thick, crusty turtle-shell like man-leather for soles. His crazy thick skin took 3 treatments, 2 weeks apart to get nice and soft. Maintain with a good foot cream with lactic acid in it after your peeling is complete. We like the O'Keeffe's Healthy Feet, conveniently also sold here on Amazon!

I think that if that Buffalo Bill guy from Silence of the Lambs had this product, he would have had to capture and kill way less people to make his people-leather suit. He could have just given all of his friends pedicures and then been their designated peeler. So get these! Not only will you not have to put the lotion in the basket, you also won't get the hose again!

column13: This is a great moisturizer...for someone else.
column14:
I tried this moisturizer when I got it as part of a gift set with purchase at a local department store. I I wanted to see if this would be a light enough moisturizer to make my skin feel hydrated without feeling clogged or feeling heavy on my skin. I love many Estee Lauder products so I was sad to find that although it appears to be a lighter moisturizer (and is lighter than most made by Lauder) it is still too heavy for acne prone skin.

I wish I could love this product, but unfortunately it just does not quite work for my skin, I need something lighter that will not cause breakouts or make my skin feel caked with lotion. I ended up giving the samples that I had to my mom who has drier skin...and ironically enough this lotion was not quite heavy enough for her skin.

I think that with any moisturizer it is important to pay attention to what your skin is telling you and to find one that makes your skin feel its best.

column6: Cosrx Bha Blackhead Power Liquid
column14:
I have super oily skin and blackheads like crazy. Well, I mean I used to have blackheads like crazy. Now, I use this stuff and my skin looks awesome. It's seriously one of my favorite skin-care products of all time and I can't live without it now.

Basically, the liquid sinks into your skin and digs out the gross, clogged up oil in your pores and purges it out. It takes faithful, constant use for complete blackhead eradication, but if you've got really dilated, clogged pores, you will probably see some results immediately. I sure did.
I use this once a day after cleansing (usually at night-time so my skin can purge without ruining my makeup). Two pumps is enough for pretty much my whole face. I rub it in a little, but then I let the rest sink in on its own. I leave it for a couple hours and then come back and clean away the purged oil which keeps my skin from getting too irritated from the excess oil everywhere. (You'll see lots of shiny spots on top of where your blackheads are - that means it's working!!) Then I continue with the rest of my routine.

Keep in Mind:
1. Your skin has to be the right pH balance for BHA (Salicylic Acid) to work. So that means don't expect to get good results if you use it right after an alkaline cleanser or after a very acidic product like a vitamin C serum (it says on the directions not to use a Vit C and a BHA together anyway). Let your skin return to a normal pH before you use it and let it sink in before you apply anything else.
2. USE SUNSCREEN. For the love of god, please use sunscreen. Salicylic Acid makes your skin photosensitive, and I don't care how well you normally tan - you WILL burn if you go out into the sun using this product, which just gives you more skin problems to worry about. There are plenty of sunscreens out there (Currently I use the Japanese Biore Milk Sunscreen) so find a good one that you like FIRST, and THEN use the BHA.

All in all, I love this stuff. It's incredibly effective, but it's also super gentle on my sensitive skin. I have no idea what I did before this, but I am never going back.dibly effective, but it's also super gentle on my sensitive skin. I have no idea what I did before this, but I am never going back.

This hair spray is amazing! I have always wanted a spray to just make my hair look effortlessly curly and wavy and this does a perfect job. It is perfect for summer time because your hair gets damp and humid a lot so not many hairstyles hold throughout the day but if you spray your hair with this spray, it will leave your hair looking carefree and stylish throughout the day. It is also perfect for beaches where there's a lot of wind and you just need that messy, tousled hair with a bit of waves in it. I recommended using it different ways to see what hairstyles you can create with it. Blow drying your hair after wards can also give a nice affect. Brushing out your hair after applying it will loosen the waves and the rough texture of the hair. Try applying it on wet hair to see a grunge like/ wet affect as well. It's an amazing product for such a low price so I definitely recommend people to buy This!

column6: Norvell Venetian Sunless Self-Tanning Mousse with Bronzer - Instant Natural Looking Bronzing Glow, 8 fl.oz.
column13: I look like the sun loves me!
column14:
I have used a ton of lotions, but this is my first mousse. It took a few applications to really get a feel for an application that works for me. I use latex gloves to apply because after the first try I realized that this self tanner does not come off of hands with soap and water like the other self tanners I've used. Do not let this drip or splash on anything because it will leave it's mark forever (my poor sink and wall!). The bottle does not say to shake it, but if I don't it comes out more liquidity than mousse-like, which is how I caused stains in my bathroom. So SHAKE before each pump. I apply to all of my upper body (including face) using small circles until I feel it settling in. It soaks in and dries pretty quickly. It is a very dark brown out of the bottle so I apply this at night and gently wipe it off in the morning. I LOVE the color! It is NOT a subtle color, and what I like best is the color it leaves is tan, NOT ORANGE, with a slight pink hue. Looks like I've naturally been spending hours in the sun. I have had zero problems with streaking. I apply to my face and neck (which never holds color well) every two days to keep the color up and chest and arms maybe every 4-5 days. Best color I've experienced and will most definitely reorder.
Happy (fake) tanning :-)

column6: Philips Norelco PT730 Powertouch Electric Razor
column14: This is my favorite shaver. Why? The HQ8 shaving heads, I like rinsing the shaver, and it's very quiet.  The HQ8 shaving heads are much more comfortable than the Speed XL HQ9 heads and do a better job.  I switched to electric shaving years ago.  Was hooked after the first shave. I haven't cut myself shaving in 20 years. I started with a standard Panasonic, then the Panasonic Linear, Norelco Speed XL(until it died about 15 years), Braun, and now back to Norelco with the 3500.  The Braun is to loud. Very loud! I couldn't take it anymore.  Used it a year and a half. The Norelco does a better job cutting longer hair when I don't shave a couple of days and does a better job on the neck.  Compared to the Braun it seems the motor is wimpy. Don't be fooled.  This shaver cuts well.  My beard is like barbed wire.  Also, I want to mention something I feel is important about skin irritation.  I've very sensitive skin and I noticed the lifters on the shaving head are brass and were causing me irritation. I took the liberty of removing them. They are not needed. Very easy to remove. I'm making no sacrifices removing them. The shave is just as close. Just use a pair of needle nose pliers and a jewelers visor so you can see what your doing.  I did this when I used the Speed XL.  I love the Norelco shaver without the lifters. It's really not difficult to remove them.  Also, this shaver does not come with a travel pouch nor a charging stand.  I contacted Norelco through a chat window on the support site and they are sending me a pouch and charging stand free of charge!  Stellar customer service!  If you are switching to an electric shaver for the first time you may have some irritation because your skin is raw from blade shaving. Give it time and you will never go back.

column14:

I love that the Amazon price is much lower than my local craft supply store. Free 2nd day shipping with Amazon Prime makes it even better. No shopping or gas expense needed to get my supplies right to my door.

I like blending 1/4 cup Shea Butter, 1/2 cup Coconut Oil and 5 drops each Lemon and Lavender essential oils together until they are whipped and combined. I use just a teaspoon or so as a lotion on my legs after shaving. It helps them stay soft and has really cut back on razor burn. I love that this is organic too! Makes me feel even better adding to my skin.

column13: Better than Thierry Mugler's Angel, Strong Green Patchouli
column14: This is one of the most potent fragrance oils I have ever experienced to date. You only need to press (not roll!) the roller ball to your skin and rub in. If you think Thierry Mugler's Angel is strong, this is 5x stronger. The scent itself side by side Thierry Mugler's iconic 23 year old Angel is very similar, especially when first applied, only I think Crystal is better overall. Right off you have that telltale, room filling scent of very green Patchouli that Angel and Jessica Simpson's Fancy Nights' is known for. At this point I'll say if Patchouli is not your thing, especially strong herbal Patchouli, this may not be for you. What makes this better than Angel is underneath all that Patchouli is something closer to how I originally remember Thierry Mugler's Angel smelling. Crystal is slightly sweeter, fresher, and has a more resinous feel compared to how Angel smells today with the level of green Patchouli being much the same between both. Another one of Crown's fragrances, Choco Musk, actually forms the base of Crystal which leaves out the burnt notes I find unpleasant in Angel. With this, there is really no point in owning the original Angel. This small bottle will last forever and if the scent transfers to clothing be prepared to live with Crystal for weeks. Even through repeated washing.

column6: Norvell Premium Sunless Tanning Solution - Venetian
column13: VERY uneven fade, despite proper prep work and post care
column14: To start, a bit of background info....I have used this product and also the St. Tropez professional classic bronzing mist with my tanning system, this is a comparison of the two.  First off, let me say that the color this solution gives off is perfection. I have light to medium yellow toned skin, and this was very, VERY natural looking once the guide color wore off. The color has a beautiful purple toned base...sounds scary, but develops beautifully. Oh, and the color was still natural with the  guide color on after initially spraying it, just very very dark.) The smell was quite pleasant as well, not as strong or perfumey as the St.Tropez products. But alas, the color wore off so patchy and unevenly, I just couldn't stand it. I always ALWAYS exfoliate and prep my skin with barrier cream before spraying, and also do the daily maintenance needed on spray tanned skin to ensure an even fade...i.e., moisturize with non oil based creams or lotions which don't degrade tan quickly the way that oil based lotions can. ( I have nice skin that's not dry anyway, but still, you have to take special care with what you use when you spray tan.) But despite all my pre and post prep work, and after three different tries with this solution, I've decided it's not for me, even though the color it produces is perfect for me, but that doesn't negate how terrible it looks as it fades, and that's half the battle. At least St. Tropez fades evenly and I can usually redo my tan after about 4-5 days without anyone really noticing it fading badly the way they did with the Norvell solution. This is just my review, it may work for you, but in addition, I also experienced the "spotting" effect that other reviewers mentioned. Too bad, not good, and not for me.

column13: YES YES YES. Its a WIN for me.
column14:
I am obsessed with this product. Bought it on a recommendation from a girl at Sephora. I definitely went home thinking this was just another product that wouldn't work.

I have bad cystic acne and have tried everything under the sun. While this does not heal acne, nor does it claim to, it DOES EXFOLIATE as it promises. You can actually SEE the dead skin, dirt and gunk it picks up off your skin. This stuff is what would otherwise be clogging your pores. This is a great addition to any skincare regimen!!!!! I don't remember what the directions say but I use this EVERYDAY, usually at night and its great! But I have oily combo skin, so I get a lot of buildup throughout the day. You may not need or want to use it that often.

I waited to write this review because I have had my hopes up on so many products only to be let down, so I wanted to make sure I wasn't getting false hope or disappointment from just one use. I have been using this product OVER A MONTH, and I have actually gotten words of encouragement from friends saying my skin looks a lot better!

Keep in mind: 1) You will notice a subtle difference right away, but real effects will take a few weeks 2) Use in combo with a gentle cleanser like Cetaphil Gentle Skin (not the Face one, for some reason its a little more harsh) 3) If you BUY IT AT SEPHORA and hate it, you can take it back! EVEN IF YOU'VE USED HALF THE BOTTLE

Anyway, hope this helps.

column6: Color Oops Hair Color Remover Extra Strength 1 Each
column13: Lightens your BASE color including NEW ROOT GROWTH
column14:
(Just for some background, as every person's hair color and dying experience will be different) I have the following colors on my shoulder-length Caucasian hair: Henna (ends to midway, not boxed stuff either, 100% natural BAQ henna), chemical BOX dyes going back from Nov-Dec 2014 (red, then black), removed using Color B4 and now mid 2015 med browns at hairdresser to mask the inevitable resulting orange). I have used both Color B4 (English equiv to Color Oops - or so I thought!) and Color Oops several times over the past 4 or 5 years with no trouble or affect on the natural color. Perhaps 4-5 times each brand! The stuff has been a miracle for me in the past. (Bye bye to my Morticia hair!)

Onto this week. Imagine my confusion when in one dose of Color Oops I not only end up with the brassiness that I was expecting (happens every time, hair colorants = bleach, except for with henna)... but with almost 8 MONTHS of root growth suddenly lightened as surely as if I'd used a bleach product!

So, breathe, chill, I'm trying to go back to natural color anyway, spilt milk and all, so I go to Sally's to pick up some demi permanents to try getting back to my natural 6 warm color so I can leave the world (wait, no, prison) of hair coloring, roots and damage behind me. I ask the lady who owns the store for Color Oops I realized there's still some darker deposits waiting to oxidize in my hair. She tells me "Don't use that - it contains bleach or something. Another customer came in last week with the same problem you have and we decided something's going on there". She recommended Color Fix instead which I used and it worked well. I can't attest to whether it would have done the same lightening effect on my hard-earned roots as Color Oops. I'm probably scared off of these products for life, perhaps not Color B4 -- that's never failed for me.

In short, if you decide to use this to get rid of OLD color, perhaps have someone capable ofapplying the product with a tint brush and mixing bowl to only hit the dyed ends. Don't just slather it all over like some kinda hair mask. Also, Color FIX came with a lotion to rinse after the washing process, so you can test if any residual colors are lurking within that will interfere with a corrective or additional color you plan on doing later on. I feel like I can get 2 uses from the Color Fix product, but you'll only get 1 use out of Color Oops unless you have short or super thin hair. Color Fix also doesn't ask for like 30 minutes of rinsing, just 3-5 (I did about 15 though, then shampoo'd THEN used the lotion)

Some tips, if you're looking into the product for the first time, or any of the removers for that matter. Not a pro but I've been doing this with myself as a guinea pig for a while.
- LEAVE OFF YOUR JEWELRY. This stuff turned one of my rings the same orange it turned my hair. It's just doing what it does.
- Whether you went black, red or bleach blonde, your natural color has almost certainly be altered by the developer, esp with gross box dyes.
- i.e. You will likely have a brassy result even if your hair was once ash. It's worse if you're a dark/warm/golden/red haired person though, i.e. if your hair naturally glows reddish or looks a "warm" color in the sun. I think dying exposes that pigment and Color Oops shows that up.
- I have never encountered any damage from this process. Some people do though. But most importantly DO NOT add conditioners or anything else straight after using except for a clarifying shampoo for the initial rinsing process. I wait about 3-4 days before using any oil or conditioning products on my hair to avoid "trapping" any unwanted residual dye molecules in the hair cuticles. So: Wash, wash, wash, THEN shampoo, then like 3 days of just combing and scraping your hair back into whatever style it agrees with.
- I do not think it works well on stain dyes such as Manic Panic, Directions or even demi dyes, but I have successfully gotten one color out so it is worth a try if you're desperate. You might want to try a salon in this case.
- Do the process in a warm room to speed it up or get the most from it. You must RINSE well. Otherwise the old shrunken dye molecules will bounce right back with oxidization. Happens to me all the time with this specific color remover, which is partly why I dislike it so much compared to the others I've used, RE-OXIDIZATION.
- Avoid using this process twice in a row. If you can, wait a few days in-between if you really must, for condition AND for your poor hair's sake.

I regret ever dying my hair or using sulfate shampoos. If you've never dyed your hair and are looking into it -- at least do your research into demi dyes or think long and hard. Maintenance, roots and damage are certainly not worth it, at least for me. I would love to get back my pre-raphaelite hair! Natural hair is awesome.

Tips even if they help just one person out there
- Good professionals. (Correction, demi jobs)
- If you're after change, maybe try changing hair STYLE, not color.
- Avoid permanent box dyes, or box dyes in general. You cannot control the strength of the developer in these. Look into getting a developer and the color to do yourself, as you can control the results much better! (Only took me 5 years + like 30 dyes to figure this one out!)
- If you're impatient, slow-grower or dislike the same color, avoid henna or any super dark colors -- good luck getting rid of true BAQ henna.
- After using every brand and product like this under the sun, I'm becoming sensitive to the nasty hair chemicals, Color Oops included. This product left me with a rash on my left ear where I have a piercing, and no it wasn't the earrings. My arms also itched that day and the day after, which is a new thing.

column6: Colora Henna Powder, 72 Count
column14:
I'm a natural dark blonde with a few red highlights, and a few grays. I wanted a gentle rinse to bring out my red and cover the gray. I use red wine vinegar once a week between shampoo and conditioner, so I was looking for a powdered henna to add to that.

*DISCLAIMER* I don't use according to package directions.

THIS STUFF IS AMAZING!!

I use two rounded teaspoons added to 1/2 cup red wine vinegar and 1/2 cup warm water. I shampoo, then work my henna/ vinegar rinse through my (very long) hair. I tie it up and cover with a plastic bag for approximately 15-20 minutes, then rinse and condition. It leaves my hair soft and silky, and the color is just perfect. I was afraid this shade would be too dark (and it probably would be if I left it on longer), but I have my recipe tweaked and my method figured out. My hair emerges as a beautiful strawberry shade, with golden highlights (like a sunset!) and no gray. This powder leaves my hair shiny and undamaged, and it's so easy to use. I just reordered my second box!

column13: After seeing him play at the park and get in the car and immediately stick his thumb in his mouth before I could get a wipey out
column14: Holy Guacamole Batman!!! This Stuff REALLY works!!!!  We have tried many ways to get our almost 3 year old son to stop sucking his thumb. Taping it up, essential oils, mittens just to name a few. After seeing him play at the park and get in the car and immediately stick his thumb in his mouth before I could get a wipey out had me utterly disgusted and horrified. BLECH!!!!!!!!! That was enough to make me come home and immediately look up a permanent solution. I came across Mavala and saw the great reviews and high star rating. Sold! I ordered and anxiously awaited its arrival. So excited when I got the package and washed his hands and put a small little drop on his thumb nail (I read other reviews that said doing the whole nail made for a exorcism type experience and so I thought a drop would do) So as we laid him down, we quickly turned on the video monitor because we knew that thumb would quickly go in. Sure enough, in it went and a quick exit it made followed by a loud, "BLEEEEECCCHHHHHHHHH! EWWWWWW!!!!!!! and rubbing his tongue on his blankets. A quick drink of water and he was out light a light. No crying, no anger. Sure enough, he did not put it back in. Next morning, I think he forgot that horrible taste as he came out, laid on the carpet as he always does and the thumb went it. Same reaction as the night before. Happy to say, that we are almost 3 weeks no thumb sucking and it hasn't gone back in his mouth. :) THANK YOU!!!!! This product gets 5 stars from us.  (Although, my hubby would give the taste a negative 5. My son went to feed him a Dorito and my hubby over bites so he gets our sons fingers to make him laugh. All of a sudden he was like, "THAT DOES NOT TASTE LIKE DORITO!!!" And proceeded to rinse his mouth out in the sink) LOL!!!!  So except for the fact that this doesn't taste like a delicious chip (that would defeat the point) We give it 2 thumbs up :)

column13: Great for hair, skin and nails!
column14:
Argan Oil has been used in Morocco for centuries. Only recently have we realized what we had been missing. Argan Oil moisturizes and softens skin, helps treat stretch marks, and gives skin a youthful glow. It repairs and nourishes hair, improving scalp health, treats split-ends, and controls frizz. It can strengthen brittle nails and soften cuticles.

Eliminer Moroccan Argan Oil is 100% Pure & Organic. It comes with a dropper in the lid for easy dispensing. When my skin is dry I massage a few drops of the oil onto my skin, as it provides lasting moisture. I also use the oil daily as a part of my hair care routine. I massage a few drops of Argan Oil into my damp hair before I blow dry. My hair is less frizzy, my ends are less dry, and my hair has much more shine when I use Argan Oil.

Argan Oil is such a great product, and I would absolutely recommend Eliminer Moroccan Argan Oil.

I received this product for free in exchange for sharing my honest and unbiased review. Opinion is entirely my own.

column6: Curl Defining Conditioner
column13: Thick, rich and hydrating conditioner for swavy hair.
column14:
I was introduced to this product at my local Sally's when it was gifted to me for renewing my Sally's card before it expired and I'm so glad!

I have swavy, type 2B/2C, fine hair that freezes up quite easily. This conditioner is thick, thick and luxurious. I literally have to remove the cap in order to get the conditioner out of the bottle more easily. It has a soft scent, not overpowering at all and it leaves my hair feeling soft and manageable. I love that because it's so thick, it provides me with plenty of "slip" allowing me to detangle my hair in the shower with ease and pain and damage free.

I gave it a four star because it only comes in 12oz size. Anyone who has curly hair knows that we go through conditioners like wild fire so a bigger size, like 32oz would be great and a dispensing pump would be oh so awesome! ;)

Overall I love this conditioner because it's thick and rich and hydrating, just perfect for my swavy hair. The scent is ok, take it or leave it kind of thing but it doesn't bother me. I will continue to re-purchase because its a great product.

column6: Brilliant EYE GEL by Eve Hansen. Gentle yet Effective for Dark Circles, Puffiness, Wrinkles - SEE RESULTS OR - 100% Vegan and Lightweight Cream with Organic & Natural Anti-Aging Ingredients
column13: A good moisturizer, but didn't help my bags or fine lines at all.
column14: Following the instructions, I've been using this product under my eyes every night and occasionally in the mornings before make-up application for two weeks now, and so far, I have not noticed any difference in my fine lines or bags.  I don't really have dark circles to begin with.  If I notice a change in the puffiness of the bags under my eyes or any minimizing of fine lines after using for another couple of weeks, I will come back and update this review.  I'm posting now just because a lot of others have said they noticed immediate results, whereas I have not.  Maybe it takes longer for some people and maybe it only works on dark circles. But I'm giving this product at least 3 stars to start with because I do like using it as a moisturizer, if nothing else.  It has a pleasant cucumber smell, is not oily, absorbs quickly and doesn't cause my skin to break out.  For the low price I paid, I'm somewhat satisfied just using it just as a moisturizer and wouldn't return the product, but I'm also not sold yet on buying it again (that might depend on how long it lasts since the container feels very light).

column6: Equate Flushable Wipes, Singles, 20 Individually Wrapped Wipes, Fresh Scent, Compare to Cottonelle Fresh Flushable Moist Wipes
column13: Durable, does not leak, individual packaging.
column14:
I'm saddened that Wal-Mart now lists this item as "Unavailable". These were the best flushable wipes that I've ever encountered. They were neither too wet or dry, and while they stronger than most, you still had to be gentle, lest they tear in use.

While the individual pouch was a bit more difficult than other similar products to open, it REMAINED SEALED WHILE IN A POCKET. Every other wipe (flushable or not) has never lasted in my pockets, even with nothing else in the pocket, the others' pouches found some way to spring a leak and make my trousers damp. Rendering the wipe too dry to function properly.

If Wal-Mart doesn't bring these back, I sure hope someone else follows up with a similarly package single, flushable wipe of the same or better caliber.

column6: PUEEN Nail Art Double Side Super Soft Squishy Silicone XL Stamper and Scraper Set - Stamping Tools-BH000485
column14:
I was really afraid to order this stamper because of the negative reviews. I was in dire need of a marshmallow stamper. I had previously bought the double sided Konad stamper, which was too hard for me because of my nail's C-shape. I disliked having to roll the stamper because it ruined the design to often. I use the hard stampers on my toenails, because my toenails are flat. I almost purchased a really expensive marshmallow stamper from Messy Mansion instead of this one, but I'm glad I purchased this one instead.

When I bought the stamper, I buffed it with a Magic Eraser Sponge by Mr.Clean to rid the shine. I used a nail file and went over three times lightly to buffer. I used the magic eraser again to buff the sides out. I let it sit for awhile because it was really sticky after being freshly buffed. I used the stamper once afterwards, and it didn't pick up anything on the yellow marshmallow part. I didn't like the scraper at all, but I have tons of hotel room cards so that wasn't a big deal.

I used this stamper again yesterday after cleaning it on a stinky lint roller. It worked perfectly! I used the yellow side again and it worked amazingly well. I didn't even buff it again, so I'm not sure what the difference was. I used it on CiCi&SiSi plates with konad. I messed up twice, but it was my fault, and besides that, this is the best stamper I've had.

The yellow part is not sticky if you wait long enough before using it again. To clean, use a stinky lint roller ad never dip it in acetone. I like how the double sides can be removed because I like to make my own decals and when you remove one of the jellys, you can stand it up on its own to dry. I also like that they can be replaced. I'm not sure why everyone else were having a lot of problems with this stamper. I guess my first attempt was bad, but the second time I tried it worked great. If you need a marshmallow stamper or a soft rectangular one, I would give this stamper a shot. The price is really reasonable compared to other expensive brands.is stamper a shot. The price is really reasonable compared to other expensive brands.

column13: Some things are good quality while others are not
column14: Overall this is an okay set. Some things are good quality while others are not. The tips that were sent are thicker than any others I have use so in the right lighting my smile line will have a slight shadow. This however I can deal with since I use size 8 on two fingers I only have one set of the clear and white tips. I like the O.P.I cuticle oil (I got watermelon). The files where of a cheaper quality. The metal cuticle pusher is great and the tip cutter is great as well. The brush I was able to use a few times but it started to pull out of the handle after a while and I always had problems with it leaving bubbles (even when I pushed them out before dipping into the acrylic). Now on to the important part. I have a love hate relationship with the actual acrylic. I do not free hand my nails and use asp forms. Its faster and not a pain in the butt when I do my opposite hand. The white didn't want to release properly. To go along with the white it also would set up way to fast. I don't sculpt with the white. The only time I use white powder is when I have plans to water marble. I had no issues with the clear or pink powders. However my biggest issues was the size of the acrylic powder. When I first pulled them out I thought these were a decent size and filled to the top. (some people said they were small but the jars were what i expected at this price). However the major down side was when I found out there is a plastic base halfway up the jar that I did not see. I haven't had any issues with this from other companies :( I am still going to get a few sets out of each so its not like it was a total waste of money. So with this set there is good parts and bad parts. But you get what you pay for.

column6: American Crew Fiber (Pack of 4) - 3oz each
column13: Never Looked Back! Best out there.
column14:
This stuff really holds and smells nice as well. I found this to be the best price anywhere. Best hair product for men. Not greasy and holds all day. What else can you ask for? Great price too buying the 4 pack!
I take a small amount and rub it in my hands to make it soft (or heat it with a hair dryer) and spread it evenly through my hair. Then comb it through to make sure it's even and there are not little clumps anywhere. No need to worry about focusing on the roots since it's just for frizz control.
Note that even with long hair, a little bit goes a long way. I use about a pea sized amount, like a large pea. Maybe a tiny bit more at the tips if they're still a little frizzy. If you use too much it makes your hair thick, heavy and greasy looking. A 3 oz tub lasts me 6-9 months.

Fiber provides the perfect look and feel in my opinion because you really can't tell there is any product in your hair if applied sparingly. In fact, you do not have to use a lot of this product depending on how much hair you have making it last a long time. Overall, I've been hooked on this product for years now and have used nothing else.

column13: These work pretty well and smell very nice.
column14: I bought these because I needed two major surgeries 8 weeks apart this summer. Since most places don't let you wear deodorant/antiperspirant the morning of surgery and since antiperspirant is hard to completely wash off the residue, I used these the night before so I wouldn't go into surgery stinking. Since my large incisions were in my armpits, I had to go without deodorant for several weeks. When I was finally allowed to wear it, I didn't want anything that would cake into my incisions or irritate it. So I used these. They smell nice and work fairly well. I usually get about 8 hours before I start to stink which is fine for the time being since I'm off from surgery. They aren't perfect, but they fit my needs at the moment. Since the incision was in my armpits, I do not sweat very much anymore. I may continue to use these now that both surgeries are complete and both armpits sweat minimally.

column6: Elba Naturals Face and Eye Advanced Firming Cream, Vitamin C, Hyaluronic Acid, Matrixyl 3000, Tripeptide-5, Retinol Anti-Aging Repair, 1 oz.
column13: Excellent Moisturizing, USA made and Organic!
column14:
I'm picky about what I eat and put on my skin, and try to use organic products whenever I can. I was pleased to be asked to test this eye cream when I saw that it's not only USA-made, organic and natural but that it also has my favorite anti-aging ingredients: hyaluronic acid (holds in moisture, improves elasticity of skin) and Vitamin C (reverses sun damage and regenerates skin cells). I've been using serums and creams with those ingredients for several years and can really see the difference in my middle aged skin.

This cream also contains Matrixyl 3000 (an antioxidant), Tripeptide-5 (stimulates collagen regeneration), retinol (Vitamin A, boosts collagen, speeds up cellular regeneration) and Glycolic Acid (fades sun spots, exfoliates dead skin cells). All great things for faces of any age!

I've been using it (twice a day) around my eyes and mouth for three weeks and I really like it. It's fragrance free and leaves my skin deeply moisturized and plumped. I believe it's also lived up to the "firming" part of its name because the bags under my eyes seem slightly diminished. Of course I still look middle aged - no cream or potion will be able to make me look 20 again. But when my skin looks dewy and the wrinkles and bags are diminished I declare victory. Knowing I'm getting these benefits with organic ingredients and not unpronounceable chemicals makes me that much happier.

I received a complimentary sample of Elba Advanced Eye Firming Cream for testing and review purposes. I wasn't asked to leave a positive review, nor was I paid or otherwise compensated for reviewing this item. Look at the hundreds of reviews I've written over ten years and you'll see that I work hard to give an honest opinion of the products I review.

column6: 50x Strength Hyaluronic Acid Serum From Uptown Cosmeceuticals, One Single Application of This Super Anti Aging, Anti Wrinkle Serum Makes the Skin Look Plumped and Lifted, 15ml
column13: I bet snow whites evil Queen wishs she had this stuff
column14: Hyaluronic acid is a naturally produced ingredient by the body and helps the skin retain moisture and it's youthfulness.  As we age, the body begins to produce less and less hyaluronic acid, resulting in the drying of the skin and adding to the appearance of those fine lines and wrinkles.  We all know that we do not want to have either of those.  So to start off with I would like to say that upon arrival I did pump some of the serum onto my finger tips and began applying in an upward motion.  Why upward you ask?  Because I am a licensed cosmetologist on of the things that you learn is to when you apply anything  to your face you always want to apply in an upward motion.  This serum is packed with moisture and did not leave any type of sticky residue.  I would also like to add that I have sensitive skin and sense using this I have not had any adverse reactions.  It appears to have made my skin look moisturized and I especially like that.  I used this product after a hot steamy shower so it immediately emulsified my skin making my skin feel silky and smooth.  One Hyaluronic Acid benefit is that id doe's help delay the aging process and can help to further delay fine lines and wrinkles.  This is what sold me on this product.  The visible benefits is what ant woman desires and with this product came just that.  It is dye free and that means it does not have those skin dyes that dry out your skin. I would say if you are looking for a visable difference try this product and enjoy the radiant youthfulness of it.

column6: Castor Oil - Jamaican Black - 8 oz - Stimulate Hair Growth
column13: Castor Oil with a Jamaican twist!
column14:
well Im not new to castor oil but i am new to Jamaican black castor oil, i've seen many natural hair gurus recommending it and i've always wanted to try it and see if its any different than regular castor so i had the opportunity to try this out for free in exchange of my honest and unbiased and unpaid review.
It smells and i won't lie strong, it smells somewhat nutty I'm not sure its not the best of smells and its quite strong but after a few hours or overnight its not so bad or maybe i got used to it. But knowing that such oils are beneficial to the hair i didn't mind the smell especially that i've used plenty smelly oils before. I do recommend putting it on overnight and washing it off in the morning for those who aren't into the smell.
The oil is thick just like regular castor oil so it isn't diluted and usually a little goes a long way aim for the scalp with this oil and finish off with coconut oil or anything else u like. This made my hair softer and shinier, I know that castor oil makes hair thicker but i need to use this long enough for those effects to come shine through. So far I like this oil regardless of the smell.
The difference between regular castor oil and Jamaican castor oil is that they roast the seeds so that pretty much explains the strong smell of it. U need to give this time to work its not a miracle product and depending on ur diet and vitamins and TLC for your hair will you see rapid results and growth.

Im glad the bottle is plastic that way it won't break i was concerned that there wasn't a pull off plug when u open it but i guess thats alright nothing to be alarmed from.the size is good too!

column14: I was so excited to try lavender essential oil for it's calming properties. I have a hard time falling asleep so I was looking forward to using it to help me wind down. To have my bedding smell like lavender I added lavender oil to a dry washcloth and then placed it in the dryer towards the end of the cycle. It makes the sheets smell amazing and really does help me relax so I can fall asleep. During the day I just add a few drops to some almond oil and rub it into my skin. It smells great and helps me take a bit of a breather when I need it.  The oil came packaged really well in plastic and then bubble wrap so there was no problems with it leaking in the mail. I would love if the oil was in a glass bottle instead of plastic, but at least it's darkened to help it last longer. It has an expiration date on the side of the bottle which is great for oils that you might not use often enough. The oil has a spray nozzle, but I prefer to unscrew the cap and use the plastic tube when I need a few drops. I'm loving the oil and wouldn't hesitate to purchase it again. column13: GREAT PRODUCT FOR A STARTER BUT ONE LESS STAR FOR NOT PLUCKING ALL MY HAIR IN MY PITS !!!
column14:
I've never used an epilator before and bought this for my very first one. I bought this last year and all I can say is that it's a great product if u are still trying to learn how to epilate. (btw this is better than shaving). The first time I used it was on my underarms. I had a bad thick hairs on my pits. sometimes there was two in one hole , it was bad. so i used this on my underarms for the first time without using any painkillers except for a cold towel (didnt really help)... IT HURT SO BAD FOR THE FIRST TIME .. however it was hard for me to get used to my skin cuz it would always pinch my pits and made it bleed & left bumps that was also painful .. u really have to stretch out ur skin and brush through ur pits so its easier for the tweezers to pluck them. also tried it on my legs and it hurt like s*** .. lesson learned for me never use it anywhere but my underarms....overall this is an awesome epilator and u just hav to learn correctly how it works with ur skin ..also it was shipped really fast.

TIPS:
- Take a warm shower
-Use ice cubes before epilating (makes ur skin numb so its less painful)
-Cut two circular shape cucumbers/ potatoes & rub it for 2 mins in ur underarms after epilating
-Use baking soda as ur deodorant (optional)

column6: NORLANYA Mini Portable RF Radio Frequency Skin Tighten Machine Bipolar RF for pimples Wrinkle Remove Skin Lightening Lifting Skin Tighten
column14:
I'd love to give this 5 ‚≠êÔ∏è, but solely because the instructions are so vague it gets 4 ‚≠êÔ∏è from me. I'm unfamiliar with RF devices, so good instructions would have been beneficial. I do LOVE this device! However, my first attempt with this was literally shocking. Come to find out, I needed to remove my earrings and ring. Also, I needed a good conducting gel. I purchased radio frequency gel. It works nicely. Next, make sure the tips touch the skin at the same time and remain touching equally through the process to keep from getting shocked!
I also watched just about every video on using these type devices on YouTube. So after all this prepping I got the nerve to try it again. WoW!! Amazing! Now, don't expect a miracle, but you definitely feel the effects even if you don't see them right away. These things do take time. In all my reading, I discovered that for some results are seen rather quickly, and for others it could be as long as 6 months before results are very noticeable.
So hang in there with whatever device you buy. I'm sure you'll love the results. I'm still in my first month, and though I don't see a lot of change, I do feel the benefits.

column6: Blue Lizard Australian Sunscreen, Sensitive SPF 30+, 5-Ounce Bottles (Pack of 2)
column14:
I've used four varieties of Blue Lizard -- Baby, Sensitive, Face, and Sport -- and I've posted the same review for each one. Baby and Sensitive are virtually identical. Face feels more dry, and doesn't leave your skin shiny. Sport seems to go on a little easier, but also has more potentially irritating chemicals than Sensitive or Baby (or so I'm told).

Here is the bottom line: Each version of Blue Lizard that I have tried will last through a 4+ hours of golf in direct midday sun, even when I'm perspiring heavily, and I'll go home with NO redness or burning whatsoever. (FYI, I am very light skinned and do develop a tan, but burn VERY easily, in 15 min. or less. I also perspire a lot, especially in the heat and humidity around the Washington D.C. metro area, where we live.) A little goes a long way, and if you take a few minutes to work it in, it stays put pretty well and doesn't run into your eyes.

It isn't the easiest to put on, and it takes some soap and water to get it off, but until they change the formula is some significant way, Blue Lizard is head and shoulders above all the other major-brand sunscreens that I've tried -- and I've tried a lot. It's also nice that the Baby and Sensitive versions get high marks for their lack of toxic chemicals, and we've used them on babies and toddlers with sensitive skin, and never had any problems, either with burning or reaction to the sunscreen. Strongly recommended.

column6: Color Oops Hair Color Remover Extra Strength
column14:
I think the picture below says it all.

Oh my dear Lord! God has given me a miracle! I'm a natural redhead and I've dyed my hair at home many times before. I haven't dyed my hair at home in about 10 years, and went to a professional I loved. But last night, I decided instead of going all the way down into the city, I would do it at home. I've always gone brighter with my dye and the results are a brighter red. Within a few washings, it was a beautiful red. Well I must have gotten the bad batch when I bought Garnier Nutrisse Magnetic Copper (medium natural copper). The side of the box shows a nice color copper red, from the lightest to the darkest natural hair colors. So I figured I would get a nice red. WRONG! My hair was a DARK almost black-red. I've been dark red before, but this was REALLY dark. It's summer. I'm pale. And I'm getting married in two weeks. Yeah. I cried. I read the reviews on Amazon and decided to buy this product in the morning.

This morning, I woke up early (I'm NOT a morning person) and ran to CVS. I bought the Oops Extra Strength, Neutrogena Clarifying Shampoo, and L'Oreal Total Repar 5 Damage Erasing Bomb. The reviews said the Oops dries out your hair and since my hair is thin & fragile, I didn't want a bird's nest on my head. I followed the directions EXACTLY! I think the people who wrote negative reviews didn't follow the directions or didn't look at the website to see if their particular hair dye would work with this product. I went from light to dark, so that's why the product worked. I also did a strand test so I knew it would work The directions say to not keep the product on for more than 20 minutes. When I did the strand test, it only took 10 minutes for my hair to come back.

So after 20 minutes, I washed my hair with the Neutrogena & I rinsed my hair so long that I think I emptied the reservoir. That's the "secret" to this product...rinse your hair like a mad woman! Even the directions say that the longer you rinse, the better your results. So after upping my water bill, I washed my hair 2 more times and rinsed for another 5 minutes. Then I deep conditioned for 10 minutes. MY HAIR CAME BACK! YAY! I was sooooooo happy!

My hair was really dry before the conditioner, so make sure you buy a heavy duty conditioner. Hell, use mayo, olive oil, beer...whatever. If you don't, Scarecrows will have softer, shinier hair than you will.

I am forever grateful for this product. It worked for me. I didn't need to dye my hair again like some reviewers did. But everyone is DIFFERENT! Do a strand test before putting this product on your hair.

Lesson learned. Go to a professional to get your hair dyed. No more home hair coloring adventures for me!Even the directions say that the longer you rinse, the better your results. column6: Merkur Heavy Duty Double Edge Razor (Blade Included)
column13: Basic razor that does an excellent job
column14:
I started with the 3pc Shaveology razor (gift from my Father in Law), and while it worked, I wanted something with more "heft", a shaft with textured grip, and I didn't like that the comb was entirely separate from the base. This razor fixed what I found lacking and didn't cost an obscene amount. Shaves very similarly, and I LOVE that the top piece screws in via the knob on the bottom to make this a 2pc razor.

The textured handle means I have full control, even with slightly slippery hands (common due to water and dripping shaving cream after a pass, etc), and the weight helps me minimize the pressure I'm tempted to apply (you should apply as little pressure as possible, idealy NONE) and thus get a less irritated face. The razor itself holds the blade such that it's not very aggressive, so that allows you to use sharper blades without getting all sliced up by them (I'm experimenting with feathers, wilkinsons, and personas right now, after having used astras for a few months and finding them not as aggressively sharp as I'd like).

column6: Bior√© - Deep Cleansing Pore Strips
column14:
I got these in a store, not knowing that they are half nose strips and half face strips. I actually like the face strips way better. I have a pretty wide nose, so I find the face strips cover my nose much better than the nose strips. Regardless, they both do their job.

As to be expected, these aren't perfect. It's a little tricky to get your nose and equal and correct amount of wet so that they work. I find there's usually a section that just wasn't wet enough, or was too wet. Not a deal breaker, but annoying that a chunk of the effectiveness is all on your skills with wetting your nose. Also, it doesn't get everything, not surprisingly. Don't get me wrong, it gets a ton of gunk and a few black heads here and there, but after I'm always left staring at a handful of black heads still left.

Also, my nose itches a lot after using them! I've found that wiping my nose with a cold wet cotton ball after, and then soaking a tissue in cold water and keeping it on my nose for a while really helps. Without doing these things, I'll be itchy for up to one hour, which is maddening when you're trying not to touch/dirty your just cleared nose! With them, the itchy is instantly calmed.

All that being said, this is the best strip for the money if you want to clean your pores! Definitely cheaper on Amazon, too!

column14:
For the price, this is a pretty good product. However, the MSRP of $220 is very misleading. It's lightweight, & the plastic parts are clearly inexpensive. I have a Paul Mitchell Neuro flat iron that cost over $100 & the difference in quality is evident. It doesn't include temperature control (it does not state that it does so I didn't expect it), and it gets HOT. The glove is provided to keep you from burning your fingerprints off, but the protection it provides is minimal. I just want to let anyone else know that it's not much better quality than something you can purchase at Bed, Bath, & Beyond or Target.
That being said, it does what it advertises. My hair is to my collarbone, and it gave me nice soft waves or curls depending on how I used it. Whether they last is usually dependent on hair type & products used, but I was pleased with the results. If you want to spend a little more you can get a wand with auto shut off, temp control, etc., but this does the trick for the price.

column6: Blue Lizard Australian Sunscreen, Sport SPF 30+, 5-Ounce Bottles (Pack of 2)
column14:
I've used four varieties of Blue Lizard -- Baby, Sensitive, Face, and Sport -- and I've posted the same review for each one. Baby and Sensitive are virtually identical. Face feels more dry, and doesn't leave your skin shiny. Sport seems to go on a little easier, but also has more potentially irritating chemicals than Sensitive or Baby (or so I'm told).

Here is the bottom line: Each version of Blue Lizard that I have tried will last through a 4+ hours of golf in direct midday sun, even when I'm perspiring heavily, and I'll go home with NO redness or burning whatsoever. (FYI, I am very light skinned and do develop a tan, but burn VERY easily, in 15 min. or less. I also perspire a lot, especially in the heat and humidity around the Washington D.C. metro area, where we live.) A little goes a long way, and if you take a few minutes to work it in, it stays put pretty well and doesn't run into your eyes.

It isn't the easiest to put on, and it takes some soap and water to get it off, but until they change the formula is some significant way, Blue Lizard is head and shoulders above all the other major-brand sunscreens that I've tried -- and I've tried a lot. It's also nice that the Baby and Sensitive versions get high marks for their lack of toxic chemicals, and we've used them on babies and toddlers with sensitive skin, and never had any problems, either with burning or reaction to the sunscreen. Strongly recommended.

column13: Perfect for adding to homemade/natural cleaners
column14: Lemon is one of my absolute favorite smells since it makes everything smell fresh and clean. This lemon essential oil has been the perfect addition to some of my homemade cleaners. Just add a few drops of it to a spray bottle filled with a 50/50 mix of vinegar and water. It smells amazing, disinfects really well, and is all natural. I love it! It also works wonders at getting rid of any strange garbage disposal smells. Pour half a cup of baking soda down the drain and half a cup of vinegar mixed with a few drops of the lemon essential oil. Let it sit for a few minutes before running the hot water and it will smell so much better. This lemon essential oil has a slight orange-y smell to it which I actually love.  It came packaged really well which I appreciated. It comes wrapped in a snug layer of bubble wrap and then has a plastic seal around the top. It has a spray nozzle instead of a dropper, but I usually end up unscrewing the nozzle and using it kind of like a dropper. column6: 1lb Organic Shea Butter - Pure & Unrefined Grade A, Ivory African Raw Shea Butter with DIY Skin Care Recipes for Skin, Hair, Stretch Marks - Best for Making Creams, Lotions and Moisturizers - Best For Dry or Acne-Prone Skin, Eczema, Anti-Aging Agent & Nourishes Your Skin - No Additives OR Artificial Preservatives - Ethically Traded 1lbs. (16oz)
column13: Good quality and well packaged - a must for Shea butter lovers
column14:
I have known for a long time that Shea butter is highly regarded for its natural moisturizing and skin-healing abilities. There are two kinds - unrefined and raw, like this product and refined/ultra-refined Shea Butter. I prefer this unrefined raw organic like this one by Shea Butter Wisdom. In deciding which one to get to use in my homemade beauty preparations I found that raw unrefined Shea butter has a higher nutrient content, better natural healing properties and of course it is free of chemicals from the refinement process.

This package has a full pound of Shea Butter, ivory in color, with the typical scent of raw shea. It is not unpleasant and I find it soothing. It can be covered up quite easily with an essential oil. I really like that it is in two airtight containers so it lasts. Shea Butter is stored at a low temp (not too low or it will solidify like coconut oil does) and in the dark. column13: Great, but buy with caution. These are sharp.
column14:
This set is great. I was easily able to remove a blackhead that I had for awhile that I couldn't get out through 'natural' means (hot shower, wait for pores to open, squeeze, or the egg whites trick).

However, you want to make sure you know what you're doing! There are NO directions with these, aside from a quick rundown on the box, which honestly is not nearly enough. You should go on YouTube first and look at a few videos on how to use these. You *need* to watch videos because just reading an article isn't enough. These tools are SHARP and if you don't use them correctly, you WILL hurt yourself!

Now since that's out of the way, I'll write about the actual quality of the tools. They're metal, sharp, and seem to be well made. They come in their own little pouch which has a zipper. It's convenient. I've only used these twice since I got them, so I can't comment about their durability yet. I've seen someone mention rust, so I'll be sure to look out for that. I plan on updating my review in a month if anything changes!

Overall, I think this is a great set of blackhead removers. They have been perfect so far!

Sample provided for review. I do feel these are worth 5 stars since they're sharp, light, easy to use, and worked perfectly. I'm not sure what else I could ask out of them.

column6: Lavanila The Healthy Deodorant-Vanilla Grapefruit- 2oz.
column13: Love This Stuff- Here are some pointers for newbies...
column14:
I've used this deodorant for over a year now. When I first made the choice to try an organic deodorant, I was super skeptical at how it would go down. I was searching for a healthier alternative to traditional deodorants and anti perspirants, however, I still didn't want to smell bad. After doing lots of online research mainly based on reviews and recommendations from people who have actually tried the product, I decided to try the Lavanila line. When I tried it, it was January. That way, if I were to start to sweat and the deodorant failed to do it's job of keeping me smelling fresh, it wouldn't be as bad as it would be during a sunny day in August. The first couple of days were tricky because I was so conscious of the fact that I was wearing a new deodorant. Here's what I discovered and some recommendations for first time users:
-Give It A Couple of Weeks....Most of our bodies are so used to using harsh chemicals to stop sweat or prevent BO. It takes a couple of weeks for everything to balance out. Be patient.
-Travel With It....This may sound a little tedious to some, but they make a small travel size that I keep in my handbag/car/desk for touch up. I never actually cut the deodorant and have BO (which would happen with traditional deodorants), but I will start to sometimes smell a little funky under my arms by the end of the day. Again, it's not the sharp repulsive smell of BO, but a softer more natural sweat scent. If I touch up in the late afternoon, it helps tons.
-You Will Sweat, You May Smell (but just a little)....This is a deodorant, not an antiperspirant. You will get wet under your arms. And like I mentioned before, you may even start to smell a little towards the end of your day after wearing it for a few hours. BUT, it's not the strong sting of the stench of BO. It's just a natural sweat smell- they are very different.

Overall, I am very pleased with this product and highly recommend it to anyone looking to try a healthier deodorant.ier deodorant.
