column6: Philips Norelco Multigroom 3100 with 5 attachments and skin-friendly blades, QG3330/49
column13: For the price, its pretty nice...
column14:
For the price on this guy, its pretty good stuff. Here's a breakdown of my experience, spaghetti western style:

THE GOOD:
-The ear and nose trimmer works very well, which was my main concern in getting this in the first place.
-The trimmer length attachments also work well, as long as you start longer than you think you'll need. I cleaned up my sideburns and armpits quite effectively with the trimmer and its length attachment. My previous method of doing so was to use a tiny scissors and it took so much longer!
-The cord you charge it with also powers the unit. The thing with these cheaper groomers (same goes for cheaper electric razors) is the batteries aren't that high quality and will eventually stop holding a charge. column6: Kirkland Minoxidil 5 percent Extra Strength Hair Regrowth for Men
column13: Kirklands Topical Solution vs. Rogaine Foam
column14:
I wanted to write a review for people who are looking at this product versus the foam or Rogaine brand. I started using minoxidil over a year ago and began with the Rogaine foam. about 6 months ago I decided to try the Kirkland brand topical solution because the difference in price was so huge (You can practically get a years supply for 3 months of Rogaine foam!). I was a bit nervous about trying a generic brand and switching from the foam because of some of the other reviews I read. Here is my experience with and comparison of the products.

I have had no negative experience from either of the products. No itchiness or redness of the scalp or anything like that. I like to keep my hair pretty short but I feel that as it gets longer before I get my hair cut the foam will not dry as nicely in my hair and leave it a little crispy (cant think of a better word). Not really a big deal as I just run my fingers through my hair to break it up. The topical solution doesnt seem to do that but it does take a bit longer to dry. So at night when I go to bed I will get some residue on my pillow, however, this hasnt caused any issues messing up a pillow case or anything like that. I also like the dropper used to apply the topical solution a lot more. It measures exactly, where as with the foam it says to use a cap full but that never seems like enough. In addition in the summer when its hot the foam starts dissolving into a liquid in my hand almost immediately which I never liked. As far as effectiveness I havent noticed any difference between the two products and think they both work well.

So in the end if your debating between foam or topical solution or Rogaine versus Kirklands I would definitely recommend the Kirklands topical solution. You will save a ton of money and I actually like the application of it better.

For those that are starting off using brushes in your shaving routine, I would recommend getting a cheaper one for starters. If you get this one from the start, I suspect you won't be able to appreciate this brush as much as it deserves. Before this brush I used, and still have it on duty, the Art Of Shaving Pure Badger brush. It's a 50-60 dollar brush that performs very well. After break in,it is soft, it has a good backbone and lathers very well. It is a very good brush, and it did (does) a very good job at teaching me the importance of certain things like, backbone, density, size, handle shape, softness and lather making. The Da Vinci excels in all of this, Not normal, not ok, not good. Excels. But I don't think I would have appreciated it as much if it had been my first brush. Just my 2cents. Anyway I can't give this brush anything but my deepest recommendations.

PS :The Price: When you see it in black and white, it does seem steep for a shaving brush. But when you hold it, use it and it shows you what it can do, you will see that it's more than worth the asking price. For me, it improved my shaving experience, which was already very enjoyable, into something a lot more so.

column6: Emu Oil by Leven Rose, 100% Pure Organic Natural Hair Strengthener Scar Minimizer Anti Aging Skin Moisturizer 4 oz
column13: I like Emu Oil for relieving arthritis pain, but it;s good for so much more than that...
column14:
I have arthritis in my left thumb so bad that it's painful for me to open jars sometimes, but I found that gently massaging Emu Oil around the joint eases the pain and inflammation and keeps me functional without having to take Calebrex. This Emu Oil is an odorless slightly milky oil that absorbs into the skin faster and more completely than other oils and creams, so it goes to work quickly and doesn't leave my skin feeling oily! I sometimes add a drop of Rosemary oil since the EMU Oil helps transport the Rosemary down into my muscle and joint along with it as it absorbs. Besides relieving inflammation and joint pain though, Emu Oil is a fabulous moisturizer that does wonders for skin and hair care.

Massaging Emu Oil into the scalp reportedly prevents hair loss. I'm not sure about that one way or another, but my daughter likes to run it through her hair to keep it nourished and prevent split ends and it works very well for that because since using this oil regularly her hair is softer, shinier, and looks healthier than it did before. Emu Oil contains plenty of antioxidants that help protect the skin from the damage done by free radicals, the sun, and environmental pollutants, and it's well known as an effective skin cell regenerator and anti-wrinkle agent too. It helps counter wrinkles and dry, scaly, thinning skin that commonly occur with aging, and I need all the help I can get in that department, so I'm using it directly on my arms, hands, and face. I use just a little bit, about a pea size on my face each night, and it soaks in within seconds, and I can both see and feel the difference.

You don't have to be growing old or have arthritis to benefit from Emu Oil either. Emu Oil has been found to be very effective on burns of all types including sunburn, at reducing the itching, redness, cracking, peeling and scaling associated with Psoriasis & Eczema, and is a marvelous natural treatment for stretch marks and scars. Leven Rose's Emu Oil comes in a dark amber glass bottle with a medicine dropper. I like that because it bugs the heck out of me when a company sends out of a bottle of expensive oil but it doesn't come with a dropper cap or a dropper, so you wind up wasting a lot by pouring it out, you know? This Emu Oil is 100% natural, super filtered, pure unadulterated Emu Oil. It comes from rendered Emu fat, so it's not vegan, but it's totally natural, safe for all skin types, doesn't clog pores, and won't leave your skin feeling greasy at all.

column14:
After using the sandalwood aftershave, I didn't want to then use a different scent for my cologne. So, I got this for putting on when I get ready to go out on the town (or go to church) with my wife, and for the days when I don't shave. The only thing that could improve the product is to have it capped by an atomizer, instead of having to pour it into the hand or dab onto the skin. Having it applied via atomized spray would evenly apply it over more skin and use less cologne overall. That's my only gripe.

A tad expensive, but it smells VERY nice without being overpowering (I've smelled other colognes for us gents that make me feel dizzy and nauseous when the fumes hit my nose), and sticks around. My wife loves the scent, so I make sure to apply it around the base of my neck up to my adam's apple and dabs on the wrists. Along with a smooth shave, she loves it.

column6: Baby Foot Exfoliant Foot Peel, Lavender Scented, 2.4 Fl. Oz.
column14: Seriously. I purchased one from another site (cheaper here!) and had read a few reviews that said it didn't work that well, but it did if you doubled the time. I got excellent (well, gross, but at the same time, cool) results by leaving this on for two hours. You get a packet of the gel and two plastic "socks" with tape at the ankles. I put the gel on, pulled on the foot bags then added the biggest pair of socks that I could find over all that hot mess and then *carefully* waddled to the bed to my soda and BLT and watched tv, folded a few loads of laundry and read a little. After rinsing, the skin on my feet felt weirdly thicker and ended up a little rougher but that was it. I kept moisturizer and a big pair of socks on for most of the days after (afraid to look). Four days later, nothing...and felt like I had wasted my time. By the seventh or eighth day the peeling began and...just wow. I'm not patient, hated waiting and really loathed spending that money. And that peeling thing is just freaky...but in the end, the soft feet thing lasted over three months and gave me better results than in shop pedicures. Ok, I admit that I DID go get a pedicure right after just so I could sit in the massage chair, because massage chairs are awesome. :D

column14: Ok I want to start off by saying I am kind of makeup obsessed. column6: Dettol Anti-Bacterial Hand and Body Bar Soap, Active, 110 Gr / 3.88 Oz (Pack of 12)
column14: I love using this soap to bath with as it's very effective at killing gems, but being that it's an anti-bacterial soap, it's never a good idea to use it too often as it's important for the skin to have some beneficial bacteria as well. That, coupled with the fact that it can dry the skin out if overly used, is why I rotate it with a good moisturizing soap throughout the week using it every other day (Monday, Wed, Fri). I like lathering up first, then I leave it on my skin while I shampoo my hair giving it time to work it's magic before rinsing it off. I also prefer the smell of the "active scent" as opposed to the regular scent since it more closely resembles a body soap rather than the original's Lysolish smell. I'm going to continue including Dettol active soap in my regular shower soap rotation.

column6: Gillette SensorExcel Cartridges for Women
column13: I See no difference between men's and women's Sensor Excel
column14: I have been shaving with the Sensor Excel for years but Costco no longer carries them and giving Wally World $22 for a 10 pack really tics me off. I couldn't do much better on ebay. A guy at the local flea market had a great price on Women's Sensor Excels. I tried to find out if there was any difference before buying. Gillette customer service told me some utter nonsense about extra edge guards on this blade that might hamper getting into tight places and somebody said the lube strip was different. I took a chance and bought them. They shave great and the only difference I could see  is everything is a different color. On the men's blade the plastic body and the rubber ribs are gray and the lube strip is white. On the women's blade the plastic body is white and the rubber ribs and lube strip are light blue and that is IT. They are 100% interchangeable. If the chemistry of the lube strip is different I sure couldn't tell; they both work fine. Buy which ever one you can get a good deal on. I'm headed back to the flea market to see if he has any more.

column14: This conditioner took me some time to get used to. I tried using too much at first and it weighed my hair down. Now I use a nickle sized drop (my hair is mid back length and very thick and dry. This is the best conditioner for my hair that I have ever found. I use the clarifying shampoo (because I use light product in my hair), I shampoo every few days, wring my hair out gently, hop out of the shower and pat it dry with a towel. I use that nickle sized drop, starting mid shaft and putting most of it on my ends. I use a bit on the top of my head (whatever is left over) then I comb it through with a very wide toothed comb. I do NOTHING more to it until it has air dried for atleast 45 mins. Then I use a Blow Brush and blowdry it straight back. This gives me shine, volume and it keeps my dry ends soft for a few days.

column6: Remington D8700 T|Studio PROtect Dryer, Aquatic Green
column13: A Little Loud, But Excellent Dryer
column14:
Hair dryers seem to be something I go through. Eventually, they burn out. As such, I was pleased to be able to try the Remington D8700 T|Studio PROtect Dryer.

In short, it is a basic hair dryer. The features are consistent with any other good hair dryer. Three heat settings, a cool blast, and two speed settings. Unique to it are the conditioning rings. Those, according to their promotional material, \\\are infused with macadamia oil, releasing micro-conditioners through the dryer air to penetrate and moisturize your hair.\\\\\" What this means essentially is it dries your hair yet doesn't dry it out.

It comes with a nice general brush and a couple attachments to allow more control of the styling process.

The one downside is that it runs a little louder than my other dryers have. It wouldn't stop from purchasing or using it, but that's something you should know.

This is my new everyday dryer so I'm happy. You will be too.

--Brockeim"

column14: I have very long thick hair and frizz is my number one enemy.  I can easily look like a hippie and typically nothing helps. No waste at the end of the bottle or trying to prop it up so that the product rolls down to where you can access it and no need to close anything up.  I will say that while this product works wonders on my hair, it doesn't do so all by itself so don't expect to be able to toss everything out leaving only this in your arsenal.  It isn't' the only thing you'll ever need, but you need it! column6: Case C1 Best Badger Shave Brush shave brush by Simpson
column13: I received a Pure Badger, NOT a Best Badger brush - Twice
column14: I received a Pure Badge,r NOT a Best Badger brush - Twice.  See photo.  Brushes filled with pure badger are often manufactured with the tips trimmed to form the final shape of the brush loft. This makes the tips of the hair blunt and gives them a scratchier feel on the face that some men find appealing for exfoliation.  I own three other Simpson brushes, Wee Scot, Chubby 1 and Chubby 2.  I bought the Case because I thought it would be a nice travel brush.  I have 13 brushes in my collection.  Both of the Case brushes that I bought are the smelliest I have ever encountered.  Soaking in Dawn overnight did nothing for the smell.  I finally washed them with a shampoo and conditioner several times over the course of a week and the odor dissipated.  The brush is densely packed and creates a great bowl or face lather.  There is plenty of lather for a three pass shave.  The bristles are the coarsest that I have ever felt.  I used one of the Case brushes for over 60 shaves and it still seems as coarse as the day I bought it.  I have several boar brushes that have softened up with time, but this brush never seems to soften up.  I will use my Wee Scot for travel because it is a much better quality brush and the Case still has a slight unpleasant odor.. Why two stars?  Sometimes I just want to use a brush with a lot of scritch.

column6: super nail White Powder, 0.75 Ounce
column14: When you think of acrylic powder, you think of dipping your brush into the bowl and pulling out a nice little Pearl of gel that you can stick to your nail and pat into the shape you desire. This is not how this powder is. Instead of forming a ball of gel, this powder turns into a runny, milky paste which is impossible to form. I tried using less acrylic liquid, and the powder didn't even clump, just stayed powder as I pat it onto my nails. I tried using more liquid, which just caused it to go everywhere. I've done acrylics on my own nails tons of times and have never had any problems like this. This powder doesn't form a workable gel ball, just turns into a paste that runs into the cuticle and all over the edges of the nail, making it look as though your nail wraps around your entire finger. I ended up doing one entire hand before giving up and ripping all of the acrylics (and the nail tips that I wasted) off. Don't waste your money

column13: I particularly love this kind or brush because they hit two birds ...
column14:
This is their spoolie and brow duo brush. I particularly love this kind or brush because they hit two birds in one stone.
I noticed that the spoolie side of the brush is quite different than the usual spoolies that I've seen.
This one is more packed with bristles. That maybe a good or a bad thing, but for me in general, I like it.
The brush side is made of synthetic fibers, this is great for creamy formula of brow products.
I usually use my nyx pomade for my brows and this brush is my new best friend.
The bristles arent too hard, or stiff, they are on the softer side.
This may be good or bad, depending on your needs.
I personally prefer this brush because I love a more natural look than a more defined, chiseled brow, so this is a win for me.
The length of the brush is perfect, it's not too short or too long, it gave me enough control whenever I use it.
I purchased this using a promo code for testing.

Don't expect the best shave of your life the first couple of times you use this type of razors. You devolp and strenghen a techinique and all of the sudden the burden that used to be the shave turns into an art that you enjoy, because you get very good at it. column13: Plant Therapy is a great brand, and the KidSafe line is wonderful!!
column14:
We live in Utah which is the home base for two big name brands in essential oils (DoT and YL), but I find them WAY overpriced and I hate having them shoved down my throat every direction I turn (figuratively of course). I came across the Plant Therapy brand months ago when I was searching for a good quality and affordable alternative to those big name brands. We've loved each one that we have tried (from ones to helps my husband sleep, a digestive blend, to an immune aid blend).

I have a 16 month old little boy that is prone to ear infections and croup. He just got over having croup in July (yes, apparently they can get it in the summer, who knew?!) and got tubes in his ears a week later. Between going to daycare in a home setting and interacting with his little friends at church, I wanted to find something that would be safe to use to try and keep germs down. I love that Plant Therapy has this KidSafe line of oils. Though it does specify that this line is safe for 2 yrs +, I feel comfortable diffusing it in my home with my son. I'll probably have this going 24/7 as cold/flu season approaches! There is nothing worse than a sick baby.
Note: Item purchased with a promotional discount to test and review.

column6: NOW Foods Lemon Essential Oil 1 oz
column14: During pregnancy, I suddenly got some small warts on my hands. I tried the OTC wart removers after my doctor OK'ed it, but it only made them worse. I did some reading and learned of some folks who had success using lemon essential oil. I figured it wouldn't hurt to buy this and try it out.  If it didn't work, there are plenty of other household uses for lemon essential oil so it wouldn't be a waste. I added a few drops of lemon oil with coconut oil and rubbed it into my hands like any other moisturizer every morning/night for 1 week. I started noticing a slight difference in the warts decreasing in size, and to my delight, after 2 weeks they were completely gone!  Easy and all-natural wart remover!

I am an African male almost turning forty and I just completed my third bottle of this hair growth formula. Two years ago I was diagnosed with Androgenetic Alopecia and I have been on Minoxidil, Ketokonazole 2%, 1mg Finpecia tablets, a hair follicle stimulating shampoo and hair growth vitamins. As weird as this may sound, I am feeling "accomplished" today. Background: I am an Indian born with very fine, silky, soft, shiny black hair but lost that lovely texture at puberty (and also because of harsh shampoo and rough handling). I am in my 30's now and still battling coarse, puffy, wavy-to-curly, frizzy, thick, easily tangled, crispy hair. Not a product junkie, but tried quite a bit of the serums, lotions and the like to tame my hair. Most of them either made my hair my hair greasy or didn't moisturize my hair at all or "stiffed" it out. And I was also constantly worried that all of these products must contain damaging chemicals ruining my hair in the long run (I had to use them generously after every hair wash. I wanted a more natural solution that wouldn't make me feel guilty while dabbing product on my hair. Actual Review - InstaNatural Argan Oil Hair Treatment: I wish I could sound less dramatic but this was THE product I was pining for decades! I used it as a leave-in and it quenched my thirsty hair instantly. It appears as though my hair cuticles are suddenly (and finally) behaving (as though a curse/ magic spell was broken). My hair looks and feels glossy, slick, smooth, flow-y, frizz free, WITHOUT looking greasy if I use the correct method of application. I can PLAY with my hair (this was unimaginable up until now). I am also dreaming about going for actual fancy bangs on my next hair cut. Precautions: Less is more. Hair can easily go an the greasy side if you are not watchful. For someone with thick bulky hair like mine, it requires section by section application (when i say "section", I am strictly talking about the salon style layered sections, NOT side-by-side and/or quadrant style). The product needs to be dabbed first, then lightly massaged onto the hair (I do this by rolling/loosely twisting portions of hair shaft like a rope) and combed out. I am a happy woman, who finally embraced her hair with love. (Slightly proud, but hesitant to admit). 2015-08-07 US 45185152 R1CW5VLBBOV37P B00A1MPACK 418264134 Clearly Natural Hot Flash Relief Spray, 1 Ounce (Pack 2) Beauty 5 0 0 N Y Works. column6: Organic Natural Deodorant \Sandalwood 2 oz\" All Day Protection - Aluminum-Free (NOT an antiperspirant)"
column14:
I try very hard to watch the chemicals I put in and on my body for many reasons, but especially since I have an MTHFR mutation and one of the characteristics of this is being inefficient at clearing toxins from the body, but especially metals. Aluminum is widely used in antiperspirant products, even some so-called natural ones, so I have been seeking out alternatives for my husband and I to keep the stink at bay and yet still protect our bodies.

Silvanapure makes this wonderful, lightly scented Sandalwood deodorant that takes the edge off of the summer stinkies. I honestly really like the light scent and I will rotate it with my other natural deodorants as the mood hits me. After awhile, I smell the coconut oil more than the sandalwood, so it is definitely light and not overpowering. Coconut oil has antimicrobial properties all on it's own and it's the number one ingredient in this preparation. Though it will help eliminate some wetness, don't expect it to compete with your aluminum based antiperspirants. Reapplication once or twice a day may be necessary, but you only use a pea sized amount and it should last awhile. It is soft, easy to apply and disappears into your skin. I've also offered it to my husband, as he's experienced irritation with another natural deodorant. He likes it, too.

I received this product at a discount in consideration of a fair and honest review, which I believe I have provided. I am a frequent and long standing Amazon shopper and would never recommend a product that I don't happily use myself.

column13: Fills a void in my facial regime:  No more papery look and feel--eye area has resilience and elasticity
column14:
This is a great find, and I am very glad that Joyal sent me a sample to try out. This gel is taking care of the area around my eyes like no other eye cream/gel has before. In the past I used a well-known and respected brand name product to plump up the area around my eyes to get rid of the small wrinkle lines there. When I used it, my eye area looked better; when I didn't use it, the eye area went back to looking aged. This product does MORE, and I could see it doing more from the very first time I used it. It continues to work even if I forget to apply it at the appropriate time, (morning and nighttime). I look at myself in the mirror in the morning and my eyes are nice and wide-open, vibrant and refreshed-looking.

This gel is formulated to be used specifically around the eyes--the area that has been avoided in my regular Vitamin C and Hyaluronic Acid serums. So, it really does serve a purpose, and for me, it fills a void in my facial regime.

The area under my eyes no longer has that fragile, papery look, and no longer feels fragile, limp and papery either. The area is soft and has an elastic and resilient feel to it. Also, after using it for three days, two impurities came to the surface and whatever it was sloughed off.

As to application, when applied without other fragranced toners, serums, moisturizers, I notice a fresh, light cucumber smell. And, the gel glides on very smoothly and soaks in almost instantly--even in humid weather.

*I received a free sample product from Joyal Beauty.

column6: Large Leak Proof Travel Bottles. Set of Four 3.3 oz TSA Approved Refillable Squeezable Silicone Bottles with Clear EVA Toiletry Case
column14:
[[VIDEOID:9ea7b348eb9bafc8c0662277f927c92a]] This travel bottle set comes with a nice, clear zippered case which keeps any contents from accidentally leaking on anything else you are packing. It also makes it easy for the TSA to look through it if you are carrying it on with you.

I love how soft and pliable the silicone is. VERY easy to squeeze for anyone who might have arthritis, or finds other bottles difficult to squeeze. These are very very squishy.

The bottles are 3.3 ounces which is an acceptable size to have on airlines. They come with labels already on the bottle caps. One for lotion, sunblock, shampoo, conditioner or soap. You might be wondering why there are 5 labels and only 4 bottles. Well, me too, quite frankly, but you are able to rotate the tab inside the cap to switch the label if you want to. It took me a little bit to figure it out, but I finally realized you move the tabs. Some are easier to move than others, and some get loosened after moving them once. So much so, that they continue to try to move on you when you put the cap back on the bottle. So, watch the label to make sure it still says what you want it to. It's very easy to remove, and put the caps back on.

There are also blank spaces. Even when a label is showing, there is still a blank space on the other side of the cap. You could use this for someone's name, or leave it blank. If you want to change the name of the contents to something else, there is still a blank label in the front if you move the tab to show it, but again, there's always a blank area on the other side of the cap showing as well.

These aren't just for traveling. I'm using one of the bottles right now for my dad. He has neuropathy, and I have made him a lotion to rub on his feet at night, and put it in this bottle. It's very easy for him to squeeze out, and apply it. I tried a firmer bpa free plastic bottle before, and he was not able to use it without my assistance. This makes it easier on me, and on him, since it's something he can now do on his own. Helps him to feel not so helpless, and able to still care for himself.

These bottles are a great gift, or nice to have for many uses. I have one in the car I've put sanitizer in, and that has really come in handy!

column6: SURFACE AWAKEN Therapeutic Treatment for Thinning Hair, Stimulate Revitalize 6 Oz (177ml)
column13: DOES NOT APPEAR TO BE THE TRUE SURFACE PRODUCT
column14:
Very unhappy. This appears to be a counterfeit product.

I have used Surface Awaken Therapeutic Treatment for several months, buying the product from my hair care salon. I have been very pleased with how well the salon-purchased treatment works - my hair was growing back noticeably and coming in dark rather than gray.

My salon ran out of product one day, so I decided to purchase it here on Amazon. The price was much less - and now I know why - this product is nothing like the salon product. It has damaged my hair, the new hair growth is gone, large quantities of hair are lost every day, and my hair, usually straight and thin, is now broken and frizzy. Large patches of my scalp are showing, worse than it has ever been. I have used this for a few weeks, hoping that I was just seeing things but finally the damage is so noticeable, that my husband, who generally does not pay attention to my hair, asked me "What's happened? Your hair looks bad. Did you change something?" Nothing changed except using this product instead of purchasing it from my salon.

I believe this is a counterfeit product. The vendor above is not the Surface Company. Buyer beware.

column6: Perfecto Deluxe Shaving Kit, 100% Badger Shaving Brush, Chrome Razor and Brush Stand and Chrome Double Edge Safety Razor
column13: A Review by a Beginner DE Razor User
column14:
I did a lot of research before buying a DE razor and I have been very satisfied with this product. If you compare what you get with this set to buying everything separately, you basically get a free razor when choosing the Perfecto. To be clear, this is an entry level product but it is great if you are on a budget or just starting out. For me, I had never used a DE razor and was not sure whether I was going to stick with it or not so the price point was very appealing.

Upon unboxing this kit, I was very pleased with the quality.

Razor:
The razor is solid and it has an even blade reveal that doesn't seem too aggressive. Just learning, I cut myself several times but that is just operator error when trying to get the feel of a DE razor. The milling on the edges of the razor was not perfectly leveled out but it doesn't affect the use of the razor at all. The razor's finish is some type of chrome overcoat that has held up well for the first couple of months since I bought it. While I don't think it will last a lifetime, I think it will last for years to come.

Badger Brush:
The brush is a good entry level brush that has a sort of break in period in which you need to rinse it out well. It also tends to shed a little at times so I'm looking forward to comparing it to a premium brush when I have a chance to upgrade. Nevertheless, I am very happy with the performance and the above quirks do not affect its use.

Stand:
The stand is great quality and was one of the big reasons I went with this set. Buying a stand separately costs more than I was looking to spend so to get it bundled with the razor and brush seemed like a great deal. I do not anticipate every having to buy another razor stand. Not to mention, when you get a DE razor, it looks great to have it displayed.

Overall, I would highly recommend this to anyone on a budget, just starting out, or looking to give an unusual gift.

I wasn't sure what to think of this at first. I was going to be rubbing mud all over my face and it sounds like something I did while playing in my backyard as a kid. But eh, why not give it a shot eh? I have to say that I was pleased with the smell, and though the kids looked at me at first like I was a crazy person, eventually they got over that. ;) I'm teasing, it wasn't that bad. My 9 year old asked why I was putting mud on my face though!
My toddler thought I was hilarious looking the entire time this sat on my face, which I let be longer than the five minutes because after five minutes some of it was still a little wet to the touch. I wanted to let it actually dry, you know?

I had a headache at the time, so excuse my less than thrilled expression in the photos!
I enjoyed the experience despite looking like I didn't. This seems like the perfect thing to do while having someone give me a foot rub as I watch netflix and pretend I'm totally more awesome and pampered than I really am.

My face was nice and smooth after removing this too. Though I almost went right to splashing water on myself, what you're actually supposed to do is rub the mask off of your face in a circular motion. Which causes it to shluf off similar to how skin does when you're using an exfoliating cloth on your arms and legs. So it was kind of messy in that regards.

I was given this product at a reduced price in order to facilitate my review and give my honest thoughts and opinions. I will say that this is honestly a great product and I highly recommend it even if you haven't ever done a mud mask and are kind of thinking it's gross. It's really not all that bad.

column13: This blend has a subtle aroma - Spicy and warm, though, not In-YOUR-Face potent. I was pleasantly surprised.
column14:
It is always a toss up when ordering a blend. Of course you are buying it for the benefits, yes, but you also want something that doesn't reek of tea tree oil, or smell like Mentholatum, am I right? This blend is none of those!

What You Get: (1) Zen Immune Boost oil blend in a 14 ml Blue Glass Bottle with black plastic screw cap. With batch number and Expiration date.

Ingredients (from label): JoJoba Oil (Simmondsia chinensis), Sunflower oil (Helianthus annuus), Eucalyptus oil (Eucalyptus radiata), Oregano oil (Origanum vulgare), Cinnamon oil (Cinnamomum cassia), Clove oil (Eugenia caryophyllus), Rosemary oil (Rosmarinus officinalis), Lemon oil (Citrus limonum), Peppermint oil (Mentha piperita), Frankincense (Boswellia carteri), Rosemary Extract (Rosmarinus officinalis).

PROs:

‚ûî Aroma. This blend has a subtle aroma. I was pleasantly surprised. The initial notes remind me of what Red Hots candies or Fireball Whiskey smells like, spicy and warm, though, not In-YOUR-Face potent (won't singe your nose hairs). Then as that initial cinnamon note fades, there is an underlying, clovey, very subtle astringent, lemony eucalyptus note - it is barely there, hovering in the foreground.

‚ûî Skin Contact. The oil goes on dry (absorbs quickly), it makes the skin very smooth - there is NO on contact "warming" effect from the cinnamon or clove oils.

I have very allergenic skin (eczema as well) that will react immediately and I had no issues with this blend.

The aroma of the blend on your skin does not stay at peak levels, it slowly mingles with your own olfactory scents - It is not noticeable after a while, so I don't see it being a problem being worn with perfume etc.

‚ûî Effectiveness. The ingredients speak for themselves. You can put drops on the soles of your feet, I think diffusing this is a more viable option.I find more benefit from the diffusing. Inhalation is very powerful, vs the membrane absorption.

‚ûî Eucalyptus oil (Eucalyptus radiata). Antiseptic qualities. Germicidal quality. Upon exposure to air, ozone is formed which is a well-researched antiseptic. ‚ÄúFever oil‚Äù. Combined with peppermint oil and sprayed on the body as a mixture of a deodorant and a temperature reducer.

The leaves of the plant contain a variety of antioxidant compounds, such as Rosmarinic Acid - which helps curb inflammation.

‚ûî Rosemary (Rosmarinus Officinalis). Stress Relief: Aside from the relaxing nature of aromatherapy and general inhalation of rosemary essential oil, it has been proven to actually decrease the level of cortisol in the saliva. Cortisol is one of the main stress hormones that are released during the ‚Äúflight or fight‚Äù response of the body to stress. Excess cortisol in the blood that may occur due to chronic stress can wreak havoc on the body, including its hormonal balance and the efficiency of the metabolism. A study released in 2007 said that inhalingrosemary oil and lavender oil for five minutes significantly reduced the levels of cortisol in the test subject‚Äôs saliva, which could seriously decrease the dangers inherent from chronic stress.

‚ûî Lemon oil (Citrus limonum). Health benefits of lemon oil include providing relief from sleeplessness. Using lemon oil ensures good sleep and helps people that suffer from insomnia. Inhaling the aroma of lemons can clear the nasal passages and sinuses, promoting good air flow and steady breathing.

‚ûî Peppermint oil (Mentha piperita). Contains rosmarinic acid, which helps curb inflammation-causing chemicals that may cause various conditions.

‚ûî Frankincense (Boswellia carteri). Immune System: Frankincense Oil is effective as an antiseptic, and even the fumes or smoke obtained from burning it have antiseptic and disinfectant qualities that eliminate the germs in the space where the smoke filters out. It can be applied on wounds without any known side effects to protect them from tetanus and becoming septic.

CONs:

‚ûî I noticed some spelling errors on the label in the case of the latin names. Someone should always spell check labeling. Always - this is your 1st impression to your customers.

Before beginning any new intensive alternative medical treatment, consult your doctor for advice, or an allergy test.

column6: MSmask Fashion Elegant Daisy Flower Nail Water Decals Art Transfer Stickers Nail DIY Decoration
column14:
These nail art decals are lovely. No they are not stickers. They are water decals. There are 23 flowers on each sheet. I have been doing my own fiberglass nails for a long time now. I usually use acrylic paints for my designs unless I come across gems like these.
I have used water decals many times, they are rather easy to use. I take an old pill bottle cap, remove the cardboard from the inside of it (if any) cut the decal out , lay it in the cap with very warm water, or use something that will not be affected by the warm water, waxed Dixie cups are not ideal. The decal will separate from the paper on it's own after a minute or two. If it doesn't, using blunt tweezers lift it off & with those tweezers place the decal on your " damp" nail, position the decal where you want it, then carefully blot your nail & decal with moving the decal. This will become easier & easier every time you do your nails.
Before you know it , piece of cake. Make sure there is no curling at the edges. Water decals generally do not curl, if that happens dampen the decal with a little water using the tip of your finger. Gently without moving the decal. It probably won't move, just take care. Waiting a few seconds apply two coats of your favorite top coat. Try from side to side, then cuticle area to tip of nail assuring it is covered around the entire edges.
For a little twinkle, sparkle on your nails check out the OUT THE DOOR'S NORTHERN LIGHTS. I use it alot.

column6: Double Edge Safety Razor
column14: Ok so I've had this for a couple of days now. I've upgraded from my van der hagen safety razor to this and I am thoroughly impressed with it. After much research I was torn between this one and the merker 34c. Both of which from what I could tell are two of the most popular ones out there. The reason I ended up going with this one is because my friend had it so I actually got to physically see it and hold it, and the handle is longer than the van der hagen I have and the merker 34c which for me personally felt very good in my hand and has been very easy to control. I've only done two shaves with it so far but it's been night and day difference between the van der hagen and this. Definitely a case of you get what you pay for. Not to knock the van der hagen, I bought it to see if I even liked this whole safety razor thing with out putting a lot of money into it and just from using the van der hagen I was sold. I'm never going back to cartridge razors and wasting my money on it. I'm in the military so I have to shave everyday and this is going to save me a lot of money and I get an amazing shave everytime. I'm still going through a sampler pack of razors to see which one is best for me but even with the blades I don't like I get a better shave than I did with my Gillette Mach 5!!! Since I've switched I can now shave before bed and still have a smooth face the next day when I get off of work! With the Mach 5 I had people wondering at 3 in the afternoon if I even shaved that day. This has also made shaving fun again for me, I actually look forward to it now. If you wondering about this razor I'm telling you you can't go wrong with this one, feels very solid and was very easy to get use to. If your on the fence about making the switch to a safety razor this is a great choice. My biggest advice is invest 30 to 40 bucks in the safety razor, buy a sampler pack of razors to see which one works best for you, get a cheap brush to start out with and a decent soap or cream. I'vebeen using col conk shaving soap and really like it. Big thing is do your research or you'll hack yourself up. It is a learning curve using one of these buts it's pretty easy. I can now finish my shave in less then ten minutes with this razor. There are plenty of videos on YouTube explaining step by step how to shave with one of these. The two guys to look up that I found to be the best are geofatboy and nick shaves. Both of these guys have plenty of videos that go into great detail on how to use a safety razor, what brush to get and the difference between soaps and creams. Most of the videos say to do three passes but I found it aggravated my face too much so I just go with the grain and against the grain and I have a baby butt smooth face. Dont be discouraged by your first couple of shaves because they probably won't be that great. You need to be patient and figure out your technique, what blade works best for you and what soap or cream works best for you. This is a very personalized thing to get into and everyone has different skin and hair growth so be patient and you won't be sorry.

column13: I made a mistake not shaking the bottle first before trying the smell to be sure I liked it. At first try
column14: I have purchased two scents of Adidas men's sprays. I made a mistake not shaking the bottle first before trying the smell to be sure I liked it. At first try, it was fantastic! My friend thought so also. I did not shake the bottle first! ALWAYS SHAKE THE BOTTLE FIRST BEFORE ANY USE AT ALL! In most every type of perfume or scented spray etc. The concentrated oils that make the smell settle to the bottom of the bottle leaving the rest on top with a minimum smell. Spraying a test before shaking up the liquid uses the best oils and leaves only the small amount of oils for mixing the complete bottle! Therefore, weak smell and short life. My recommendation, Shake, Shake, Shake. Don't forget to shake FIRST!

column6: Lipogaine for Men Intensive Treatment and Complete Solution for Hair Loss/Thinning, 2 oz
column14:
I am in my ffities and have been using this product for the last several years. It is the best one currently on the market. It definitely has held my hair loss at bay for those last several years. When I first used Lipogaine, I got quite a bit of new hair that first came in as fine hairs, but thickened over the next several months Lipogain has allowed me to maintain that new growth to date.

My brothers serve as a kind of control for whether Lipogaine is working. Every time I see them, I am suprised by how much their hair loss seems to have progressed. They ocassionally ask me why I don't seem to being blading like them. I tell them to give Lipogaine a try, but so far I dont think any of them have pulled the trigger.

In the past, I had tried both Minidoxil and Propecia. Propecia didn't seem to do much for me on the hair growth front. But, it did give me a bunch of nasty side effects. Not the right product for me. Regular 5% minidoxil worked ok for me, but defintiely not as much regrowth or thickness on new hair. There was a product that was over 5% minoxidil on the market, which worked well, but the FDA shut it down due to concerns about potential side effects. For me, Lipogaine work at least as well as that banned product and I have not had any negative side effects with Lipogaine. The banned product did seem to cause some odd, transient blood pressure drops (dizziness).

column6: Driclor Antiperspirant Roll on 75ml
column14: This product works as intended and am very pleased about this purchase.  I cannot express how well this works so long as you use it as instructed.  Apply at night, wash off in the morning, apply deodorant, and enjoy a day not worrying about whether or not sweat will begin to soak your clothing.  I speak about this primarily about underarm sweat.  I am an active person who works out 4 to 5 days a week.  I wear slim fit clothing where the clothes fit snug around my upper body, especially at the armpits.  I have been using this for nearly a week now and am very impressed.  I experience excessive sweating at the armpits that frequently becomes embarrassing in public.  I have had to use tissues to place under my clothing to limit sweat exposure on my clothes.  I frequently had to wear dark clothing in order to mask the sweat.  I have tested this wearing bright clothing and am extremely happy about the results.  The biggest drawback is that if you have any cuts or irritation, this product will find it and it will sting.  The stinging can last for a while.  On one day, I resorted to wiping it off later in the night because the stinging was keeping me up.  The product still worked the following day.  If you can get by this, you will be happy to have found a product that works.  If you experience excessive sweating each and every day you get out of the house for any activity, check this out.  You will be impressed.

column6: Silk'n Flash & Go Permanent Hair Removal System
column13: I think this is definietly worth it.
column14: I have only been using this on my face for some very stubborn patches of thick black hormone induced hair that showed up a few years back (think mens beard hairs, Im talking thick black coarse hair, 5 o clock shadow by days end, scratchy and sandpaper rough). After the first treatment all the smaller hairs and sideburns on my face were gone and haven't come back. My upper lip is gone too after one treatment (but that was lasered years ago so I didnt have that many hairs to begin with)  I just finished my 7th treatment on the 2 chin areas ( I have been using weekly on highest level).  I would say about 70% of it is gone and the last 30% is not growing back as quickly. Its still thick and black but much smaller patches now and not as revolting. I have yet to try my legs.  Treatments are fast, under a minute for the face and I definitely saw results immediately. I live 2 hours from a city with laser treatments and cant go every 2 weeks for a 5 minute session.  Taking care of this at home is well worth it.  Even if I have to do this monthly (or even weekly) to keep hairs at bay, one minute a month at home is not much of a price to pay to not look like Robin Williams (RIP).  My only minus is the sheer size of the machine.  For the face it can be a little unwieldy, but fairly large coverage area.

column6: Malteser Triple-cut Nail File with Cuticle Pusher & Nail Cleaner, 9 cm. Made in Germany
column14:
I bought this little guy in October of 2012. Little did I know then that it would become one of my favorite items.

First of all, this is NOT your typical emery board. Don't buy this to "polish" the tips of your nails. This, my friends, is a nail FILE. When I first got it, I thought I was being set up for disappointment. It came in a fairly cheap plastic case, was fairly small, and was extremely thin. I didn't think it could possibly hold out for very long.

Well, I am coming up on 3 years and both the case and the file look brand new. Still performing like a champ.

Pros:
+ Long lasting.
+ Shaves down your nail and takes off rough edges in seconds (I've used weekly filing instead of cutting them at times).
+ Great size for fingers and toes.

Cons:
- Took a little getting used to. As stated, this is no emery board.

column6: Cute Floral Makeup Bag for Travel and Home Perfect For Your Makeup and Cosmetics
column13: The size is definitely perfect for travelling
column14:
The "Glam" makeup travel bag is aesthetically pleasing by itself, it screams "vintage" sophistication.
It has a dimension of 10'x7'x3'. Personally, I think the size is just enough, it is not too big for travel, yet not too small to not be able to bring your makeup kit with you. The size is definitely perfect for travelling.
The inside pockets are transparent, this I prefer, because I can easily see and find the item I need.
That way, you are more organize while travelling, needless to say, it saves you time when finding the item you want inside the bag.
It came with various pockets, I am pretty sure it will fit a lot of makeup inside. The more interesting feature of the bag is the hook.
This is pretty genius, especially when travelling.
You can store the bag open if you want to by using it.
Another way is to hook the bag to a pole or a hook and make both sides more accessible.
The stitching is pretty neat, not a stray threads found *thankfully*.
It just turns me off when I get a product with very poor stitching.
And can I just say how pleased I am that they paid so much attention to details, that even the zippers are cute as hell.
Look at those cute heart (photo attached). Definitely a highly recommended product! The style, the functionality, and the price is unbeatable.
I purchased this using a promo code for testing.

column14: These scissors are comfortable to hold, super sharp--I wasn't paying attention and sliced the tip of my finger when I went to put them down--so be careful. They trip hair quickly, without splitting the ends. The stainless steel is perfect for cutting hair when its wet as these scissors won't rust. Very happy with these scissors. I received these scissors at a discounted rate in exchange for an honest review.

column14:
I purchased this for a Gatsby themed wedding I'll be attending next month. I have to admit, it is much better quality than I was expecting! column6: Ralph Lauren Polo Red Eau de Toilette Spray
column13: This is by far my favorite cologne! I bought it several years ago after ...
column14: This is by far my favorite cologne! I bought it several years ago after reading a few reviews and deciding I wanted to try it out. For me the scent does not project very far, but stays close and lasts all day, which I personally prefer. I am 23 year old welder and love this cologne, not merely becasue I get compliments and inquiries on it, I personally enjoy the scent of this cologne above any cologne I have tried.

column13: Works great on my husband and sons skin
column14: Works great on my husband and sons skin.  They both have eczema and very sensitive skins.  Tar soap clears in up, you do need to use regularly. Only issue, shower may get a little black just spray and wipe it down after use.

column6: Secret Outlast Completely Clean Scent Clear Gel Antiperspirant & Deodorant 1.7 Oz
column13: Great, but wait am I wet?
column14:
I received a sample size of this from bzzagent.com and Secret Outlast¬Æ Clear Gel Deodorant to test and review (complimentary).
I already am a fan of Secret deodorant, so of course I was excited to test Secret Outlast¬Æ Clear Gel Deodorant. They advertise up to 48 'epic' hours of wetness protection, odor protection, and no white marks on clothes.
I loved the scent that I received. The clean scent was nice, I didn't want anything was that was fruity or too potent. My sample package was a little on the empty side, which of course was disappointing, but I still had plenty to test.
I used mine on really hot days (95+) while hiking and geocaching. I loved that every time I really started to sweat, I could smell the deodorant, that to me mean that it was working, possibly working overtime. I loved that I could wear black and blue shirts, and I did not have any marks showing that I had put on my deodorant first. The one thing that I didn't like, was that the armpit areas of my shirts were not dry. This was very unattractive.
I would purchase this deodorant and recommend it because I believe in the Secret brand, and was impressed with how well Secret Outlast¬Æ Clear Gel Deodorant worked.
(even though I received the product complimentary, the opinions are 100% mine)

column6: Ladyshape Shaving Stencil - Heart
column13: Mixed Feelings on this Particular Product
column14:
I rate this product only 3 stars for the following reasons.
1. It claims to keep the skin taut - it does not.
2. It claims to be non slip - it is not.

I found it difficult to shave one handed in the upper part of the heart down the middle. The razor they include is like a bic razor - not much help in the upper heart area. I do have a electic bikini razor with a very small accessory which was perfect for getting into the top for a nice shave but if you buy this without a shaver with that small accessory I don't think your going to get the pictured results. In conclusion, I do like it in that as far as heart stencils go there are not many options. Other than stickers this was the only actual stencil I found. BUT, this one needs improving. So, if you have an awesome hubby to help you and a bikini shaver you will be ok.. If you buy this and think the razor they include is going to give you the nice heart shape in the box picture -- good luck.
If you found my review helpful - please click helpful found below my review and if you have questions I did not answer feel free to leave a comment or go to my profile and email me. Thank you!!

column6: Schick Hydro Silk TrimStyle Moisturizing Razor
column13: Hydro lubricant is a BIG mistake
column14:
I like the trimmer part of this just fine. But the "Hydro" part of the razor end is not well designed.
The lubricant comes out in little holes next to the razor blades and dries there. So when you try to shave, the lumps from the lubricant don't move (they've dried) and leave strips on my legs untouched by the razor. Plus the lubricant is kinda slimy gross goop when it does work. I end up scrubbing it off after (trying) to shave. I've even tried to scrape off the hardened lubricant to no avail. As you can see in the photo I've attached, the lubricant sticks out and blocks the blades. Scraping off the hardened goop is difficult to impossible.
The trimmer end is perfect. Why didn't I have one of these things before? Don't change a thing on the trimmer end.
Just ditch the goop.

I love this stuff! I have used it for about 2 years now and it has changed my life (or at least my how I feel about my feet). Zero stink. Ever. I tried following the instructions that said to apply it to clean feet at night, but, like other reviewers, did not find that worked well. For the first week or so, I applied it daily after my shower and before putting on shoes. By the end of that first, maybe, 7-10 days, my feet were completely odor free. Since then, I've applied it roughly every 2-4 days, more frequently if it's extra hot or I'm wearing shoes or doing things that make my feet sweat more. Over time, it seems to eliminate existing odor in shoes. Any shoes that had a little smell in them are now odor free, too.

I suspect that the people who say it's messy are applying too much. It's shocking how little you need to use and you really only use it on the ball of the foot. I have used about 1 jar a year. Yes, that's correct 1 jar a year. I put a little on my finger (like a grain of rice sized amount), dab it around the ball of my foot, then quickly rub it around. It starts to become less manageable quickly, so I don't leave it there for too long. The dabbing helps distribute it across the area, since it's less spreadable than some creams. I usually immediately put on shoes, but have not found that the cream transfers to floors or other stuff, I think, because I'm not using much. It is a little drying, so I occasionally use moisturizer at night.

You may be thinking - well, clearly this person didn't have anything like the ginormous foot odor problem that I have - not true. I could start to funk up a pair of shoes within a couple of weeks no matter what I did (scrubbing feet, putting shoes in the washing machine on hot) and could rarely keep shoes for more than one season. The standard drugstore remedies did nothing for it except add horrible deodorant fragrance into the mix. I'm sold. Beauty 5 0 0 N N Such a nice smelling versatile oil! This Lemongrass Essential Oil has a light and fresh lemony smell with earthy undertones. It smells amazing when diffused and is so relaxing and soothing!

It's fabulous as a natural toner too because it has antiseptic and astringent properties and it does wonders for balancing my combination skin. If your feet get sore from standing a long time like mine do, you can add about 10 drops to warm water and make a relaxing foot bath that will soothe your aching feet. It has antibacterial and antifungal properties as well, so soaking your feet will also get rid of athletes foot and toenail fungus.

Especially good for oily, acne-prone skin and lackluster hair, lemongrass makes an excellent addition to deodorants, soaps, cosmetics, shampoos, skin lotions and tonics. It has anti-fungal, insecticidal, antiseptic, and anti-inflammatory properties, and blends well with many other essential oils-like basil, cedarwood, coriander, geranium, jasmine, lavender and tea tree.

Lemongrass is also a natural insect repellant that works best on mosquitoes, ants, and fleas. You can add about 5 drops to water to make a home made mosquito spray that's safe to apply all over (except your eyes), and even spritz your dog's coat with it to repel fleas.

This is premium quality, therapeutic grade, undiluted and unfiltered steam distilled Lemongrass Essential Oil that's 100% pure and natural with no additives, fillers, or chemicals. Morning Pep offers it in a generously sized 4oz dark amber glass bottle, but with no dropper cap or medicine dropper, so plan to purchase a separate dropper unless you have a spare so you can dispense the right amount of drops without wasting any.

It detangles your hair, gives it body and shine, while making your hair soft and smooth. This spray produces results even if you do or do not use heat. I hate to dry my hair as anyone who has hot flashes can tell you. So this is just the greatest for someone like me who has unruly hair and needs to tame it without all the drama of heat. So if you want a great product for your hair this is my suggestion.

How And When to Apply;

Use on wet or dry hair.
Spray in sections and simply air dry and finger style or brush through.
Heat tools such as flat irons or blow drying give incredible shine.
Reapply or simply brush again after activities such as exercising or on the go when you don't have time to wash and style.
You won't feel the need to wash it out after a long day.

Directions;
Spray on wet or dry hair. Air dry for natural, long lasting leave-in conditioning. Brush or comb to activate encapsulated material. You may choose to flat iron or blow dry for enhanced shine and softness. You can reactivate throughout the day simply by brushing or heat tools.

(Please understand before reading I purchased from Target, not Amazon)

A while back I purchased this primer after running out of the one I had ; the price was much more reasonable then the one I was paying from Benefit, and I had heard it was one of the really good one's out there. So I decided to test it out and see if it was worth the raves it had been getting - sadly, it was not.

The consistency is very similar to Vaseline, but yet has a powdery feel in my opinion. It felt very strange and heavy. Upon application, I didn't notice any difference, except heaviness on my face. I decided it was one of those products where you needed to get fully made up to notice any difference, and went on to finish my makeup.

Within a little over an hour my face became VERY oily - even with my powder on, it was like an oil slick on my t-zone and around my nose. Now, my skin has always been oily, but never that bad. I used some blotting papers, but within another hour it was oily and icky once again.

The next morning, I woke up to a dotting of little pimples all around my nose! I had washed my face with my usual routine before going to bed - I have never broken out like that before, and my skin was nearly clear until the day after I used the primer, so I'm assuming it was that.

Personally, I don't recommend this product. It may just be not for oily skin, or maybe I'm the only one who had a problem like this. But with the experience I had, it was too bothersome blotting my face every hour and then waking up with a painful breakout. 2015-08-07 US 38351764 R3L1ZNXQXLJD96 B00H56KCUU 522630450 Maybelline New York Baby Skin Instant Pore Eraser Primer Beauty 5 0 0 N Y Five Stars Love this stuff! column6: Blue Lizard Australian Suncreen, Face SPF 30+, 5-Ounce
column14:
I've used four varieties of Blue Lizard -- Baby, Sensitive, Face, and Sport -- and I've posted the same review for each one. Baby and Sensitive are virtually identical. Face feels more dry, and doesn't leave your skin shiny. Sport seems to go on a little easier, but also has more potentially irritating chemicals than Sensitive or Baby (or so I'm told).

Here is the bottom line: Each version of Blue Lizard that I have tried will last through a 4+ hours of golf in direct midday sun, even when I'm perspiring heavily, and I'll go home with NO redness or burning whatsoever. (FYI, I am very light skinned and do develop a tan, but burn VERY easily, in 15 min. or less. I also perspire a lot, especially in the heat and humidity around the Washington D.C. metro area, where we live.) A little goes a long way, and if you take a few minutes to work it in, it stays put pretty well and doesn't run into your eyes.

It isn't the easiest to put on, and it takes some soap and water to get it off, but until they change the formula is some significant way, Blue Lizard is head and shoulders above all the other major-brand sunscreens that I've tried -- and I've tried a lot. It's also nice that the Baby and Sensitive versions get high marks for their lack of toxic chemicals, and we've used them on babies and toddlers with sensitive skin, and never had any problems, either with burning or reaction to the sunscreen. Strongly recommended.

column6: Waterpik Waterpik Ultra Dental Water Jet Flosser Wp-100
column13: took it to the UPS store and my replacement came in like 2 or 3 days (before my old unit got ...
column14: Okay, read the reviews and I ended up replacing an older Water Pik with this one based on the reviews and the price. When I received the first one (you know where this is heading...) the Power On button did nothing... NA-DA, zero.  I said okay what did I do wrong... read the instructions again and it turns out I actually followed them. I tried pressing down harder on the Power On button and felt a little vibration. I pressed down really hard on it and it turned on. Well, it's hard to water-pik your teeth when one hand is pushing down really hard to get the Power On button to actually work. The only way the thing would work was to press down really hard on the Power button. I went back to Amazon, l described my problem, ordered a replacement, printed out their UPS label, took it to the UPS store and my replacement came in like 2 or 3 days (before my old unit got to them. I was amazed at how fast I received the replacement. I tried the replacement and it seems to work fine.  The 5 stars is for Amazon's replacement policy. So far this replacement is working fine. I will update this posting if this replacement Water-Pik gives me any trouble. Amazon will charge you for the price of the replacement as well as the original if you don't return the first item back in 30 days... but that is to be expected... outstanding replacement service!

column6: Philips Sonicare Airfloss Rechargeable Electric Flosser
column13: A great flosser. It works very well and the convenience ...
column14:
A great flosser. It works very well and the convenience of having a flosser at hand can't be beat. I now airfloss after eating anything, not just after meals. I even airfloss just for the massage.

PRO: Works very well and removes food particles as big as flax seeds or chunks of meat. Not painful and very much like a gum massage. Fun to squirt at wife.

Cons: Only four stars because the liquid chamber could be larger and easier to fill. Note to Philips...have your design team sit on a couch in the living room and fill the Airfloss, that will help them develop a better way to fill the chamber and an appreciation for a larger chamber.

I highly recommend this flosser and will never be without one. It is easy to use and I will buy one for my office and one for the car since the one I have lives in the living room at home. I still floss with tape, but this is a good quick floss when I can't go the whole tape route; at night I even do both...airfloss, then tape. But the airfloss is a good way to floss anytime, anywhere and is even easy to carry in a pocket or purse.

My wife is as thrilled with it as I am. Especially since she gets to squirt me when she has it.

column13: I really liked this pretty little pocket mirror

I really liked this pretty little pocket mirror, but there were a few tiny little details that bothered my OCDness. Well, one thing in particular that bothered me with MY particular, was that it's slightly off. I mean, it still shuts straight, and it isn't off centered, but the little hinge just looks slanted to me. It doesn't do anything bad to the mirror or with the alignment or anything, but it just -bothers- me visually. That, and the red paint isn't nearly as vibrant as is pictured, just maybe a touch darker, but nothing terribly misleading. Also, it's a pocket mirror for a reason! It's not the type of compact that shuts and firmly stays that way. It swings open fairly easily. So having it in your purse and jostling it about may lead to bad things.

column14:
At first I was skeptical that the 3D Daily Cleansing & Whitening system was a ploy by P&G to make twice the profit off of the same product they already sell in a smaller tube. Thanks to BzzAgent, an awesome site that allows consumers to try and review products so that you don't have to waste money on the "highly marketed-brain-washed-advertising-to-buy-it" items; I can share with you the truth of the new 3D white Crest toothpaste (Thank you Crest!!).

Yes, you do have to get used to the taste but that's what I like! After finishing both steps, I have the tingling sensation of feeling like I just left the dentist office. There are two steps involved in this process but that is the beauty, you will spend more time concentrating on brushing your teeth thoroughly rather than up down, back forward, spit.

I have issues with my teeth, they have calcium build up that was an inherited trait, so they look like they have spots. This has been hard for me to whiten because the whitening solutions have always made the spots brilliant white and the rest of the enamel did not match. This Crest product has been consistent, not over whitening, which has made for a more even smile.

I am proud to say I fully support this product, maybe it won't work as well for you, but it sure has for my teeth!! Hope this helps :)

column6: Panasonic Ear and Nose Trimmer, Wet/Dry Convenient, ER415SC
column13: Good trimmer for your for your nose-scaping needs
column14:
I'm 40+ years old. I got hair growing in weird places, and in the normal places hair is growing like weeds. Take my nose for instance...

I've had this thing for about a month, and use it once a week (is that normal for nose hair to grow this fast?), and it works as advertised.

PROS
* arrived in the sealed OEM packaging/box
* instructions were so-so. the device itself is easy to figure out if you bother to spend a few minutes with it, but the marking on the device and as detailed in the manual are pretty small and it's not easy to see what you're supposed to be doing. But you figure it out.
* works wet, so you can clean it under the faucet. just like most **I'm going to hide this one here... for the ladies it makes a nice travel buddy (only one speed though) that doesn't look like a travel buddy thus eliminating any embarrassing TSA searches. SO I'VE HEARD** shavers/clippers these days. can confirm that i was not electrocuted when putting device under water, and more importantly that water did not get into the battery compartment
* it takes a single AA battery. this is a PRO to me because then I don't have to waste another outlet plug for a device that I'll use only occasionally.
* this thing whirrs like a champ - so much so that it really tickles my nose and I end up sneezing a bit from all of that flying debris. but when i blow my nose, there's hair bits everywhere, so yeah, it works

CONS
* it's not 100% easy to clean. you have to turn the head a bit to unfasten it, but it all seems delicate in that too much torque will snap a small but critical piece of plastic. would have preferred a a push-button release to get to this area.
* the manual is definitely lacking, but again this isn't a dual overhead cam engine (I have no idea what that is, I just remember it from 80's TV commercials... and it sounds cool)
* it's a slider on/off mechanism. i don't like sliders, i prefer push button on/off switches which i thought it was based on the picture

======

Can't go wrong for $10. I've had this Tweezerman nose hair clipper for years (the twisty one, not the squeezy one), and I now keep the Tweezerman in my travel kit and this one in the master bath.

column14: I recently was given a chance by Gillette to try their Fusion ProGlide Sensitive Shave Gel + Skin Care through Amazon.com. Gillette Fusion ProGlide Sensitive Shave Gel + Skin Care has provided me with an excellent shaving experience every single time I have used it. It is very soothing and refreshing to my skin. My razor glides effortlessly across face with absolutely no irritation. Additionally, I am left a a fresh, lingering scent (I am using the Alpine Clean scent) that is very pleasent. My wife loves it! I wholeheartedly recommend this product.

More so with this bar, with the extra moisturizers. The bar is solid in the hand, with a good grip, and maintains rigidity. It has a distinctive non-subtle smell, but it is neither obnoxious nor objectionable, nor one of those marketing-inspired "man smells" (think Axe and such). I think many ladies would probably like it too.

It lasts about as long as other 4oz to 5oz bar soaps that I previously used, so perhaps a mild advantage when comparing to 5oz bars, but then again, most people buy soap by the number of bars or the package, not by weight.

As advertised, it is nice and gentle on the face (avoid contact with eyes), I couldn't really notice a difference between it and a basic facewash. The issue with face washing is on subsequent baths. How many people would feel comfortable using the bar on their face after it went through a full body wash? Sure, one could use one side for the face, and the other for the body. Still, many will still say "no", so another possibility is to use two bars. One designated for the face, and one designated for the body. At some point, you can always transition the Face to the Body (so it doesn't linger around for too long) and open a fresh bar for the face. But this adds more bathing complications or perhaps not enough space for multiple bars of soap.

There is a long list of ingredients printed on the outer wrapper but not on the individual soap boxes. There's the usual avoid contact with eyes warning.

Prices and promotions go up and down, so I can't compare those. Personally I am not picky on soaps, so if I was out of soap and had to buy an 8 pack, I would probably buy this if it was within 1.5x or less of the price of the typical brands (Irish Spring, etc). column13: Awesome product, photo was not of the product I received.
column14: I've used this product before and I love it! I have been trying to go platinum from about a level 4.5 dark brown. In the past month (prior to using Olaplex) I stripped the color (Color Oops), then bleached and toned in one night then a week later I bleached once then toned and used a high lift color once then had to tone it again. I noticed my hair was feeling a bit angry and damaged and purchased a sample kit of Olaplex and did an at home treatment once a week for 2 weeks (along with some deep conditioning treatments and overnight coconut oil masks) and then I went to my stylist to help lift further because I couldn't get it past a brassy medium blonde. I brought my own Olaplex and she used it in the bleach but had to bleach my head 3 more times that night. I'm still not as light as I would like to be but am very light. I don't have any breakage and my hair is soft and strong. It's not stretchy or gummy when wet and looks great dry with or without any heat styling. THIS STUFF WORKS!  Needless to say, I was sold and decided to order the larger bottles for use at home and I found this listing. When I purchased it 2 days ago, the photo for the product showed the 17 ounce bottles so I bought them immediately. I just received the 3.3 ounce bottles. I see now that someone answered the question as to the size of the bottles and the seller has since changed the photo to 3.3 ounce bottles. I am frustrated with the false advertising and will not purchase from this seller again (Beautacious) but I will definitely purchase Olaplex again and again!

column6: Dove go fresh Body Wash, Mandarin and Tiare Flower
column13: Very very aromatic, but not a scent for a man
column14:
Five stars because -other- people love it. I personally was shocked at how aromatic this body wash is. The entire bathroom was filled with a strong "mandarin and tiare flower" scent. It is not a manly scent and I was concerned that I would be carrying that scent for the rest of the day. I think the scent largely washed off because no one commented on it and I even asked a couple trusted advisers if I smelled perfumed.

Other people, people without a Y chromosome, have review this body wash as follows: "It's nice <smile>".

As for the body wash itself, it lathered up nicely, rinsed off, and definitely moisturized. It's not that big a deal for me in the summer (as I write this) but I do dry out during the winter. I'll see if dove has a less scented body wash.

A note on body washes - I use them exclusively at home and keep the bathrooms stocked with them because bar soap builds up on the shower walls. My showers haven't had a soap scum in over five years since I switched to body washes.

column14: I bought four packs of these blotting papers. Compared to other brands offered on Amazon they are a great deal price wise. I have been using different kinds of blotting papers for my face for around 15 years. My forehead and nose tend to get a bit oily and shiny through out the day and I like to use them to remove the excess oil and shine. Like all other blotting papers I have tried they are very easy to use; just have to swipe them across your skin. They work well but I found I have to use three or four sheets at one time to absorb all the oil. I think it may be the material these are made of. It reminds me of very thin wax paper. I prefer other brands that feel just like tissue paper because I only have to use one at a time or rarely two if I'm extra greasy. Although I liked the price of these compared to others I don't think I will buy them again. I think I will stick to one that gets the job done with one sheet.

column6: Burma-shave Shaving Brush
column13: A Clydesdale of a brush. The only one you'll ever need.
column14:
I bought mine in 2002. I shave with a safety razor and my Burma-Shave brush at least 6 days a week.
Yes, it doesn't blossom like my English badger brush. But that's its charm. This brush does its job--and you know when you drag it over your beard that it's penetrating your pores and softening up those whiskers while building a great base of lather for your blade. Paired with a firmer shaving soap (like Col Conk or Williams), it will put a perfect lather on your face every morning. (Warning: it will tear through a mug of fu-fu glycerin soap pretty quickly and you'll be disappointed with the bubble water instead of lather. But I already give you credit for using a more manly soap, though.)

Is it rugged? I dropped mine in the shower in 2003 and it broke in half, but I put a heated pin through the two halves where they join and it has been perfect ever since. I have not experienced much bristle loss at all, and it is still pretty firm after all of these years and shaves. I rinse this brush well after every use, hang it properly to dry, and clean it every 6 months with Borax to remove any soap residue. Take care of it, and it will last you a lifetime. Highly recommend you get one.

column14:
The texture of this primer is all right when you put it on. It doesn't interfere with the application of makeup (which is good), and it doesn't conflict in any way with any of my other products (toner, serum, moisturizer, SPF).

However, it is not quite right for me. It has a decidedly pinkish tinge to it and it kind of makes my foundation look a little orange (I'm very pale so this is noticeable) by comparison. Also, for what it's worth, it is not particularly good at controlling oil -- by midday, my nose, chin, and forehead are pretty shiny. Also, it has a fragrance, which I would prefer to avoid in a product used on the face.

I'm undecided on the "brightening" aspects. I can see how this *might* help with that on someone with a somewhat darker skin tone than I have. But for now, the only people I'd recommend this for are those who want to add a pink tone and who don't have very oily skin.

column6: Professional Cosmetic Brush Set Beauty Makeup Kit + PU Leather Pouch
column13: A Plethora of Wonderfully Soft Brushes
column14:
I was sent these for review, and I'll never buy into the theory that receiving items for review somehow obligates me to leave a glowing review. You can check my other reviews to see the truth of this statement.

First, let me explain that I'm not a makeup artist. I'm just a woman who loves makeup and is always looking for the next best thing to help it go on the skin the way I want it to. That said, one of the first things I noticed about the brushes is that they are not labeled as to use. I really would have preferred a small label, like "angled eyeliner brush," etc. to help me sort out this bunch of brushes because I'm no pro when it comes to makeup.

However, the brushes themselves have been wonderful so far. One of the first things I did was tug on bristles to see if there'd be fallout; nope. I also held them up to see that they were uniformly cut, and they were.

All brushes are very soft, synthetic brushes. There are several blush-size brushes as well as several identically shaped eyeshadow brushes. I like this. I've just pulled out ones I need now and put the rest in storage for someday.

I think my favorite brush so far is the blush size. These aren't brushes that lay down a lot of makeup. Rather a bit of blush on the brush and applied to the skin makes a very natural glow that I don't have to then buff out. The blush is blended as I go. There are big, fluffy brushes, contour brushes, brushes that would be suitable for HD powder application, fine eyeshadow contour brushes, larger eyeshadow blending brushes, and eyeliner brushes galore.

I think this is an excellent kit for a makeup student, professional artist, or amateur like me who doesn't mind experimenting and learning.
