column6: Natural Whitening Tooth & Gum Powder with Activated Charcoal (2.75 oz Cinnamint)
column14: When I found this product, I was already considering making my own tooth powder and decided to try this version first.  The combination of natural ingredients intrigued me, having heard of them but never used them.  Prior to this, I was using my own concoction made with baking soda, but I didn't find it to do a better job than any other toothpaste I've tried.  It took a few tries before coming to the least messy brushing routine, but the results have been very impressive.  Firstly, I'll address the amount by saying I now use a 1/8 size teaspoon measure which I keep with the jar, pour it into the palm of my hand, and mix into a paste with a wet toothbrush. For me, that's enough to reload the brush a second time.  The unusual flavor/fragrance is very green, earthy and fresh smelling, and the stevia leaf powder adds a slightly sweet taste. A few days before I started using  it, I had just scaled my teeth and so I was interested in how long it would be before I noticed any plaque reappearing.  Now having used it for nearly three weeks, I've noticed none!  Nada!  Zero!  In addition, I've discovered that after rinsing, if I don't brush my tongue of any remaining powder, it will absorb and remove any whitish paste, leaving  fresh breath, and tongue and gums a beautiful, healthy pink, so no tongue brushing or scraping is necessary either!  I'll admit that I was in search of a natural tooth whitener and I have noticed an improvement but I think that's subjective. The antimicrobial ingredients, combined with the absorption nature of the charcoal, have won me over completely - the whitening effect is a bonus.  This product will be all I ever use from here on.  If oral health is your goal, and you're looking for a powerful, natural alternative, keep an open mind and give it a reasonable trial period, and I believe you'll agree.

column13: his is probably my favorite Bella and Bear makeup brush
column14:
his is probably my favorite Bella and Bear makeup brush.
The brush is made of synthetic fibers, it is so thickly packed and super soft.
I use a flat kabuki brush most of the time to apply my foundation, and this one is perfect for me.
It glides in my skin smoothly, it is also perfect to buff in the product evenly.
It gives me a very smooth finish, no streaks or lines of demarcation whatsoever.
It gave me a flawless airbrushed look. It is so easy to use.
I simply enjoy using it. I used it quite a few times now and never experienced shedding.
This is a great addition in my makeup vanity and I think I will be using it more often for my makeup.
They also included a brush guard for this brush, and that is always a plus in my book.
A brush guard will help maintaining the shape of the brush and protect the bristles from unnecessary shedding.
It is also very useful when travelling as it keeps your brush more compact and space friendly.
I purchased this using a promo code for testing.

column13: sonicare has better battery, slick design
column14:
im a 5 years oral B user, and after some considerations we decide to give a try on the sonicare.
in general, sonicare has better battery, slick design, also a very nice looking charge station and good travel case as well. all of those Oral B cannot offer.
but brush head will cost more, and if you want to share it with your family members, it will be painful to find a place to put brush head. and you may not feels comfortable as oral B, especially when your tooth is touching the plastic body of the head. Oral B only the brush is vibration, sonicare's whole brush head will vibrate. But after some time, we are getting use to it. i took one star off because of those.
In terms of the cleaning experience, all of them does good job. and sonicare were less likely to cause your gum bleeding. but it depends, different ppl may experience different thing.
Also worth mentioning is the battery, we have suffer a big problem with the oral B's battery life. at the begining, 2 weeks, 1 yrs later, 2-3 days at most. and their newer model does not support the 220V. very bad for the travelers. sonicare has a way better battery, at least from all other reviews.

column6: Vivica A. Fox (H175-V) - Human Hair Full Wig
column14: It's ok for the price and even though it feels more natural than other wigs I've felt, I'm not convinced it's human hair. I bought it for my daughter because she has thinning hair for  an undiagnosed reason and hopefully she regrows her own her while she uses this. The hair is totally dark brown with no highlights like the photo. That was good in my daughter's case because it matches her hair color exactly.There are no bangs like in the photo either. What I didn't like was that the scalp line in the middle of the wig near the forehead was a little too white and a little too wide.I fixed that by coloring it in with brown marker. Going back to the fact that there are no bangs, I found that having my daughter pull out some of her own baby hair from under the wig right where the bangs would be made it look more natural. The curls are pretty tight and tousling them a little adds to a more realistic look. It's a good wig and I would say it's pretty ok for $100. I'll be in the market for something a little more expensive and since I just got this ,I can't comment on how it holds up to washing.

column6: HSI Professional Glider | Ceramic Tourmaline Ionic Flat Iron Hair Straightener | Straightens & Curls with Adjustable Temp | Incl Glove, Pouch, & Travel Size Argan Oil Hair Treatment | Packaging Varies
column14:
This is an OK flat iron. I was looking for something to tame my thick, semi-straight, frizzy hair that wasn't too costly so I bought the HSI based on reviews.

Pros:
-heats up very fast
-slim and compact for storage
-various temp settings

Cons:
-Auto shut off timer isn't long enough, it has generally heated up and shut off before I'm even finished with blow drying my hair.
-Display is near impossible to see. it's located inside the handle and at an odd angle so you can see the color that it's lit but not the actual setting its on
-snags and pulls hair between blades

This is an OK flat iron for the price but when it's dead, I won't buy another.

column14: I received this as a gift from a girlfriend who discovered it on vacation. I use a liquid foundation that I was using a sponge to spread, but it did have streaking issues if done quickly. I have since bought two more; one for my travel case and a spare. I clean it by placing in a mug with dilute Dawn dishwashing soap. I let it soak for a few minutes, give it a little shampoo, rinse well, and let it dry by placing next to an air conditioning vent.

However, I don't like the fact that the powder is SO fine that even when kept in a drawer, right side up, and not jumbled with all my other products in a makeup bag, it gets everywhere every time I open the lid.  I feel like I'm wasting half the product each time I open it and I have to try to get the excess off the rim and my hand with my brush.  It's also so fine that even after holding my breath while brushing it over my face and waiting a minute, I still breathe in a bunch of it.  So in short, it's very messy and I wouldn't recommend keeping it in your purse or traveling with it to reapply during the day.  I've gone back to keeping a compressed power in my purse for touch ups and I only use this product at home, over my bathroom sink, and before I put on dark clothing.  If it had a way to close the holes during storage, I might buy again because it sets my foundation well and doesn't wash out my face and make me look more pale than I already am, but I really hate the mess and the wasted powder.

column6: L'Or√©al Paris Revitalift Triple Power Day Lotion SPF 20, 1.7 fl. oz. (Packaging May Vary)
column13: A decent lotion with some SPF protection
column14:
An overall good moisturizer, although it's almost as thick as a sunscreen rather than a lotion. It contains "Pro-Xylane," which is purported to be a plant extract purported to preventing skin from producing an enzyme that breaks down collagen (elastase) since collagen is important for skin firmness. It does have a pretty strong floral fragrance that fortunately quickly dissipates over time.

There was a pretty dry patch (thanks to a lack of recent sunscreen use, oops) that it cleared up quickly. It is rapidly absorbed and does leave skin much softer. Are the fine lines less apparent? Hard to say with any objectivity. It does seems to be a decent moisturizer and provides some sun protection (although it's not clear if it protects against UVA and UVB, although it likely does not as it's suggested to be used in conjunction with a broad screen sunscreen). Also note that it suggests reapplying every 2 hours, and it's not waterproof. Makeup does go on nicely on top of it (once it's absorbed).

It's a weird caution to say "ask a doctor" for kids under 6 months. It seems like this shouldn't be recommended for young kids at all, as hyaluronic acid isn't even recommended as a supplement for breastfeeding moms and salicylic acid can cause skin peeling.

Overall: I'll be continuing to use this and am likely to purchase it on my own after this sample has run out.

When I bought this razor, I replaced another model of Philips Norelco (sorry, I can't remember the old model number); the old charger and stand work just fine on my new razor.  If I were to need to replace this razor right now, I would definitely buy the same model.

column13: For all skin types - really makes a difference in the appearance of your skin
column14:
I have been using a shiritaki body sponge for quite a while now and LOVE it. I got it as a gift and knew what a difference it made - especially to my shoulder area where I am subject to acne breakouts. When I saw this one for the face (My other one is giant size) - I had to get it. I just read that the milia I experience on my forehead is the result of several things one of which is lack of good exfoliation. This Shiritaki facial sponge is all natural and an excellent exfoliant. I have found that with very little effort using this sponge (which is wet when first opened) my face feels cleaner and smoother. After you open it and rinse it out and use it, there is a small string that can be used to hang it up to dry. When I want to use it again, I soak it in water, put my cleansing lotion on, and then use this sponge to massage the lotion into my face. Then I rinse the sponge, dry it and repeat when I wash my face again. The natural konjac fibers that the sponge is made out of create a web-like structure that is very effective at bringing oxygen to the skin as well as exfoliating gently.

I RECEIVED THIS SPONGE AT A DISCOUNTED RATE FOR TESTING AND REVIEWING HONESTLY. It is a staple of my cleansing routine. I love it.

column6: Aztec Secret Indian Healing Clay Deep Pore Cleansing
column14: The mask arrived on time as promised. The tub is pretty large so I am pleased with the amount. I mixed the mud in a glass bowl with water and apple cider vinegar as directed with a plastic stirrer. I made way too much, and I only used three capfuls (cap from the vinegar bottle) of water and cider. It made enough mask for me, my daughter, and my reluctant teenage son... and I still had some left. So this is going to go a long way! When you add the mud to the water/vinegar mix it fizzes a bit, but that goes away as you stir. We applied the mask with our fingers and let it stay on 15 minutes. My face tingled and got really tight. Really tight!. I used a warm water wash cloth to rinse off the mask, and it came off easily. Our faces were a bit pink for a little while after, but the result was great! My skin was so soft. My pores were smaller and my skin glowed. This was my first ever mask like this, so I really didn't know what to expect, but I was thrilled. I am definitely glad I bought this and plan on using it once a week.

column6: DRAPER/HOLM - Natural USDA Certified Organic Lip Balm Set
column14:
Very impressive set of 7 ORGANIC lip balms. We go through tons of lip balm in my family. It used to be that I only had to use them in winter but I find that the air conditioning also makes for lips that crave moisture. Thank goodness for lip balms. But not all are created equal. I worked for a company that makes a famous lip balm and was privvy to the clinical studies that showed that the lip balm actually contained an ingredient that would leach the moisture out of your lips, thereby requiring more and more lip balm. It was (and is) a vicious cycle. With organic lip balms, I dont worry about that at all. Natural and soothing and nurturing - I feel good about using this product. And the fact that they are vegan, paraben-free and use recycled materials for labeling and packing are awesome in my book!

This set, as mentioned above has 7 flavors. The tubes are pretty standard for a lip balm except that they are not round. They are oval, which is different. The flavors come in Soulful Brown Sugar, Lovely Cherry, Spirited Orange, Peaceful Melon (which is like a honeydew), Wild Key Lime, Heavenly Blueberry and Charming French Vanilla and each flavor stands up to its name. Not overpowering - just a hint of the flavor. The balm glides onto the lips and feels very lightweight and protective. My family and I use them mostly indoors because they do not contain an SPF (which I guess would not make them organic any longer :( The lip balm lasts for awhile but does have to be reapplied depending on your conditions and environment. (like any lip balm).

I RECEIVED THESE LIP BALMS AT A DISCOUNTED RATE SO I COULD REAL LIFE TEST THEM AND REPORT MY FINDINGS THROUGH THIS REVIEW. I am honest in my assessment above and I do recommend this set if you are looking for a good variety of organic lip balms.

column13: Nice \sampler pack\" to determine the right size"
column14:
These are nice sleeves. A bit thinner than expected but they work very well. Only time will tell how long they last but now that I know what size I need I can get a three-pack of just that size from LeLuv for $9.99 - so $3.33 each which is reasonable even if they have to be replaced somewhat frequently.

My pump cylinder is 2 1/2" OD and these are a very tight fit so I suspect that's the maximum OD but maybe they'd stretch to 2 3/4"? There are some small "seams" left from the molding process but if they're contacting your penis you have the sleeve attached to the cylinder inside out.

Since these are silicone only water based lube should be used. Apparently the color is not always indicative of the size based on what's shown here and at this other page:

http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B00QJE3H7Y/ref=ox_sc_act_title_1?ie=UTF8&psc=1&smid=A3VZEZDUSWXB7M

column13: Low abrasive, little taste, not messy, good price!
column14:
It doesn't have much taste. It's not gritty. It doesn't have dyes, sodium laureth sulfate, other detergents, parabens and all that toxic stuff. It just has baking soda, calcium carbonate, fluoride and peppermint oil I wet my Sonicare in it, brush the bottom, dip again, brush the top, and rinse. I don't have a string of toothpaste drool hanging from my mouth to the sink with this stuff. Toothpaste burns my mouth. This does not. Diabetics could probably use this without any problem. The price is right. It came quickly. Heavenly Harvest, the company that makes it, has a lot of other good stuff in the shop. I will buy this again.

Edit: It's great for my teeth, which are sometimes sensitive. I added some extra peppermint oil. That worked well. I added some cinnamon oil. Not good. I felt the burn. I don't recommend adding cinnamon oil.

column13: Hadn't been to the dentist in 6 years, don't judge me!

It might work great for other people, but it's really clear to me that this type of Hydro Silk blades is not for me.

column13: Favorite part of my morning routine
column14:
I really love this product. I've been using it daily for about a year now and I'm just now buying my third bottle of it. It's expensive, but a little bit really does go a long way. Just a little dab on the finger and it lathers up like crazy with a little bit of massaging.

As for the smell, I personally really like it. It smells like lime to me and once it's washed off, it doesn't linger. It leaves my beard soft and feeling wonderful.

Don't expect this to keep your beard from being frizzy though. It makes it softer overall, but it doesn't help hold it in place. You'll need some beard saver or something for that.

column13: I've just added blonde highlights to my hair and the highlighted areas were very dry or hay like. I have tried high-end products
column14: I have been coloring (highlights etc...) my hair since I was 20, I am 48 so it's been awhile.  I've just added blonde highlights to my hair and the highlighted areas were very dry or hay like.  I have tried high-end products and every conditioner under the sun but have never had results like this with an over the counter product or even a professional product.  I bought the oil to replace my biosilk at my stylist's suggestion, I was so excited when I got the product and read it could also be used to repair damaged hair as well, so I tried it.  I applied it to my hair for a couple of hours and then washed my hair and applied a couple of pumps (fine hair and don't have volume so I didn't want to over apply) to my regular products and let my hair air dry overnight.  I was AMAZED my hair normally dries and looks frizzy due to color processing, my hair looked healthy, supple, and was soft even where my highlights were, the texture was not like my regular hair but the texture improved overnight, my daughter asked me what I had used!!!!  I am a believer and will continue to use this product.  Thank you for the other reviews that were posted and convinced me to at least try the product, I was not disappointed.

column6: Epilady Esthetic - Delicate Facial Epilator
column13: you get better at it over time as you recognize light pressure ...
column14: All of these type products require a feather-lite touch, practice & patience. You almost have to focus just on grazing the surface - it may not get every single hair every time, but it does get most. Not even waxing or creams will always get each hair. With all of these speed-tweeze type things, you get better at it over time as you recognize light pressure and growth direction. The bonus is how long the hair stays gone and that over long term use, it becomes finer or nonexistent I spent a little over 20 dollars for an emjoi 140 tweeze and this 3 tweeze for the face at CVS. Both work well and fast. Yes, it does hurt the first few times, but use ice or an anti-inflammatory beforehand & it wont bother you much. It literally is tweezing your hair out with the root, so pain is the thing most people forget is an unavoidable aspect. But not having stubble or ingrown hairs or long periods of time trying to tweeze the problem hairs that only increase with age? Totally worth it.

column6: First Botany Cosmeceuticals 50X Strength Hyaluronic Acid Serum for Skin ‚Äì The Ultra Moisture Magnet Anti aging Serum 0.5 fl. oz
column14:
I‚Äôve never encountered such a product before. Most serums are creamy and this is more like an oil, reminiscent of an omega-3 oil. It does have a rice/grain like odor, probably due to the rice extract that‚Äôs in it. It disappears after a while. I think this product is for a certain skin type or for a very specific use. I have normal skin and live in a humid environment, so for me the serum sat on my skin and didn‚Äôt fully absorb right away, making it difficult for me to put on my moisturizer.
However, for my mother who has very dry skin and a minimal routine, she LOVED it. It absorbed quickly for her and left no residue. She gets sensitive with how much Vitamin C stings and liked that this Hyaluronic acid had no stinging.
So I‚Äôd use this product, just not as a serum. Use it if: you have dry skin (really moisturizes and gets your skin with youthful plump), in the winter, or as a final moisturizer. My mother doesn‚Äôt like a lot of steps to her routine, so this is perfect for her. She just puts this on and she‚Äôs done. I‚Äôm only giving it 4 stars as I think it‚Äôs better advertised as an oil, not a gel. Otherwise, the product works great!

I would recommend giving this a shot if you're looking for a natural shampoo, but I won't be repurchasing it. column13: My strategy when I feel the need for a bit of exfoliation: Combine this scrub with regular gentle gel cleanser, work in together
column14:
When I first received this jar of exfoliate and scrub, I used it as a "stand-alone" product. I used very wet hands, just a bit of scrub and not too much pressure. It's great: Not too harsh/particles not too large or sharp; fragrance is un-assuming and very pleasant, and my skin feels so soft, with great buoyant texture after I've rinsed and patted dry.

I don't feel the need to use it more than a few times a week--definitely not every day. When I do use it, I still feel the need to use my usual Deep Clean facial gel cleanser. Always looking for a way to speed things up and get in and out of the shower quickly, I happened to hit upon a practice that seems to work superbly for me: Now, when I feel the need for a bit of scrub--when my gentle gel cleanser needs a boost--I wet my face and my hands, dip out a bit of this scrub, then pump my gel cleanser on top of it. I work it all onto my face together. Pretty amazing results, and just what I need a few times a week.

column6: Van Der Hagen Safety Razor
column14: I have been using a 2-blade Gillette Sensor since the 1980s. Those blade prices are now astronomical...I wonder sometimes if the price is going up to 'force' people to stop using the old versions and convert to a modern multi. The problem with a fat multi is that I can't get in close to shave under my nose. I have an average nose so how people with large one manage with a multi-blade is beyond me.  On a safety razor, it takes a few shaves to unlearn the 'bearing-down' technique you use with a multi. Instead, use a steady, light drag across the face using only the weight of the razor. The reason is that a safety razor actually shaves the face smooth...multiple passes shave closer...rather than drag on the hair to let the next blade chop it (like a multi).  TIPS: use it with Gillette Foamy 'Menthol' shave foam which was rated as the best in the US by a leading consumer magazine back in the 90's. Somersets Original English Shaving Oil is also pretty neat stuff...and buy some quality blades...I use the Personna double-edge which are excellent.

column14:
Replacing the blades [heads] every 6 - 12 months is still cheaper than purchasing a new Norelco razor. I've not noticed any irritation after installing new heads, just a better shave with less effort. Keep your old razor and replace the heads! You can't go wrong! Amazon's price for these HQ 8 Spectra replacements was the lowest I could find on the Internet. Shipped very fast!
Thes factory-authorized replacement cutters correct these problems. They are easily installed, but you must be careful to line up the stationary part wings with the slots in the shaver head designed for them or the cutters will not allow you to close the head properly. It is a simple positioning step.
Be very careful not to separate the movable cutters from their stationary housing, as they are carefully ground together for a perfect fit - and a good clean cut.

I have tried the newer norelcos that have different screen designs and have not gotten a closer shave than with this model. The blades stay sharp for over a year! It is rare to find a product that works exactly as it is meant to and exceeds your expectations for performance and longevity. That is exactly what these norelco blades and razors do for me. I highly recommend and won't change from this razor set.

column6: SweatBlock Antiperspirant - Clinical Strength - Reduce Sweat up to 7-days per Use
column13: I recommend this for amputees who have perspiration issues.
column14:
I'll keep this brief. I'm an amputee who has had to deal with sweat problems in my prosthesis for years. To compound the issue, I live in the deep south, where the heat and humidity can be stifling.

Sweat Block is the first product I tried when I decided to look for answers, and I need look no further. I really do not sweat at all where I apply it -- even while out in July and August heat -- for three of four days after applying Sweat Block, and for a few days afterward I sweat only a very small amount that is hardly worth mentioning. I'd say I have a full week's worth of protection from each application. Considering prosthetics can be quite hot, and Louisiana summers even hotter, I can't imagine a solution that would work as well as this product.

column6: Microplane Colossal Pedicure Foot Rasp - Brown (Pack of 2) + Bonus Pedicure Nail File 100/100 Grit
column13: FINALLY, A WAY TO REMOVE THICK CALLUSES QUICKLY AND EFFECTIVELY!
column14: Truly worthy of 5 stars for an impressive callous remover.  If you have thick callouses, this is the unit for you. This works so much better than the method I was using.  I was going to buy the motorized variety, until I found out the rotating cylinder is mineral based, like a grinding wheel.  I had thought the motorized units used a rotating rasp cylinder.  Reviews complained that application of pressure stopped such units from rotating.  I knew the motorized version would be insufficient as I WAS USING A DeWalt Orbital Palm Sander WITH LARGE GRIT SANDPAPER to remove my heavy callouses.  This still took a fair amount of time.  Also, when applying pressure and sanding for a while with the DeWalt, my heel could get painfully hot from the friction.  The Microplane Colossal Pedicure Foot Rasp is just the right size.  The comfortable handle allows a good grip.  The beveled head allows easy control.  The actual rasp area allows nice long strokes.  Dimension:  Total Length 10.75"; Rasp head overall 5.5" x 2.75", Rasp teeth area 4" x 1.63".  The size makes it so much easier to use than the egg variety, which I gave up on in lieu of the Dewalt.  Now the Dewalt can get out of the bedroom and back to the garage.  I am glad I bought the 2 pack, which lowered the price per unit.  Now my wife and I can have our own units.

column6: Radha Beauty Vitamin C Serum for Face, 2 fl. oz - 20% organic Vit C + E + Hyaluronic Acid
column13: REAL REVIEW - I did NOT receive this product discounted or free
column14:
First off, I did not receive a discount or receive this product for free. I also was a little skeptical and wondered if some of these positive reviews I read were real or fake? I'm guessing they are actually real because I'm happy to say I've found this to be a good product. Just so you also know, I am a huge product junkie. I am constantly buying/trying new face products all the time, expecting miracles in the end. Unfortunately, I never seem to be fully satisfied. For me to rate this 4 stars means I'm pretty happy.

I decided to try this 3 months ago after using Radha's Skin Clearing Serum (this is actually a good product as well) for a month. With this order, I also bought the Radha Retinol Moisturizer to use with it. I am in my 30's and have some very small fine lines forming on my forehead and get occasional mild breakouts. What I found works best for me is using this product on alternating nights. I use the Radha Skin Clearing Serum one night and then the Radha Vitamin C Serum/Radha Retinol Moisturizer the next. After 3 months, I can honestly say I am quite pleased. The small fines lines on my forehead definitely have a softer appearance. Some days, they are completely gone. For an "over the counter product", all 3 of these are quite good. If you are expecting it to work a miracle overnight, then you're going to be disappointed. However, if you use these products consistently for a few months, then I think you will be pleasantly surprised.

The only negative I can think of is the bottle it comes in. It gets exposed to air every time you use it. I read in the Q&A section that they only recommend using it for 3 months after opening. The Skin Clearing Serum and Retinol Moisturizer come in a much better designed system that is airtight. I wish they would also put this in that same type of container. I only use this every other night so I still have half of the bottle left. Since this serum is inexpensive, I don't mind repurchasing this every 3 months. I can't believe I just said REPURCHASE. I usually never try the same skin care product TWICE ;-)every 3 months. I can't believe I just said REPURCHASE. I usually never try the same skin care product TWICE ;-)

column6: Lord Premium Safety Razor Model LP1822L aka L6
column14:
One of the dirty little secrets about double edge shaving involves the weight of the razor. You always let the weight of the razor do the shaving and NEVER PRESS. That's counter to what you and I have been doing with cartridge/disposable ones.
Since the weight of the razor will affect the closeness of the shave (along with other variables), this lightweight Lord L6 is more suited for newbies; ones who haven't had a lot of experience with double edge shaving.
It's a good starter for those shaving their heads for the first time, too, with the long handle that can reach back there and the mild shave in case you screw up.
Do the math. Compare the most popular DE razors and you'll see the heavyweights like vintage Fat Boys and Slims get the job done.

column6: Luxury Shaving Cream For Men - Infuse And Prepare Your Beard And Moisturize Your Skin With The Must-Have Luxury Shaving Cream By UrbanXY For Men. BIG 4oz VALUE SIZE!
column13: Smooth shave cream - perfect size for travel
column14:
It's important to note that this is a shave 'cream' product and not a foam or gel. The product is pump dispensed and comes out as a small dollop of lightly scented white cream. A thin layer is all you need to get a smooth draw from both a standard manual razor as well as a wet electric shaver. The product works best on low growth areas and is not ideal for mowing down thick growth.

This product comes in a 4 ounce dark amber, plastic bottle and while this sounds like a small portion you really don't very much to get the job done. Also, the 4 ounce bottle makes it very convenient to pack along for travel (but not as a carry on item for air travel as the weight is above the TSA 3.4 ounce rule).

This UrbanXY shave cream works best when paired with another product from their Men's skincare line - [[ASIN:B010L938OO Pre-Shave Oil]] (product sample provided for review).

column6: Henna Hair & Beard Dye - 100% Natural & Chemical Free - The Henna Guys
column13: Medium Brown Henna - Great For Getting Bleached Hair Back To Brown!
column14:
I ordered this Medium Brown Henna Powder to get my bleach-ravished hair back to brown. Part of my hair was platinum blonde, part was natural brown. I was so scared that if I used box-dye on my bleached hair it might fall out because it is pretty damaged. Henna is a gentle alternative to dye!

I was worried the medium brown would be reddish/auburn and IT IS NOT RED. In fact, it almost seems to have some green tones to it. Thank goodness! I am going to apply a second time in a few days because it's a little light, but I am shocked at how close of a match it is to my mousy-brown natural hair color. In certain light, you can't even see the difference! I think a second application should darken it up. I read online that "henna is so messy", but it really wasn't so bad. Mixed it with water in a porcelain bowl, put on gloves, and doused my hair with the stuff. I didn't use a paintbrush or anything. Pretty much the same process/mess as a box dye. Use vaseline on your forehead!

A lot of people say their hair feels really nice and silky after - mine doesn't really feel any different, but then again it's pretty damaged.

column6: DHS Clear Shampoo 16 Oz
column13: Not the same product as before
column14:
I have used DHS Clear shampoo for many years and had been very satisfied with the product in the past. Because it hasn't been on my pharmacy shelves for a long time, I've had to special order it through the pharmacy, usually ordering three 16 oz. bottles at a time.

When I started using the first bottle from my most recent order, it quickly became apparent that several things had changed. First, the very convenient "toggle-switch" type cap had been replaced with a inconvenient traditional cap which has to be unscrewed and removed in order to dispense the shampoo. Then, when I turned the bottle upside-down and gently squeezed it, as I have done in the past, a lot more shampoo dropped into my hand than I had anticipated, much more than in the past. It was apparent that the consistency of the shampoo, which used to be more like a gel, was now much thinner.

I compared the list of ingredients on my old and new bottles, and I noticed the order of 2 ingredients had changed, and one ingredient called "Cocamide MEA" had been apparently replaced by "Cocamidepropyl Hydroxysultaine".

My theory is that these changes were all made with the following intention: to get the consumer to use up the contents of a bottle much quicker than before in order to increase sales. The new cap and the thinner shampoo makes it harder to control the amount of shampoo being dispensed. For consumers who still have an old bottle, I recommend saving the toggle-switch cap and use it on the new bottle. And thinning down the consistency of the shampoo means you have to use a lot more of it than before to get an equivalent lather. However, on rechecking this out, even when I used 3 times as much shampoo as before, I was not able to produce an adequate amount of lather.

The older I get, the more I wonder whether Karl Marx may have had some good ideas after all!

By the way, in reference to a previous review of this product, I could not find the words "New and Improved" or "Dermatologist Recommended" on the new bottles. In fact, I could not find the words "Dermatologist Recommended" on my old bottle.

column6: Wella Color Charm T18 Lightest Ash Blonde Toner
column14: This is the best toner out there! I have used this product for years and it is amazing for banishing orange brassy tones and removing slightly yellow tones. Perfect for those who wish to reach a very pale white blonde color. Follow the directions with this product because it can and it WILL turn your hair grey or possibly some other funky color like purple or blue if you do not follow the instructions. You can use with 10 or 20 vol developer. You can never go wrong with 20 Vol developer though that would be my recommendation if you have a lot of brass. And please do know the difference between "brassy" color and ORANGE! This product will not remove orange hair, if your hair is still orange after bleaching it then it did not lift enough and you need to re-bleach the hair to lift the orange out and then tone. If you simply put the toner over orange hair you will not be satisfied with your hair guaranteed and it is of NO fault to the product, but simply your own fault.

column6: Just For Men Auto Stop Chemical Hair Dye
column14:
Here's some tips:

Buy at least 1-2 shades LIGHTER. You leave it on the full 10-15 minutes, and your hair will come out DARK, and stay that way for over a week.

Don't want stained skin or ears? Take something like a Chap-Stick, and outline your scalp and ears. It doesn't allow the coloring to get to your skin.

Buy a $1 plastic toothpaste "roller". That way you can wind out the coloring completely, and when you put the cap on for storage, all the air will be removed because you're rolling up the tube.

If you only have grey on certain parts of your head, just do those - saves money and looks more natural ( as long as you've picked the correct color).

Buy at least 1-2 shades lighter !

Stay with the Auto-Stop - what a great invention ! Believe me, with the original, if you get distracted, you'll end up looking like Elvis - fat or original, he had jet black hair (did you know he dyed it from brown to black because his mother had black hair?)

column14: This crystal flower necklace is stunning! I love being outside, love flowers and everything nature (well, except spiders....).  Anyway, this necklace is perfection! The flower pendant is composed of stacked colored crystals, giving it a beautiful depth and shine.  The crystals are pink (my favorite), green, purple, yellow and red.  The chain itself is a design I haven't seen before, a rectangular style that's very pretty.  The chain measures 21" with a 2" extender, so 23" total length.  It fastens with a small lobster claw clasp that was a little hard for me to operate.  Now I just fasten it at it's longest length and slip it over my head.  The pendant has a 1.75" drop, and is beautifully designed on both the front and the back.  It comes in a standard paper gift box, mine included a free scarf as well.

US	25410223	R2YU4SN5BHILP5	B00FF7TO3W	804070600	18K Yellow Gold Solitaire Diamond Engagement Ring Round Brilliant Cut ( J Color VS2 Clarity 2.03 ctw)	Jewelry	3	0	0	N	N	READ THIS FIRST - BUY ONLY GIA CERTIFIED	DO NOT BUY FROM THESE PEOPLE! I purchased an emerald diamond ring for my proposal, it arrived just in time, I proposed and she said yes!! That is the good news.  I then took the ring to a jeweler and gemologist to be checked out. The ring was sold to me as a VS2 clarity, very good cut, E color.  Turns out it is more like an I-1 clarity with inclusions visible to the naked eye, the cut is poor, and the color is more like a J!!! This means the ring is worth about half of what it was sold to me as, and it nothing like described.  Nice gift for my new fiance to go along with our beautiful new relationship huh!!! I have contacted the seller twice so far with no response.  DO NOT BUY FROM THESE PEOPLE, IT IS LIKELY THAT THEY THINK THEY CAN GET AWAY WITH GIVING POOR QUALITY DIAMONDS BECAUSE MOST PEOPLE WILL NOT CHECK AND THEY WILL JUST GIVE THE RUN AROUND WHEN YOU RESPOND. I will update hear if I hear anything and get any resolution, UNTIL THEN ASSUME THIS IS A SCAM COMPANY.  08/10/15: UPDATE: finally got a response, they said they could have my ring certified (which it is supposed to be already) or could potentially replace the ring.  I will let you know when I get a response as to their replacement offer, and what happens during the process.  08/25/15: UPDATE: After weeks of back and forth, I finally received a replacement ring that is GIA certified, VS1, E color, and the quality that was specified.  I paid more for this ring but HDD made a concerted effort to compensate my emotional distress, and provide me with a good product at cost (at least that is what they stated.)  I have had the ring inspected, and it is as stated, so ultimately I ended up with a great priced ring, but went through weeks of distress, frustration, paying for inspections, paying for shipping, constant emails etc.   This appears to be a legitimate company with legitimate products at a great price - BUT BEWARE, UNLESS IT IS GIA CERTIFIED, IT IS LIKELY APPRAISED AT A QUALITY MUCH HIGHER THAN IT ACTUALLY IS.  The moral of the story, buy only GIA from these people and you should get a good deal.	2015-08-07

column14:
I ordered this item for a wedding I'll be attending next month. I only ordered one just to make sure the quality and look were what I wanted. It arrived in a lovely pink box and was just what I wanted! It didn't have the extra gems as stated, but it didn't need any, either. They were all there.
I liked it so well, I ordered a second one for my other hand. This one is the reason for the bad reviews. It came in a clear cellophane bag, still none of the promised extra gems, and it was missing one of the stones from the ring.
Had the second bracelet been in a box and intact, I would have given a five star rating, but the second was a disappointment. I'm just going to fix it myself instead of returning it. I don't want to take a chance exchanging it only to receive one that could be worse. I took photos to show the differences. Both came from the same seller, ZC Express.
Overall, it's well made for what it is. I have slender wrists and it fits me perfectly. Just enough slack to not pinch and leave marks. The ring looks better than I thought it would. I couldn't even tell it was stretched.

column13: READ THIS FIRST - BUY ONLY GIA CERTIFIED
column14: DO NOT BUY FROM THESE PEOPLE! I purchased an emerald diamond ring for my proposal, it arrived just in time, I proposed and she said yes!! That is the good news.  I then took the ring to a jeweler and gemologist to be checked out. The ring was sold to me as a VS2 clarity, very good cut, E color.  Turns out it is more like an I-1 clarity with inclusions visible to the naked eye, the cut is poor, and the color is more like a J!!! This means the ring is worth about half of what it was sold to me as, and it nothing like described.  Nice gift for my new fiance to go along with our beautiful new relationship huh!!! I have contacted the seller twice so far with no response.  DO NOT BUY FROM THESE PEOPLE, IT IS LIKELY THAT THEY THINK THEY CAN GET AWAY WITH GIVING POOR QUALITY DIAMONDS BECAUSE MOST PEOPLE WILL NOT CHECK AND THEY WILL JUST GIVE THE RUN AROUND WHEN YOU RESPOND. I will update hear if I hear anything and get any resolution, UNTIL THEN ASSUME THIS IS A SCAM COMPANY.  08/10/15: UPDATE: finally got a response, they said they could have my ring certified (which it is supposed to be already) or could potentially replace the ring.  I will let you know when I get a response as to their replacement offer, and what happens during the process.  08/25/15: UPDATE: After weeks of back and forth, I finally received a replacement ring that is GIA certified, VS1, E color, and the quality that was specified.  I paid more for this ring but HDD made a concerted effort to compensate my emotional distress, and provide me with a good product at cost (at least that is what they stated.)  I have had the ring inspected, and it is as stated, so ultimately I ended up with a great priced ring, but went through weeks of distress, frustration, paying for inspections, paying for shipping, constant emails etc.   This appears to be a legitimate company with legitimate products at a great price - BUT BEWARE, UNLESS IT IS GIA CERTIFIED, IT IS LIKELY APPRAISED AT A QUALITY MUCH HIGHER THAN IT ACTUALLY IS.  The moral of the story, buy only GIA from these people and you should get a good deal.

I purchased an emerald diamond ring for my proposal, it arrived just in time, I proposed and she said yes!! That is the good news. I then took the ring to a jeweler and gemologist to be checked out. The ring was sold to me as a VS2 clarity, very good cut, E color. Turns out it is more like an I-1 clarity with inclusions visible to the naked eye, the cut is poor, and the color is more like a J!!! This means the ring is worth about half of what it was sold to me as, and it nothing like described. Nice gift for my new fiance to go along with our beautiful new relationship huh!!! I have contacted the seller twice so far with no response. DO NOT BUY FROM THESE PEOPLE, IT IS LIKELY THAT THEY THINK THEY CAN GET AWAY WITH GIVING POOR QUALITY DIAMONDS BECAUSE MOST PEOPLE WILL NOT CHECK AND THEY WILL JUST GIVE THE RUN AROUND WHEN YOU RESPOND. I will update hear if I hear anything and get any resolution, UNTIL THEN ASSUME THIS IS A SCAM COMPANY. 08/10/15: UPDATE: finally got a response, they said they could have my ring certified (which it is supposed to be already) or could potentially replace the ring. I will let you know when I get a response as to their replacement offer, and what happens during the process. 08/25/15: UPDATE: After weeks of back and forth, I finally received a replacement ring that is GIA certified, VS1, E color, and the quality that was specified. I paid more for this ring but HDD made a concerted effort to compensate my emotional distress, and provide me with a good product at cost (at least that is what they stated.) I have had the ring inspected, and it is as stated, so ultimately I ended up with a great priced ring, but went through weeks of distress, frustration, paying for inspections, paying for shipping, constant emails etc. This appears to be a legitimate company with legitimate products at a great price - BUT BEWARE, UNLESS IT IS GIA CERTIFIED, IT IS LIKELY APPRAISED AT A QUALITY MUCH HIGHER THAN IT ACTUALLY IS. The moral of the story, buy only GIA from these people and you should get a good deal. 2015-08-07 US 20127651 R1ON8DAJFR3J5H B004UDJOQ4 953616000 14k Gold-Bonded Sterling Silver Tri-Color Interlocking Bangle Bracelets, 8\""

column6: 14K White Gold Solitaire Diamond Engagement Ring Heart Cut ( I Color VS1 Clarity 0.5 ctw)
column13: READ THIS FIRST - BUY ONLY GIA CERTIFIED
column14: DO NOT BUY FROM THESE PEOPLE! I purchased an emerald diamond ring for my proposal, it arrived just in time, I proposed and she said yes!! That is the good news.  I then took the ring to a jeweler and gemologist to be checked out. The ring was sold to me as a VS2 clarity, very good cut, E color.  Turns out it is more like an I-1 clarity with inclusions visible to the naked eye, the cut is poor, and the color is more like a J!!! This means the ring is worth about half of what it was sold to me as, and it nothing like described.  Nice gift for my new fiance to go along with our beautiful new relationship huh!!! I have contacted the seller twice so far with no response.  DO NOT BUY FROM THESE PEOPLE, IT IS LIKELY THAT THEY THINK THEY CAN GET AWAY WITH GIVING POOR QUALITY DIAMONDS BECAUSE MOST PEOPLE WILL NOT CHECK AND THEY WILL JUST GIVE THE RUN AROUND WHEN YOU RESPOND. I will update hear if I hear anything and get any resolution, UNTIL THEN ASSUME THIS IS A SCAM COMPANY.  08/10/15: UPDATE: finally got a response, they said they could have my ring certified (which it is supposed to be already) or could potentially replace the ring.  I will let you know when I get a response as to their replacement offer, and what happens during the process.  08/25/15: UPDATE: After weeks of back and forth, I finally received a replacement ring that is GIA certified, VS1, E color, and the quality that was specified.  I paid more for this ring but HDD made a concerted effort to compensate my emotional distress, and provide me with a good product at cost (at least that is what they stated.)  I have had the ring inspected, and it is as stated, so ultimately I ended up with a great priced ring, but went through weeks of distress, frustration, paying for inspections, paying for shipping, constant emails etc.   This appears to be a legitimate company with legitimate products at a great price - BUT BEWARE, UNLESS IT IS GIA CERTIFIED, IT IS LIKELY APPRAISED AT A QUALITY MUCH HIGHER THAN IT ACTUALLY IS.  The moral of the story, buy only GIA from these people and you should get a good deal.

They arrived in a black box, nothing too fancy but good enough to give as a gift, and came with plastic spacers on the end to help keep the earrings in place (or you can use your own). column6: Platinum Solitaire Diamond Engagement Ring Round Brilliant Cut ( J Color SI1 Clarity 4.1 ctw)
column13: READ THIS FIRST - BUY ONLY GIA CERTIFIED
column14:
DO NOT BUY FROM THESE PEOPLE!
I purchased an emerald diamond ring for my proposal, it arrived just in time, I proposed and she said yes!!
That is the good news. I then took the ring to a jeweler and gemologist to be checked out.
The ring was sold to me as a VS2 clarity, very good cut, E color. Turns out it is more like an I-1 clarity with inclusions visible to the naked eye, the cut is poor, and the color is more like a J!!!
This means the ring is worth about half of what it was sold to me as, and it nothing like described. Nice gift for my new fiance to go along with our beautiful new relationship huh!!!
I have contacted the seller twice so far with no response. DO NOT BUY FROM THESE PEOPLE, IT IS LIKELY THAT THEY THINK THEY CAN GET AWAY WITH GIVING POOR QUALITY DIAMONDS BECAUSE MOST PEOPLE WILL NOT CHECK AND THEY WILL JUST GIVE THE RUN AROUND WHEN YOU RESPOND.
I will update hear if I hear anything and get any resolution, UNTIL THEN ASSUME THIS IS A SCAM COMPANY.

08/10/15: UPDATE: finally got a response, they said they could have my ring certified (which it is supposed to be already) or could potentially replace the ring. I will let you know when I get a response as to their replacement offer, and what happens during the process.

08/25/15: UPDATE: After weeks of back and forth, I finally received a replacement ring that is GIA certified, VS1, E color, and the quality that was specified. I paid more for this ring but HDD made a concerted effort to compensate my emotional distress, and provide me with a good product at cost (at least that is what they stated.) I have had the ring inspected, and it is as stated, so ultimately I ended up with a great priced ring, but went through weeks of distress, frustration, paying for inspections, paying for shipping, constant emails etc.
This appears to be a legitimate company with legitimate products at a great price - BUT BEWARE, UNLESS IT IS GIA CERTIFIED, IT IS LIKELY APPRAISED AT A QUALITY MUCH HIGHER THAN IT ACTUALLY IS. The moral of the story, buy only GIA from these people and you should get a good deal.

column14:
[[VIDEOID:f6e44d72f8f677267afad600f26789e9]]This review is for the Sterling Silver Simulated Diamond Baguette Eternity Ring by SilverCloseout.

This is a very traditional design, and in fact would look excellent on even a male's finger. The design also lends itself to being stacked with another ring. You could purchase two of these and stack them together for maximum sparkle and shine.

The ring is smooth against my finger and doesn't pull or scratch. My skin is very sensitive. I guess this also means the plating on the ring is sufficient to prevent any base metals from irritating my skin.

The design and is wrap around. There are faceted crystals at every angle. I love this as if the ring becomes twisted on my finger; it still looks exactly the same. There is no front of back to this ring.

The ring is not so thick that it will bother the spacing between your fingers. The middle diamonds are flanked by upper and lower lines of small crystal flecks. It is very beautiful and very sparkly. 5/5 stars for design, craftsmanship and quality.

If you have any questions please post below and I would be happy to answer! I received a free promotional sample of this item for my honest and unbiased review.

This ring is absolutely beautiful. It is a twist on a classic design. The ring features 5 rows of wavy simulated diamond crystals that create drama on your finger as each crystal dances in the light. It is a show stopper and every time I wear it, I receive a TON of compliments.

The ring is smooth against my finger and doesn't pull or scratch. My skin is very sensitive. I guess this also means the plating on the ring is sufficient to prevent any base metals from irritating my skin.

Each row of diamonds has several miniature flecks all lined up perfectly. The diamonds are all set and very secure. The crystals are faceted to bring maximum sparkle with finger movement. It is absolutely stunning.

5/5 stars for design, femininity, and value for the quality of jewelry SilverCloseout makes.

column13: Tasteful and delicate, these earrings will make you look gorgeous!
column14:
These are beautiful earrings! They are just the right size -- large enough to be seen but not so large as to be gaudy. The tiny delicate diamonds catch the light and sparkle, and the sparkle lights up your face, especially your eyes. This is the kind of jewelry that makes you look and feel glamorous.

I would wear these earrings for almost any occasion. They would be appropriate for office wear, where you want to look professional, because they are tasteful and discrete. They would transfer seamlessly to cocktails and dinner in the city and you will feel polished and well-dressed. You can also wear them with to an evening event, because diamonds will always dress up an outfit.

The earrings are comfortable to wear. They are slightly heavy as you would expect, because of all the gemstones. But they are not so heavy as to be painful. They are easy to put in and take out. I like the built-in back clasp -- no tiny little slide-ons to drop and lose.

These earrings are great! If you are considering them for a gift, I enthusiastically endorse the idea. They come in a pretty box. She will love them.

column13: READ THIS FIRST - BUY ONLY GIA CERTIFIED
column14: DO NOT BUY FROM THESE PEOPLE! I purchased an emerald diamond ring for my proposal, it arrived just in time, I proposed and she said yes!! That is the good news.  I then took the ring to a jeweler and gemologist to be checked out. The ring was sold to me as a VS2 clarity, very good cut, E color.  Turns out it is more like an I-1 clarity with inclusions visible to the naked eye, the cut is poor, and the color is more like a J!!! This means the ring is worth about half of what it was sold to me as, and it nothing like described.  Nice gift for my new fiance to go along with our beautiful new relationship huh!!! I have contacted the seller twice so far with no response.  DO NOT BUY FROM THESE PEOPLE, IT IS LIKELY THAT THEY THINK THEY CAN GET AWAY WITH GIVING POOR QUALITY DIAMONDS BECAUSE MOST PEOPLE WILL NOT CHECK AND THEY WILL JUST GIVE THE RUN AROUND WHEN YOU RESPOND. I will update hear if I hear anything and get any resolution, UNTIL THEN ASSUME THIS IS A SCAM COMPANY.  08/10/15: UPDATE: finally got a response, they said they could have my ring certified (which it is supposed to be already) or could potentially replace the ring.  I will let you know when I get a response as to their replacement offer, and what happens during the process.  08/25/15: UPDATE: After weeks of back and forth, I finally received a replacement ring that is GIA certified, VS1, E color, and the quality that was specified.  I paid more for this ring but HDD made a concerted effort to compensate my emotional distress, and provide me with a good product at cost (at least that is what they stated.)  I have had the ring inspected, and it is as stated, so ultimately I ended up with a great priced ring, but went through weeks of distress, frustration, paying for inspections, paying for shipping, constant emails etc.   This appears to be a legitimate company with legitimate products at a great price - BUT BEWARE, UNLESS IT IS GIA CERTIFIED, IT IS LIKELY APPRAISED AT A QUALITY MUCH HIGHER THAN IT ACTUALLY IS.  The moral of the story, buy only GIA from these people and you should get a good deal.

[[VIDEOID:7d45f1c6464d40ddd013275a0929302e]]This review is for the Sterling Silver Simulated Diamond Chain Link Ring by SilverCloseout.

The design of this ring is very unique. It features chains of diamonds that are seriously a show stopper. Everyone notices the design on this ring. I receive so many compliments every time I wear it. I have never seen a piece like this before.

The chains are set with fine rows of small diamonds. The mini diamonds are faceted and hit the light perfectly for maximum sparkle and shine. There is a lot of detail in this ring for being such a petite piece. It is not too wide, and goes with every outfit. It can be casual or be carried into evening wear for a night out on the town.

The ring is smooth against my finger and doesn't pull or scratch. My skin is very sensitive. I guess this also means the plating on the ring is sufficient to prevent any base metals from irritating my skin.

5/5 stars for uniqueness, design and craftsmanship.

[[VIDEOID:ace8e52f223bb765ce598e79851eb3e8]]This review is for the Blue and Clear Austrian Crystals Round Disk Women's Pendant Sweater Chain Necklace Costume Party Jewelry by Qianse Jewelry.

I LOVE this piece of jewelry! It is unique and unlike any other pendant I have ever owned. The crystal work and chain are so quality and really look beautiful against my skin.
The metal is triple plated gold alloy. The chain or pendant does NOT irritate my skin. The chain is thin and feminine. It is a claw clasp and very easy to operate yet very secure. The chain can be removed from the pendant and used for other purposes. It is that beautiful white gold color so goes with so many of today's styles.

The crystal work is AMAZING! It reminds me of a million tiny, shining stars. Each of those stones is faceted to catch the light and create sparkle and drama. This is a statement piece. It is meant to be worn and noticed. I have received SO MANY compliments on this already. It is sustainable in size and weight. I love how this piece does not feel cheap; the weight suggests high quality materials and craftsmanship.

The piece comes boxed in a beautiful hard sided white box with gold accents. It is ready to gift give. It also comes with a cute complimentary scarf. I love how it is a complete package ready to present to someone you love. I purchased this for myself for a special treat! 5/5 stars for glitter, design and craftsmanship.

column6: Rhodium-Plated Sterling Silver Onyx | Jade | Aquamarine and Diamond Accent Pendant Necklace
column14:
This attractive necklace is the sort which must be exactly matched to an outfit to be appreciated, or worn against something black, but generic. It is not a "wear with anything" piece. Not just any ensemble will do.

The necklace itself is not the issue, as it is not unlike any other. It is the pendant. It is a darker green than pictured, looking very much like a small jelly bean (the apple flavored kind). As such, it has a plastic-y look about it.

With the right dress, matched against the right complex -- perhaps someone with green intonations in her eyes -- it can be perfect.

Anthony Trendl
anthonytrendl.com

column6: King Will BASIC Unisex 8MM Tungsten Carbide Ring Wedding Band Matte Finished Center Comfort Fit
column14:
First things first, I received this ring free for the purpose of review. Hopefully, my observations and impressions will prove helpful to you in your decision making. If you have questions, feel free to post them in the comments section, and I'll do my best to answer based on my own experience with the product.

What you're getting with this order:

(1) "King Will" 8mm Men's White Tungsten Carbide ring.

What is Tungsten Carbide, and how does it compare to Tungsten?: Tungsten is an element and Tungsten Carbide an alloy. You will find differing opinions, but many feel that Tungsten Carbide is the better material for a ring because it is essentially scratch resistant to anything but diamond. Both have very similar characteristics when it comes to looks, and the two terms are frequently used interchangeably as I believe King Will has done in the product description here.

The "King Will" 8mm Men's White Tungsten Carbide ring: This ring features a brushed matte finish with contrasting but complimentary polished beveled edges, each showing of the deep grey of Tungsten. The inner ring is comfort fit, meaning that it is contoured and is easier to slide on/off your finger compared to flat bands. This is a classic and somewhat conservative look that is perhaps most popular among this style of ring. I know it's the style I most prefer, and this band has replaced my gold wedding band which I no longer fit. I like its modern look and the polished edges reflect just enough light to draw one's eyes to the ring, while the matte gives the ring a modest feel.

Bottom line: This is a classic Tungsten Carbide ring that by nature of its construction is very durable and highly scratch resistant. It is well represented in the product description photos, The craftsmanship is excellent. I don't hesitate to recommend it to anyone looking for a durable and stylish band, and at its current price point one has very little to lose. Enjoy!e. Enjoy!

column14:
The design of this bracelet is beautiful, I have never seen anything like it! The blue Swarovski crystal has a ton of sparkle, and measures 6" fastened at its smallest, to 7" fastened with the extender. The crystal itself is about 3/4" in length. It has a lobster claw clasp, and can be a challenge to get fastened (I had to have my husband do it). I love it on though! I have a 6" wrist and love the way it fits on me! It comes in a standard paper gift box, and mine included a free scarf gift. I received it free in exchange for my honest review.

This bracelet broke the second time I tried to wear it, so I lowered my rating by one star. The link that joins the two sides by the crystal is weak, definitely a flaw in the design. It was an easy fix, I was able to attach it back together with some needle nosed pliers, but if I wouldn't have been able to if I hadn't found the ring as it fell off.

I purchased an emerald diamond ring for my proposal, it arrived just in time, I proposed and she said yes!! That is the good news. I then took the ring to a jeweler and gemologist to be checked out. The ring was sold to me as a VS2 clarity, very good cut, E color. Turns out it is more like an I-1 clarity with inclusions visible to the naked eye, the cut is poor, and the color is more like a J!!! This means the ring is worth about half of what it was sold to me as, and it nothing like described. Nice gift for my new fiance to go along with our beautiful new relationship huh!!! I have contacted the seller twice so far with no response. DO NOT BUY FROM THESE PEOPLE, IT IS LIKELY THAT THEY THINK THEY CAN GET AWAY WITH GIVING POOR QUALITY DIAMONDS BECAUSE MOST PEOPLE WILL NOT CHECK AND THEY WILL JUST GIVE THE RUN AROUND WHEN YOU RESPOND. I will update hear if I hear anything and get any resolution, UNTIL THEN ASSUME THIS IS A SCAM COMPANY. 08/10/15: UPDATE: finally got a response, they said they could have my ring certified (which it is supposed to be already) or could potentially replace the ring. I will let you know when I get a response as to their replacement offer, and what happens during the process. 08/25/15: UPDATE: After weeks of back and forth, I finally received a replacement ring that is GIA certified, VS1, E color, and the quality that was specified. I paid more for this ring but HDD made a concerted effort to compensate my emotional distress, and provide me with a good product at cost (at least that is what they stated.) I have had the ring inspected, and it is as stated, so ultimately I ended up with a great priced ring, but went through weeks of distress, frustration, paying for inspections, paying for shipping, constant emails etc. This appears to be a legitimate company with legitimate products at a great price - BUT BEWARE, UNLESS IT IS GIA CERTIFIED, IT IS LIKELY APPRAISED AT A QUALITY MUCH HIGHER THAN IT ACTUALLY IS. column6: King Will TYRE 8mm Black Tungsten Carbide Comfort Fit Wedding Band Ring Black High Polished Classy Domed Ring
column14:
First things first, I received this ring free for the purpose of review. Hopefully, my observations and impressions will prove helpful to you in your decision making. If you have questions, feel free to post them in the comments section, and I'll do my best to answer based on my own experience with the product.

What you're getting with this order:

(1) "King Will" 8mm Black Tungsten Carbide ring.

What is Tungsten Carbide, and how does it compare to Tungsten?: Tungsten is an element and Tungsten Carbide an alloy. You will find differing opinions, but many feel that Tungsten Carbide is the better material for a ring because it is essentially scratch resistant to anything but diamond. Both have very similar characteristics when it comes to looks, and the two terms are frequently used interchangeably.

The "King Will" Black Tungsten Carbide ring: This ring features a black tungsten carbide that has been polished to a glossy finish. This ring differs significantly from the product description photo in that the photo almost makes it appear like a brushed matte finish. In reality, it is a high gloss finish with a rounded band and no beveled edges. While a solid black ring may seem understated, this finish reflects a good deal of light and draws one's eyes to the ring quite easily. The inner ring is comfort fit, meaning that it is contoured and is easier to slide on/off your finger compared to flat bands.

Bottom line: This is a unique Tungsten Carbide ring that by nature of its construction is very durable and highly scratch resistant. It is has a high gloss finish that does not show up well in the product description photos, The craftsmanship is excellent. I don't hesitate to recommend it to anyone looking for a durable and stylish band, and at its current price point one has very little to lose. Enjoy!

I purchased an emerald diamond ring for my proposal, it arrived just in time, I proposed and she said yes!! That is the good news. I then took the ring to a jeweler and gemologist to be checked out. The ring was sold to me as a VS2 clarity, very good cut, E color. Turns out it is more like an I-1 clarity with inclusions visible to the naked eye, the cut is poor, and the color is more like a J!!! This means the ring is worth about half of what it was sold to me as, and it nothing like described. Nice gift for my new fiance to go along with our beautiful new relationship huh!!! I have contacted the seller twice so far with no response. DO NOT BUY FROM THESE PEOPLE, IT IS LIKELY THAT THEY THINK THEY CAN GET AWAY WITH GIVING POOR QUALITY DIAMONDS BECAUSE MOST PEOPLE WILL NOT CHECK AND THEY WILL JUST GIVE THE RUN AROUND WHEN YOU RESPOND. I will update hear if I hear anything and get any resolution, UNTIL THEN ASSUME THIS IS A SCAM COMPANY. 08/10/15: UPDATE: finally got a response, they said they could have my ring certified (which it is supposed to be already) or could potentially replace the ring. I will let you know when I get a response as to their replacement offer, and what happens during the process. 08/25/15: UPDATE: After weeks of back and forth, I finally received a replacement ring that is GIA certified, VS1, E color, and the quality that was specified. I paid more for this ring but HDD made a concerted effort to compensate my emotional distress, and provide me with a good product at cost (at least that is what they stated.) I purchased an emerald diamond ring for my proposal, it arrived just in time, I proposed and she said yes!!
That is the good news. I then took the ring to a jeweler and gemologist to be checked out.
The ring was sold to me as a VS2 clarity, very good cut, E color. Turns out it is more like an I-1 clarity with inclusions visible to the naked eye, the cut is poor, and the color is more like a J!!!
This means the ring is worth about half of what it was sold to me as, and it nothing like described. Nice gift for my new fiance to go along with our beautiful new relationship huh!!!
I have contacted the seller twice so far with no response. DO NOT BUY FROM THESE PEOPLE, IT IS LIKELY THAT THEY THINK THEY CAN GET AWAY WITH GIVING POOR QUALITY DIAMONDS BECAUSE MOST PEOPLE WILL NOT CHECK AND THEY WILL JUST GIVE THE RUN AROUND WHEN YOU RESPOND.
I will update hear if I hear anything and get any resolution, UNTIL THEN ASSUME THIS IS A SCAM COMPANY.

08/10/15: UPDATE: finally got a response, they said they could have my ring certified (which it is supposed to be already) or could potentially replace the ring. I will let you know when I get a response as to their replacement offer, and what happens during the process.

08/25/15: UPDATE: After weeks of back and forth, I finally received a replacement ring that is GIA certified, VS1, E color, and the quality that was specified. I paid more for this ring but HDD made a concerted effort to compensate my emotional distress, and provide me with a good product at cost (at least that is what they stated.) I have had the ring inspected, and it is as stated, so ultimately I ended up with a great priced ring, but went through weeks of distress, frustration, paying for inspections, paying for shipping, constant emails etc.
This appears to be a legitimate company with legitimate products at a great price - BUT BEWARE, UNLESS IT IS GIA CERTIFIED, IT IS LIKELY APPRAISED AT A QUALITY MUCH HIGHER THAN IT ACTUALLY IS. The moral of the story, buy only GIA from these people and you should get a good deal. 2015-08-07 US 3528417 R1SG70UG9R2YZT B00A6KQVCK 456811095 It's Sterling Silver 925 Cubic Zirconia 2.00 Carat Round Pendant White Jewelry 3 0 0 N Y Three Stars Ok 2015-08-07 US 32680850 R337LLNLION6CL B00R65VIJ4 48293631 kate spade new york \"Any Way You Slice It\" Stud Earrings"

I know next to nothing about pearls, but they appeared to be pretty nice. Because a couple of reviewers questioned whether they were really South Sea pearls, I decided to take them to a very reputable jeweler to have them verified.

The gemologist's findings were inconclusive. She said while she can't confirm they aren't South Sea pearls, it is unlikely--especially given the cost. She said they are more likely Akoya cultured pearls. (She did confirm they are cultured, and the posts are 14k gold.) The jeweler suggested I be careful with them, as the shells are thin.

Because I was fortunate enough to get them when the price dropped really low ($87), I'll keep them. As noted they are very nice, and, as the gemologist said, she couldn't confirm they were not South Sea. For the price I paid, I think I got a pretty good deal. One of my coworkers, who is very knowledgeable about pearls, agreed that they were a very good deal--and that they are of pretty decent quality, as well. column14:
[[VIDEOID:5e5d56a7304ce9fd93a737311c8b5fc4]]This review is for the "Heart of the Ocean" Blue SWAROVSKI ELEMENTS Crystal Heart Shape Pendant Women Necklace by Qianse Jewelry.

This necklace reminds of me of the movie Titanic. I wonder how many other people are thinking the same thing? It is a GORGEOUS crystal clear sapphire color. I purchased the one on the silver chain. This piece is a real show stopper.

The clarity of the crystal heart is superb. The heart is flanked by 3 lines of asymmetrical opalescent crystals. The crystals pick up the sparkle and add to the glow. I love how the necklace hangs from the chain. The asymmetrical lines are formed slightly off the top of the heart and the chain slides in and out easily.

The chain is another story. It is BEAUTIFUL and feminine. It is thicker but not too thick. You can remove the heart pendant from the chain and use it for other purposes. Both the pendant and chain are triple coated in 18k white gold. This jewelry will NOT irritate your skin. The shine is excellent and all the facets hit the light and cause drama. It is stunning!

5/5 stars for sparkle, clarity and design.

If you have any questions please post below and I would be happy to answer! I received a free promotional sample of this item for my honest and unbiased review.

column13: Really cheap, lousy stones in this jewelry set
column14: I was looking for a nice jewelry set to wear to weddings and formal events that didn't cost too much. I'm pretty surprised by the good reviews this necklace/earring set got. The moment I opened the package, I knew I had to immediately return them. This set looks incredibly cheap and the stones look so fake. Obviously I wasn't expecting diamonds but the stones look so much cheaper than cubic zirconia. And I have plenty of CZ jewelry that I love so I have no qualms with CZ. I wouldn't tell anyone to not give this set a shot since there are free returns but if you like decent-quality, don't have high expectations for this set. I ended up finding a nice set of CZ earrings and a necklace on Overstock.

column6: Church of Satan Satanic Cross w/Chain Stainless Steel
column13: Absolutely beautiful jewelry from a top-notch merchant
column14:
First off, Xerxes Enterprises had this item at my destination four days ahead of schedule, so the seller's promptness is amazing in this area.

Regarding the actual product, it is absolutely beautiful. It really does look identical to the pictures that are posted. It is neither too big nor too small. It feels thick and solid, but is not too heavy when put on a necklace and worn.

From a social and psychological standpoint, this type of Satanic jewel is probably somewhat "safer" to be seen wearing in public than a Baphomet or pentagram is. If you wear something with an inverted, five-pointed star, you are sure to get some hateful looks. Wearing this item is likely to generate a lot of quizzical looks, but not hateful or paranoid ones. So, if someone is new, somewhat passive, or shy about Satanism, but is still tempted to tacitly show the public a hint of this side of their personality, then this a great alternative to the more familiar symbols mentioned above.

If you like thin wire rings this is for you!

column6: 18K Yellow Gold Solitaire Diamond Engagement Ring Round Brilliant Cut ( J Color SI2 Clarity 3 ctw)
column13: READ THIS FIRST - BUY ONLY GIA CERTIFIED
column14: DO NOT BUY FROM THESE PEOPLE! I purchased an emerald diamond ring for my proposal, it arrived just in time, I proposed and she said yes!! That is the good news.  I then took the ring to a jeweler and gemologist to be checked out. The ring was sold to me as a VS2 clarity, very good cut, E color.  Turns out it is more like an I-1 clarity with inclusions visible to the naked eye, the cut is poor, and the color is more like a J!!! This means the ring is worth about half of what it was sold to me as, and it nothing like described.  Nice gift for my new fiance to go along with our beautiful new relationship huh!!! I have contacted the seller twice so far with no response.  DO NOT BUY FROM THESE PEOPLE, IT IS LIKELY THAT THEY THINK THEY CAN GET AWAY WITH GIVING POOR QUALITY DIAMONDS BECAUSE MOST PEOPLE WILL NOT CHECK AND THEY WILL JUST GIVE THE RUN AROUND WHEN YOU RESPOND. I will update hear if I hear anything and get any resolution, UNTIL THEN ASSUME THIS IS A SCAM COMPANY.  08/10/15: UPDATE: finally got a response, they said they could have my ring certified (which it is supposed to be already) or could potentially replace the ring.  I will let you know when I get a response as to their replacement offer, and what happens during the process.  08/25/15: UPDATE: After weeks of back and forth, I finally received a replacement ring that is GIA certified, VS1, E color, and the quality that was specified.  I paid more for this ring but HDD made a concerted effort to compensate my emotional distress, and provide me with a good product at cost (at least that is what they stated.)  I have had the ring inspected, and it is as stated, so ultimately I ended up with a great priced ring, but went through weeks of distress, frustration, paying for inspections, paying for shipping, constant emails etc.   This appears to be a legitimate company with legitimate products at a great price - BUT BEWARE, UNLESS IT IS GIA CERTIFIED, IT IS LIKELY APPRAISED AT A QUALITY MUCH HIGHER THAN IT ACTUALLY IS.  The moral of the story, buy only GIA from these people and you should get a good deal.

column6: BodyJ4You Gauges Kit Spiral Tapers and Plugs 14G-00G Stretching Set - 54 Pieces
column13: GREAT QUALITY, LOW COST, HIGH SATISFACTION!!!
column14: LOVE LOVE IT!!! Ordered these after searching all over for best deal, this was the most for your $ & cheaper than everybody else. I was hesitant to get em just bc they weren't on PRIME & I didn't want to wait for a long time to get em. This is my first time stretching my ears, I have many piercings but I haven't been able to start this for a long time bc in the stores, like hot topic & Spencer's it was like $12 for just 1 pair of tapers etc. I wanted the whole shabang. I have regular size, 18 to 14g ear holes, so was glad this kit starts at 14g!! Other kits started at 12g to 8g which would've never worked! I ordered these on 7/31 & received em the first day 8/6 on the estimated arrival date (8/6_8/10). Which was awesome! They probably would've been earlier but I ordered em on a weekend day. Came with ALL SIZES & PIECES SPECIFIED, ALL WERE IN LIL BAGGIES WITH THE SIZE ON IT, so no guessing, even a lil card with a conversion/ruler to know sizes. Quality is awesome! I will definitely use this seller again & would recommend to anyone who has any piercings for quality and low cost with high satisfaction rate!! Thankyou so much!!!  UPDATE now it's 8/25/15 it's been about 3 wks I've been using this ear stretching kit & I absolutely stand by original review! I am currently at 4g in 1 ear & 2g in other! I'm going down sizes faster than normal but all is well! I really love this set, I like being able to choose between wearing spirals in day & tunnels, tapers for bed... if this your 1st x as it is mine I highly recommend buying some vit. E oil & tea tree oil to help clean & moisturizing lobes. I use Vaseline with those when I put in new size & it's all good! Thanku again for awesome products @ awesome prices!

column6: GIA 14K White Gold Solitaire Diamond Engagement Ring Emerald Cut ( E-F Color VS2 Clarity 0.5 ctw)
column13: READ THIS FIRST - ONLY BUY GIA CERTIFIED
column14:
DO NOT BUY FROM THESE PEOPLE!
I purchased an emerald diamond ring for my proposal, it arrived just in time, I proposed and she said yes!!
That is the good news. I then took the ring to a jeweler and gemologist to be checked out.
The ring was sold to me as a VS2 clarity, very good cut, E color. Turns out it is more like an I-1 clarity with inclusions visible to the naked eye, the cut is poor, and the color is more like a J!!!
This means the ring is worth about half of what it was sold to me as, and it nothing like described. Nice gift for my new fiance to go along with our beautiful new relationship huh!!!
I have contacted the seller twice so far with no response. DO NOT BUY FROM THESE PEOPLE, IT IS LIKELY THAT THEY THINK THEY CAN GET AWAY WITH GIVING POOR QUALITY DIAMONDS BECAUSE MOST PEOPLE WILL NOT CHECK AND THEY WILL JUST GIVE THE RUN AROUND WHEN YOU RESPOND.
I will update hear if I hear anything and get any resolution, UNTIL THEN ASSUME THIS IS A SCAM COMPANY.

08/10/15: UPDATE: finally got a response, they said they could have my ring certified (which it is supposed to be already) or could potentially replace the ring. I will let you know when I get a response as to their replacement offer, and what happens during the process.

08/25/15: UPDATE: After weeks of back and forth, I finally received a replacement ring that is GIA certified, VS1, E color, and the quality that was specified. I paid more for this ring but HDD made a concerted effort to compensate my emotional distress, and provide me with a good product at cost (at least that is what they stated.) I have had the ring inspected, and it is as stated, so ultimately I ended up with a great priced ring, but went through weeks of distress, frustration, paying for inspections, paying for shipping, constant emails etc.
This appears to be a legitimate company with legitimate products at a great price - BUT BEWARE, UNLESS IT IS GIA CERTIFIED, IT IS LIKELY APPRAISED AT A QUALITY MUCH HIGHER THAN IT ACTUALLY IS. The moral of the story, buy only GIA from these people and you should get a good deal.Y IS. The moral of the story, buy only GIA from these people and you should get a good deal.
