Beautiful fine cross with a dove, just like I was looking for! The chain is a very good length, for me the cross sits just below that hollow between my collarbones. I am not sure what this is made of, so I take it off for bed and showering, and it stays nice and bright. The seller shipped quickly and the necklace arrived in a nice sturdy box packed in a padded envelope. The chain also manages to stay out of my hair (like many women, I have problems with necklaces twisting up in the hair at the nape of the neck), so no knots, and no having to cut the chain out of my hair!

The only thing I don't care for about this necklace is that the clasp that holds the cross onto the chain sometimes fips and because the hole at the top of the cross is so large it either turns the necklace backwards, or occasionally it's upside down poking me in the neck.

column6: 14K Rose Gold Solitaire Diamond Engagement Ring Cushion Cut ( G Color VS1 Clarity 0.45 ctw)
column13: READ THIS FIRST - BUY ONLY GIA CERTIFIED
column14: DO NOT BUY FROM THESE PEOPLE! I purchased an emerald diamond ring for my proposal, it arrived just in time, I proposed and she said yes!! That is the good news.  I then took the ring to a jeweler and gemologist to be checked out. The ring was sold to me as a VS2 clarity, very good cut, E color.  Turns out it is more like an I-1 clarity with inclusions visible to the naked eye, the cut is poor, and the color is more like a J!!! This means the ring is worth about half of what it was sold to me as, and it nothing like described.  Nice gift for my new fiance to go along with our beautiful new relationship huh!!! I have contacted the seller twice so far with no response.  DO NOT BUY FROM THESE PEOPLE, IT IS LIKELY THAT THEY THINK THEY CAN GET AWAY WITH GIVING POOR QUALITY DIAMONDS BECAUSE MOST PEOPLE WILL NOT CHECK AND THEY WILL JUST GIVE THE RUN AROUND WHEN YOU RESPOND. I will update hear if I hear anything and get any resolution, UNTIL THEN ASSUME THIS IS A SCAM COMPANY.  08/10/15: UPDATE: finally got a response, they said they could have my ring certified (which it is supposed to be already) or could potentially replace the ring.  I will let you know when I get a response as to their replacement offer, and what happens during the process.  08/25/15: UPDATE: After weeks of back and forth, I finally received a replacement ring that is GIA certified, VS1, E color, and the quality that was specified.  I paid more for this ring but HDD made a concerted effort to compensate my emotional distress, and provide me with a good product at cost (at least that is what they stated.)  I have had the ring inspected, and it is as stated, so ultimately I ended up with a great priced ring, but went through weeks of distress, frustration, paying for inspections, paying for shipping, constant emails etc.   This appears to be a legitimate company with legitimate products at a great price - BUT BEWARE, UNLESS IT IS GIA CERTIFIED, IT IS LIKELY APPRAISED AT A QUALITY MUCH HIGHER THAN IT ACTUALLY IS.  The moral of the story, buy only GIA from these people and you should get a good deal.

column13: It's a very cute ring and if you love Russia you need to have it!!
column14:
I have always loved Russia and anything having to do with said country, so when I saw this ring I had to get it!!

It arrived in a fairly large envelope, a little big for the box I think. The package box was simple and white, and then I opened it I was so surprised!! I didn't know it came in a case!

It's a very sturdy case, brown all around with a metal sheen in the middle(and also the nameplate) that feels like the plastic folders that when you scratch it it sounds like a dj record, you know those? With a snap closure using the raised name plate, showing the logo and the name. Inside the cute case was the ring in a small zip lock bag. The ring is a deep, semi-shiny black, and quite heavy(I've never had a carbide ring so maybe that's what that feels like).

The hammer and sickle are not the way the actual hammer and sickle are, it's sort of backwards.

It's a very cute ring and if you love Russia you need to have it!! It'd actually be great as a gift because of the case.

I received this item in exchange for my honest review.

column14:
I bought these rings for an anniversary present for my boyfriend and I. At first there were some complications with the order. However, thanks to Amazon support and emails between the third party seller, we were able to resolve this initial issues. For those of you who are wondering; yes they are separately priced, and yes engraving cost extra. I called Amazon support after making the order and purchase and asked if engraving cost extra because I could not see that information on this purchase. The woman on the phone told me she didn't believe engraving was extra so she put in the order for the engravement. Once the email that the woman on tech support sent to the third part distributor came in my inbox, I realized she had spelt my boyfriends name wrong. So I had the call back once again. A man from tech support answer and at first he had no idea was I was saying. No offense to anyone he had a very thick accent, and I'm pretty sure he had troubles understanding me as well. Anyways after a long conversation with him, we finally came to a conclusion and he sent me an email that I confirmed was the correct spelling. After about an hour, the third party responded to our emails. They were very friendly and simply informed me that engraving would be an extra $5 (I believe) per ring. I didn't end up going through with engraving and told them to proceed with the original order.

About a week later (to my surprise, they weren't supposed to be delivered for another couple weeks) they showed up :) the heart shaped stone on the woman's ring is very delicate and small, so if you're looking for a big stone this will be a disappointment. If you're okay with that, then you will love it. It's not the sturdiest metal in the world, but it's very shiny and real looking. My boyfriend really loves his ring and he wears it all the time, as do I.

If you're looking for a very meaningful and special anniversary present this is it!

Turns out it is more like an I-1 clarity with inclusions visible to the naked eye, the cut is poor, and the color is more like a J!!! This means the ring is worth about half of what it was sold to me as, and it nothing like described.  Nice gift for my new fiance to go along with our beautiful new relationship huh!!! I have contacted the seller twice so far with no response.  DO NOT BUY FROM THESE PEOPLE, IT IS LIKELY THAT THEY THINK THEY CAN GET AWAY WITH GIVING POOR QUALITY DIAMONDS BECAUSE MOST PEOPLE WILL NOT CHECK AND THEY WILL JUST GIVE THE RUN AROUND WHEN YOU RESPOND. I will update hear if I hear anything and get any resolution, UNTIL THEN ASSUME THIS IS A SCAM COMPANY.  08/10/15: UPDATE: finally got a response, they said they could have my ring certified (which it is supposed to be already) or could potentially replace the ring.  I will let you know when I get a response as to their replacement offer, and what happens during the process.  08/25/15: UPDATE: After weeks of back and forth, I finally received a replacement ring that is GIA certified, VS1, E color, and the quality that was specified.  I paid more for this ring but HDD made a concerted effort to compensate my emotional distress, and provide me with a good product at cost (at least that is what they stated.)  I have had the ring inspected, and it is as stated, so ultimately I ended up with a great priced ring, but went through weeks of distress, frustration, paying for inspections, paying for shipping, constant emails etc.   This appears to be a legitimate company with legitimate products at a great price - BUT BEWARE, UNLESS IT IS GIA CERTIFIED, IT IS LIKELY APPRAISED AT A QUALITY MUCH HIGHER THAN IT ACTUALLY IS.  The moral of the story, buy only GIA from these people and you should get a good deal.
